Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.40,0:02:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}片名：埃及妖后{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.30,0:05:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}于是，当法萨力亚…{\r}\NAnd so it fell out that at Pharsalia...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.27,0:05:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在罗马发生了最惨烈的流血内战{\r}\N...the great might and manhood of Rome met in bloody civil war...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.64,0:05:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒的部队打败了庞培的军队{\r}\N...and Caesar's legions destroyed those of the great Pompey...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.98,0:05:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒成为罗马唯一的统治者{\r}\N...so that now only Caesar stood at the head of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.75,0:05:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如其他胜战一样他并不觉得高兴{\r}\NBut there was no joy for Caesar as in his other triumphs...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.59,0:05:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}因为无数战死、被埋没…{\r}\N...for the dead which his legions counted and buried and burned...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.96,0:05:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}或被烧死的军人都是他的同伴{\r}\N...were their own countrymen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.73,0:05:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}焚烧罗马士兵尸体产生的黑烟 与臭味同样又黑…{\r}\NThe smoke of burning Roman dead is just as black...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.63,0:05:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}又臭{\r}\N...and the stink no less.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.24,0:05:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是庞培希望这样，不是我{\r}\NIt was Pompey, not I, who wanted it so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.27,0:05:47.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}希望我所讲的说话 历史会忠实地记下来{\r}\NLet what I have said be set down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.15,0:05:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们可以站起来{\r}\NYou may stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.48,0:05:59.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}面对我，不要太自愧也不必故作高傲{\r}\NDo not try and impress me by looking either too penitent or too proud.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.75,0:06:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}身为战场军官你们为了庞培吃尽苦头{\r}\NAs field officers, you fought miserably for Pompey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.46,0:06:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们的士兵可编入我的部队{\r}\NMen under your command will be permitted to enlist in my legions...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.13,0:06:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}跟罗焉人一样光荣地返回罗马城{\r}\N...and returned to Rome as Romans.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.76,0:06:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们将拥有相同的权力{\r}\NYou shall have the same privilege.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.83,0:06:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我并非如此宽宏大量 你们将会被监视{\r}\NI'm not magnanimous. Your names are marked. You'll be watched.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.44,0:06:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一有叛变或懦夫行为立刻处死{\r}\NFirst sign of treachery, you'll be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.04,0:06:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}什么事，弗拉维乌斯？安东尼？{\r}\NWhat is it, Flavius? Antony?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.04,0:06:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}哦，是坎尼迪斯 希望你有庞培的消息{\r}\NOh, yes. Canidius. With news of Pompey, I hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.01,0:07:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 凯撒万岁！ - 为我干杯，坎尼迪斯{\r}\N-Hail Caesar! -Drink that in my name, Canidius.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.35,0:07:05.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}敬马克安东尼的骑兵 凯撒的左右手{\r}\NTo all Marc Antony's cavalry, Caesar's left wing and right arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.09,0:07:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}庞培有什么消息？{\r}\NWhat news of Pompey, or what's left of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.66,0:07:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒，庞培逃走了{\r}\NPompey's gone, Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.26,0:07:14.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}假装成商贩溜走了{\r}\NSlipped through our fingers, disguised as a peddler.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.86,0:07:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 他丢下军队不理 - 逃到哪里？{\r}\N-Leaving most of his merchandise. -Gone? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.37,0:07:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听说他事先准备了一艘大船 目的地是埃及{\r}\NHe has a galley waiting at the coast. Provision enough for Egypt, they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.04,0:07:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及？很可能埃及人亏欠他很多{\r}\NEgypt. Possibly. They owe him a great deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.24,0:07:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他会要求庇护，借钱，拖时间{\r}\NHe'll ask for sanctuary. Borrow money, borrow time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.95,0:07:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我以为结束了，看来还没有{\r}\NI thought it was over. It seems it's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.18,0:07:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}鲁非欧，问占卜师{\r}\NRufio, consult the augurers. I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.22,0:07:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}庞培有没有胆在埃及见我{\r}\NIn Egypt, will Pompey face me at last?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.29,0:07:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒不是要返回罗马吗？{\r}\NBut surely Caesar will now return to Rome!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.10,0:07:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}无论如何，我也要去埃及一趟{\r}\NI must go to Egypt in any case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.10,0:07:52.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}托勒密国王舆姊姊打内战{\r}\NYoung King Ptolemy and his sister have a civil war of their own...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.53,0:07:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}想置对方于死地 况且罗马需要粮食{\r}\N...intent on destroying each other, and in the process, Rome's wheat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.04,0:07:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}殿下，不需要这么急逼{\r}\NThat cannot be so urgent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.94,0:08:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}让罗马最后才庆祝{\r}\NLet the Romans welcome great Caesar properly at last...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.31,0:08:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒的大胜利{\r}\N...in this greatest of his triumphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.65,0:08:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}庆祝？庆祝什么？{\r}\NTriumph? Over what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.82,0:08:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为谁？{\r}\NOver whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.42,0:08:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 坎尼迪斯 - 有什么吩咐，凯撒？{\r}\N-Canidius. -Caesar?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.56,0:08:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}除了第十和十二军队留下 其余的跟安东尼回罗马{\r}\NLeave me the 10th and 12th. Antony's to take the rest to Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.13,0:08:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 他几时可以起程？ - 随时都可以{\r}\N-When can he start? -Whenever you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.59,0:08:21.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那么就立刻起程{\r}\NThen at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.30,0:08:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼在罗马将会代表我{\r}\NAnd in Rome, Marc Antony is to speak for Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.97,0:08:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们不准质疑他的权力！{\r}\NHis authority is not to be questioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.00,0:08:30.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他的命令就是你的命令{\r}\NHis word will be yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.11,0:08:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒说的就是法律{\r}\NAs always, Caesar's word is law.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.07,0:08:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那当然{\r}\NOf course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.64,0:08:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}提醒他要抓紧兵权 有兵权才有实力{\r}\NBut remind him to keep his legions intact. They make the law legal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.08,0:08:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒{\r}\NCaesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.43,0:08:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}尽管凯撒的舰队驶向埃及…{\r}\NAnd even as Caesar's galleys sailed the great sea to Egypt...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.66,0:08:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但是，一如罗马人…{\r}\N...it was happening that, just as the Romans...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.93,0:09:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及人也是战祸连年{\r}\N...so the Egyptians made war, one upon the other...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.67,0:09:05.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}托勒密舆姊姊克莉奥佩特拉{\r}\N...for young King Ptolemy would no longer share the throne...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.11,0:09:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不能共享王位{\r}\N...with his sister Cleopatra...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.38,0:09:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他将她逐出亚历山卓{\r}\N...but drove her from the city of Alexandria...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.18,0:09:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}意图将她彻底打败{\r}\N...and sought to destroy her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.24,0:10:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们正好遇上本星期的墟期{\r}\NWe've arrived on their market day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.54,0:10:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}平民可以进入皇家禁地{\r}\NOnce a week they're allowed in the royal enclosure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.45,0:10:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}管他墟期不墟期{\r}\NWhere's the guard of honor for Caesar?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.85,0:10:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}欢迎凯撒的卫队呢？{\r}\NSome representative of the royal or military?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.73,0:11:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}至少应该有皇室或军方代表 难得一见高贵的凯撒自行穿过市集{\r}\NWe have the privilege of watching Caesar battle through our marketplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.51,0:11:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}马撒勒斯！派十二名军官，只准带剑{\r}\NMarcellus, a dozen front-rank men, swords only.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.31,0:11:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}开一条路直通皇宫{\r}\NClear a direct line to the palace steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.85,0:11:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}并且保持畅通！{\r}\NThen as many more to keep it open.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.65,0:11:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这样正好中了他们的计 不可以对群众无礼{\r}\NIt's precisely what they hope we'd be stupid enough to do: manhandle their people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.02,0:11:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}既然是墟期我们就来买东西{\r}\NNo. This is their market day, we will go marketing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.66,0:11:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 您说笑吧？ - 我们一路买到皇宫{\r}\N-You're not serious. -We'll shop our way to the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.33,0:11:42.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有带钱吗？ 买东西一律用钱币付款{\r}\NHave you my money? Everything is to be paid for by coin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.36,0:11:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}告诉手下将剑收起来，改带钱包{\r}\NTell them to put away the swords and carry moneybags.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.36,0:12:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}橄榄…橄榄油{\r}\NOlives. Oil of olives.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.83,0:12:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}萨姆斯酒{\r}\NAh, the wine of Samos.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.23,0:12:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}酒卖多少钱？ 4德拉克马{\r}\NHow much for your wine? Four drachma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.33,0:12:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们要六十瓶{\r}\NSixty of your wine for my men.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.57,0:12:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}付钱{\r}\NPay him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.67,0:12:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}付钱啊{\r}\NPay him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.01,0:12:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你说罗马人会推撞、惹怒群众{\r}\NYou said they'd push the people and make them angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.25,0:12:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}怎么没有发生呢？{\r}\NWhy aren't they doing what you said they'd do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.31,0:12:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}宫廷大臣，回答陛下{\r}\NYour king has asked a question, Lord Chamberlain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.39,0:12:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马人自贬身价，陛下{\r}\NThe Romans have degenerated minds, Most High Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.26,0:12:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们行事诡异{\r}\NThey do the unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.33,0:12:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}其中有一个{\r}\NParticularly one Roman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.69,0:12:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}特别奇怪{\r}\NMaster of the unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.23,0:12:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}可是他们那么少人…{\r}\NBut with so few men.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.71,0:13:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们都气宇非凡{\r}\NYou all look so impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.71,0:13:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}每个人都可以当国王{\r}\NAny one of you could be king.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.85,0:13:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}至高的托勒密国王{\r}\NHis Divine Majesty, my Lord Ptolemy...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.35,0:13:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}上、下省的头主{\r}\N...lord of the Upper and Lower regions...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.02,0:13:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}太阳神、赫拉斯、托斯、塔…之子{\r}\N...son of Ra, of Horus and of Thoth, beloved of--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.79,0:13:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}等等…不一而足…欢迎我{\r}\NEt cetera, et cetera. You welcome me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.56,0:13:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我是朱利斯凯撒 罗马元老院执政官麦希马斯{\r}\NAnd I, Gaius Julius Caesar, Pontifex Maximus...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.86,0:13:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}…等等，感谢你{\r}\N...et cetera, et cetera, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.40,0:13:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马元老院与人民向托勒密国王以及…{\r}\NFrom the Senate and people of Rome, hail King Ptolemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.87,0:13:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}舆他共治的姊姊克莉奥佩特拉女王致敬{\r}\NAnd his sister and co-ruler, Queen Cleopatra?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.04,0:13:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}事实并非如此 克莉奥佩特拉已死！{\r}\NThey won't tell you so, but Cleopatra's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.74,0:13:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她企图谋杀我 我们将她放逐到沙漠{\r}\NShe tried to kill me, and we chased her into the desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.31,0:13:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她已死在那儿{\r}\NAnd there she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.15,0:13:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}事实上皇姊…{\r}\NWhereas it is true that His Majesty's sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.72,0:13:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屡次想谋杀国王{\r}\N...repeatedly plotted to have him killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.28,0:13:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉已死却非事实{\r}\N...it is not true that Cleopatra is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.79,0:13:48.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她只是逃离了亚历山卓{\r}\NWhereas it is true that she fled from Alexandria--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.99,0:13:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}抱歉打扰你{\r}\NI seem to always interrupt you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.16,0:13:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但我想问清楚{\r}\N...but the search for truth can go on and on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.13,0:13:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你是波第诺斯？{\r}\NPothinus, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.63,0:13:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}宫廷大臣… 就是托勒密国王的最高宦官了{\r}\NLord Chamberlain and chief eunuch to King Ptolemy. An exalted rank.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.43,0:14:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}成就非凡，或者说…牺牲重大{\r}\NObtained not without certain, shall we say, sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.14,0:14:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}席铎特斯，你说是吗？{\r}\NTheodotus, am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.14,0:14:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}陛下历史、哲学舆野心的导师{\r}\NTutor to His Majesty in history, philosophy and ambition.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.45,0:14:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亚其勒斯，听说你是个好战士{\r}\NAnd Achillas. They say you're a good soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.28,0:14:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 克莉奥佩特拉女王在哪里？ - 舆她的军队同在{\r}\N-As one to another, where is Cleopatra? -With her army.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.19,0:14:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你有多少军队对付她？{\r}\NAnd how many of your men between her and Alexandria?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.29,0:14:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 足够的军队 - 我可以说句话吗？{\r}\N-Enough. -May I speak?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.29,0:14:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}伟大的凯撒心平气和而来{\r}\NSurely you have come in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.63,0:14:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们也热诚、隆重的欢迎你{\r}\NAnd we present ourselves to you in warm and respectful welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.26,0:14:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们唯一的问题是内政问题{\r}\NOur only problem being an internal one, of concern only to us...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.64,0:14:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒为何而来？{\r}\N...why have you come, Caesar?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.04,0:14:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}托勒密与克莉奥佩特拉之父驾崩时{\r}\NAs we all know, when the father of both Ptolemy and Cleopatra died...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.21,0:14:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}遗诏指示二人共同治理埃及{\r}\N...he named the two of them to rule jointly over Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.01,0:14:49.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马身为保护者与遗诏执行者{\r}\NRome was appointed their guardian and the executor of his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.52,0:14:53.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我代表罗马质疑 何以克莉奥佩特拉被驱逐{\r}\NI have come in the name of Rome to ask why Cleopatra has been deposed...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.69,0:14:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我来是解决她与托勒密之争{\r}\N...to resolve the differences between her and King Ptolemy...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.02,0:15:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}希望他们可以和平共治{\r}\N...and to see that they peacefully resume their joint rule of Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.66,0:15:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}恐怕困难重重 克莉奥佩特拉已犯罪失权{\r}\NThat will be difficult. Cleopatra has forfeited her right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.37,0:15:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我设法秉公处理{\r}\NI shall try to decide justly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.74,0:15:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们难道看不出来？ 他要带克莉奥佩特拉回来{\r}\NDon't you see he'll send for her? He'll bring her back!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.34,0:15:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}或者烈日太过锺情{\r}\NThe sun which sheds its grace upon the ruler of the two lands...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.24,0:15:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}国王陛下{\r}\N...burns too brightly perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.18,0:15:19.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如果托勒密国王愿意先行回宫…{\r}\NIf Lord Ptolemy wishes to retire--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.35,0:15:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我绝对没这个意愿{\r}\NI wish nothing of the kind!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.25,0:15:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不会回宫 除非你给他看那个！{\r}\NI won't be put out of the way until I've watched you give him that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.36,0:15:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}真对不起，我几乎忘记了{\r}\NA thousand pardons, I had almost forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.53,0:15:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我王托勒密有份礼物 送给凯撒以袁欢迎之诚{\r}\NLord Ptolemy wishes to enhance his welcome by a gift of some importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.50,0:15:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}感激厚礼相赠{\r}\NMost generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.77,0:15:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}戒指，庞培的戒指给他！{\r}\NThe ring. Give him Pompey's ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.05,0:15:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}代表我王对凯撒{\r}\NAnd now the token of His Majesty's affection for Rome...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.55,0:15:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}与罗焉的敬意{\r}\N...and regard for Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.03,0:16:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}庞培大帝！{\r}\NPompey the Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.47,0:16:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们说死人不会咬人的{\r}\NDead men, they say, do not bite.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.78,0:16:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这礼物你满意吗，凯撒？{\r}\NDoes it please you, Caesar?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.11,0:16:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们说这礼物会令你很开心{\r}\NThey said it would please you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.55,0:16:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}烈日果真会灼身{\r}\NThe sun does shed its grace too brightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.92,0:16:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这对王者不利{\r}\NIt has become too hot here for kings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.06,0:16:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}吾王托勒密要先行告退！{\r}\NMy Lord Ptolemy will retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.48,0:17:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}庞培是罗马荣誉的守护者{\r}\NFor His Majesty, a Roman guard of honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.36,0:17:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}庞培应该不是你杀的吧？{\r}\NIt was not by your hand, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.63,0:17:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如果你曾听说过我的事 你会比较了解我{\r}\NIf, as you say, you've been told of me, you know better, Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.27,0:17:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}请照顾我手下的起居饮食{\r}\NMy men shall be properly housed and fed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.77,0:17:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 我可以说句话吗？ - 有人问你才可发言{\r}\N-May I speak? -Not until you're spoken to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.27,0:17:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我要求住在皇宫里{\r}\NI'll require rooms in the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.31,0:17:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}本人有幸亲自护驾{\r}\NI shall consider myself honored to escort you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.68,0:17:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}除了你，任何人都可以{\r}\NAnyone but you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.72,0:17:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}尽全力打探{\r}\NFind the rest of Pompey.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.62,0:17:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}庞培的尸首{\r}\NTear out a thousand tongues, but find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.96,0:17:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为他举行净身{\r}\NHave him purified...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.66,0:17:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}含银币等尊荣之礼{\r}\N...the coin in the mouth and the rest, honorably.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.46,0:17:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当然{\r}\NOf course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.10,0:18:29.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}眼下我们必须据有…{\r}\NFor now, this is what we must hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.44,0:18:31.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}月门和其他三个要点 这、这和这儿{\r}\NMoon gate and three others. Here, here and here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.01,0:18:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们的部署如何？{\r}\NHow are we placed?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.74,0:18:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}第十军团守月门 其余的都在后备{\r}\NThe 10th slingers on the moon gate. The rest in reserve.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.54,0:18:39.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}第十二军团分散在其他位置 兵力很少，凯撒{\r}\NThe 12th holding all other positions. Very thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.78,0:18:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}目前这样足够了{\r}\NFor now, deep enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.55,0:18:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 有没有验过井水？ - 有咸味，但可以喝{\r}\N-Have we tested the wells? -The water's brackish, but drinkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.09,0:18:48.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们的玉米和小麦也要注意{\r}\NSo far. Keep an eye on them. Watch the corn and wheat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.39,0:18:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为什么？我们供给无虞 大可无限供应{\r}\NWith our supplies secure, we can hold indefinitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.43,0:18:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一星期或许够 但现在时间似乎不够用{\r}\NFor a week, perhaps. For the time being, time enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.10,0:18:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你有什么事？{\r}\NWhat do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.70,0:19:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这人可以信任吗？{\r}\NIs the man to be trusted?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.91,0:19:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}看来有人要送礼物给我{\r}\NSeems someone's brought me a gift...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.41,0:19:11.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是克莉奥佩特拉女王送的{\r}\N...from Queen Cleopatra.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.65,0:19:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}地毯小贩{\r}\NApparently, a rug peddler.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.95,0:19:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但弗拉维乌斯不信{\r}\NFlavius doubts it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.65,0:19:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他太了解皇宫了{\r}\NHe seems to know the palace very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.99,0:19:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他经由秘道突然出现 那秘道没有人知道{\r}\NHe appeared through a secret passage which none of the men knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.39,0:19:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}波第诺斯可能以 克莉奥佩特拉之名派刺客来{\r}\NPothinus might send an assassin in Cleopatra's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.06,0:19:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}带他进来{\r}\NHave the man brought in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.35,0:19:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你就是帮克莉奥佩特拉送礼物来的人？{\r}\NAre you the one who brings a gift from Cleopatra?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.28,0:19:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}把东西放下，立刻离开{\r}\NPut it down and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.79,0:19:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}女王吩咐我亲手送交凯撒{\r}\NIt is the command of my queen I deliver her gift personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.99,0:19:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我是凯撒，将东西放在我面前{\r}\NI am Caesar. Lay it here before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.36,0:20:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亚格里巴，你不是凯撒{\r}\NForgive me, Admiral Agrippa, but you're not Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.76,0:20:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}鲁非欧将军也不是 朱曼尼卡斯当然也不是{\r}\NNor you, General Rufio. Nor you, Germanicus.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.53,0:20:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}女王的礼物只有凯撒…{\r}\NMy queen's gift is for the eyes of Caesar...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.50,0:20:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}可以看{\r}\N...alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.34,0:20:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 那地毯看来没什么特别 - 不，凯撒…{\r}\N-It seems harmless enough. -No, Caesar!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.94,0:20:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}鲁非欧，借剑给我 有东西要割断{\r}\NYou can lend me your sword, Rufio. It may require some cutting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.95,0:20:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你搬地毯的方法真奇特{\r}\NOdd way to carry a rug.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.15,0:20:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}用肩膀抬不是比较轻松吗？{\r}\NIsn't it easier to sling it over your shoulder?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.12,0:20:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那样比较不舒服{\r}\NIt was less comfortable that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.83,0:20:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 你不舒服，还是地毯？ - 凯撒，你的剑…{\r}\N-For you or the rug? -That sword, Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.00,0:20:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}地毯手工很精细 我可否为你解下？{\r}\NThe rug is such a delicate weave. If I may untie it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.00,0:20:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将它反转过来{\r}\NTurn it over first.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.84,0:20:47.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 地毯已经面向上了 - 我要底向上{\r}\N-But the rug is right-side up. -I want it the wrong side up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.88,0:20:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 要我用剑来反转吗？ - 不不不！{\r}\N-Should I flip it over with my sword? -No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.88,0:21:00.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}货物好坏，一看…{\r}\NI find one can tell more about the quality of merchandise...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.25,0:21:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}背面就知道{\r}\N...by examining the back side first.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.99,0:21:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉女王万岁… 王室的荣耀{\r}\NAll hail Cleopatra, kindred of Horus and Ra...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.66,0:21:13.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}日月的光荣 埃瑟丝女神之女{\r}\N...beloved of the moon and sun, daughter to Isis...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.00,0:21:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}至高无上的埃及女王{\r}\N...and of Upper and Lower Egypt, queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.22,0:21:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谢谢{\r}\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.05,0:21:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这里{\r}\NHere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.59,0:21:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}把这手令交给夜更侍卫队长{\r}\NTake this to the captain of the night watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.46,0:21:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他会预备好女王的侍卫队{\r}\NHe'll see the queen's quarters are made ready to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.43,0:21:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}别动{\r}\NStay where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.73,0:21:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 我叫你走了吗？ - 没有，陛下{\r}\N-Have I dismissed you? -No, Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.23,0:21:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这是我的地方{\r}\NThis is my palace, Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.40,0:21:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}由我发号拖令{\r}\NAll of it is available to me at my will.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.57,0:21:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不是你的犯人 而你是我的客人{\r}\NI am not your prisoner. If anything, you are my guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.71,0:21:56.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}悉听尊便{\r}\NMost kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.94,0:22:00.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}至于帮我预备侍卫队…{\r}\NAnd as for having my quarters, as you put it, made ready...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.71,0:22:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我的侍女已将其他人带出{\r}\N...my chief handmaiden has, by now, brought the others out of hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.42,0:22:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}应该全部出来了{\r}\NThey should almost be finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.45,0:22:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}恐怕不可能，外面戒备深严{\r}\NImpossible. The doors are under guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.99,0:22:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}此处有无数的门{\r}\NThere are doors, and doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.13,0:22:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当然{\r}\NOh, yes. Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.79,0:22:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}改天带我参观您的皇宫{\r}\NYou must take me on a tour someday within the walls of your palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.73,0:22:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 你还等什么？ - 等您下令让我离开{\r}\N-What are you waiting for? -Permission to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.77,0:22:22.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}可以走了{\r}\NGranted.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.10,0:22:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}阿波罗德斯{\r}\NApollodorus.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.31,0:22:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谢谢你{\r}\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.15,0:22:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}很高兴你收到我的召唤 而且能够…{\r}\NI'm pleased you received my summons and were able to--
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.62,0:22:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}召唤？我没有收到{\r}\NSummons? I'm pleased to say I received nothing of the kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.29,0:22:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}要我回应我真的十分讶异{\r}\NI'm surprised you thought I would answer one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.13,0:22:48.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}小姐，你的地毯旅程显然不累{\r}\NYoung lady, the voyage in your non-magic carpet...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.96,0:22:51.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但我今天真的很累了{\r}\N...has apparently not tired you, but I'm exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.27,0:22:55.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒，我们必须互相了解{\r}\NCaesar, it is essential we understand each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.67,0:22:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只有我能帮你…{\r}\NOnly through me can you hope to escape...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.21,0:23:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}脱离这个危险{\r}\N...the desperate situation in which you find yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.01,0:23:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如果是我的话 我决不会吃那个水果{\r}\NI wouldn't bite into that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.61,0:23:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是你带来的吗？ 尝过吗？{\r}\NDid you bring it with you? Have you had it tasted?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.35,0:23:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如没有，可能有毒{\r}\NIf neither, it's probably poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.62,0:23:15.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这也是脱离危险的方法之一{\r}\NAt least it's another way out of the desperate situation in which I'm found.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.39,0:23:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你对我很容忍，不是吗？{\r}\NYou're being tolerant of me, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.66,0:23:24.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是因为你比我年长很多？{\r}\NIs it because you're so much older?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.90,0:23:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的地图比我的逊色{\r}\NYour maps are inferior. Out-of-date, compared to mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.74,0:23:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}它和我一样都老了{\r}\NThey and I have aged together.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.31,0:23:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}西边的湖泊位置不对{\r}\NThe lakes to the west are poorly marked...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.91,0:23:37.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}几个重要山丘甚至没标记{\r}\N...certain important hill positions not even noted.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.25,0:23:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}请你帮我的绘图师舆全体官兵上课{\r}\NI must arrange for you to address my mapmakers and general staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.55,0:23:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们一开始就不和{\r}\NWe've gotten off to a bad start, haven't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.16,0:23:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不过是倒顺你的毛{\r}\NI've rubbed you the wrong way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.52,0:23:54.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}小姐，其实你根本不该摸{\r}\NI'm not sure I want to be rubbed by you at all, young lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.40,0:24:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}请问我可否坐下？{\r}\NIt is permissible for me to sit, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.77,0:24:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒，请尽快让我单独登上埃及王位{\r}\NAs quickly as possible you must set me alone on the throne of Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.54,0:24:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我的任务是平息你们姊弟的纷争{\r}\NMy mission is to put to an end the tiresome squabbling between your brother and you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.41,0:24:14.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你不是个傻瓜吧？{\r}\NYou're not a fool. Or are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.95,0:24:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}恕不自谦，应该不是吧{\r}\NImmodestly, perhaps, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.52,0:24:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你见过我弟弟 听过他说话吧？{\r}\NYou've seen my brother and listened to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.25,0:24:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那数典忘宗邪恶的人{\r}\NAnd that truly evil man to whom he belongs?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.36,0:24:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}见过{\r}\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.89,0:24:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们都同意罗马一向…{\r}\NShall we agree upon what Rome really wants...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.76,0:24:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}对埃及的倚赖吗？{\r}\N...has always wanted of Egypt?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.80,0:24:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}玉米、谷物和珍宝{\r}\NCorn, grain, treasure. It's the old story.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.47,0:24:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一直以来，罗马的伟大 建立在埃及的富足之上{\r}\NRoman greatness built upon Egyptian riches.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.11,0:24:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你要和平取得这些物资{\r}\NYou shall have them. You shall have them all and in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.28,0:24:46.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}办法只得一个{\r}\NBut there is only one way.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.48,0:24:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}让我当女王{\r}\NMy way. Make me queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.38,0:24:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听起来像最后通牒{\r}\NThat sounds very much like an ultimatum.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.79,0:24:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没有其他方法{\r}\NThere is no other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.96,0:24:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}下通牒的人，几分钟前…{\r}\NFor one whose assets, up to a few moments ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.76,0:25:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}仅有一个忠仆和一张地毯{\r}\N...was a devoted slave and a rolled-up carpet....
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.66,0:25:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在有了你，凯撒{\r}\NBut I have you now, Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.96,0:25:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}而且我有军队{\r}\NBesides, there are my armies...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.97,0:25:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没有一个凡人可以打败我{\r}\N...and the simple fact that no mortal hand can destroy me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.07,0:25:11.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}记得你自称具有神力{\r}\NYes, I recall some mention of an obsession...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.67,0:25:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃瑟丝女神降世{\r}\N...you have about your divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.74,0:25:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}对吗？{\r}\NIsis, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.48,0:25:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我警告你小心说话{\r}\NI shall have to insist that you mind what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.62,0:25:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我是埃瑟丝女神 受千万人爱戴{\r}\NI am Isis. I am worshiped by millions who believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.82,0:25:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不要用罗马将军们的…{\r}\NDo not confuse what I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.82,0:25:31.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}保护神{\r}\N...with the so-called divine origin...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.46,0:25:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}混淆我的身分{\r}\N...that every Roman general acquires together with his shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.43,0:25:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们不是维纳斯的近亲吗？{\r}\NIt was Venus you chose to be descended from, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.77,0:25:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}容许我表达我小小的固执{\r}\NI must now do a little insisting of my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.47,0:25:47.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}首先，你始终是旅途困倦 需要休息…{\r}\NFirst, your journey has tired you and you wish to retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.51,0:25:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不是你的仆人 你无权遣我走{\r}\NI am not your servant, Caesar. Do not dismiss me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.54,0:25:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}第二，你停发军饷{\r}\NSecondly, you have no armies, young lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.18,0:25:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的军队跑光了{\r}\NThey are gone because you could not pay them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.18,0:25:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及的财富你都无法享用{\r}\NEgypt's riches are not available for your own use...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.32,0:26:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}更何况是赠与他人{\r}\N...much less to give away. Perhaps in a day or two...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.32,0:26:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 我们改天再谈吧 - 那对我俩…{\r}\N-...we can speak again. -That may be too late...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.89,0:26:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}都太迟了{\r}\N...for both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.29,0:26:08.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我要负责你的安全{\r}\NYour safety will be my responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.00,0:26:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你自己的安全呢？{\r}\NAnd what about your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.47,0:26:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}目前，我已有对策{\r}\NI am prepared, I believe, for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.00,0:26:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}希望如此吧{\r}\NI hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.31,0:26:21.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}希望你像传闻中一样{\r}\NI hope you are as wise, as brilliant...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.48,0:26:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}明智而杰出，像神一样{\r}\N...the god they say you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.68,0:26:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马将军轻易就被神化{\r}\NYou Roman generals become divine so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.55,0:26:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只要几场胜仗和屠杀{\r}\NA few victories, a few massacres.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.09,0:26:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}昨天庞培还是个神{\r}\NOnly yesterday, Pompey was a god.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.25,0:26:37.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 今天不是惨遭屠杀吗？ - 是的{\r}\N-They murdered him, didn't they? -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.49,0:26:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}因为他们以为你会高兴{\r}\NBecause they thought it would please you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.39,0:26:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 你高兴吗？ - 不{\r}\N-It didn't, did it? -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.33,0:26:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}今天，我想起我女儿很喜欢他{\r}\NToday I found myself remembering how much my daughter loved him.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.87,0:26:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她因为想为他生子而丧命{\r}\NShe died trying to bear him a son.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.34,0:26:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她给他这个戒指{\r}\NShe gave him this ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.74,0:26:59.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}好好睡一觉{\r}\NSleep well tonight, Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.08,0:27:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}未来几天可不好过啊{\r}\NThese next days may be difficult for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.08,0:27:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}晚安{\r}\NGood night.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.56,0:27:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}朱曼尼卡斯 派个侍卫送女王回府{\r}\NGermanicus, a guard to escort Queen Cleopatra to her apartments.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.19,0:27:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}侍卫！{\r}\NGuards!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.07,0:27:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}走廊很暗，各位{\r}\NThe corridors are dark, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.31,0:27:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但不必怕，有我在这里{\r}\NBut you mustn't be afraid. I am with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.09,0:27:45.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}今晚任务是否完成了？{\r}\NHaven't we covered everything we can tonight, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.06,0:27:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 是的，其他留待明天 - 不，还有几件事{\r}\N-Perhaps a fresh start in the morning. -No, a few more matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.76,0:27:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}例如，你不觉得我们的地图…{\r}\NRufio, has it occurred to you that our maps of this area...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.30,0:27:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有点不妥吗？{\r}\N...are not quite what they should be?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.77,0:27:58.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不会啊，你怎会这样想？{\r}\NWhy, no. What makes you think they're not?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.57,0:28:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}对这种事我有直觉{\r}\NI have an instinct about these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.82,0:28:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}根据资料是马其顿血统{\r}\N--actually of Macedonian descent.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.95,0:28:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没有埃及血缘{\r}\NNo officially-admitted Egyptian blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.62,0:28:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉以足智多谋{\r}\N"Reputed to be extremely intelligent and sharp of wit.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.99,0:28:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}阅历丰富著称 擅长科学…{\r}\NQueen Cleopatra is widely read. Well-versed in the sciences...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.70,0:28:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}与算术{\r}\N...and mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.00,0:28:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}并精通七国语言{\r}\NShe speaks seven languages proficiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.93,0:28:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若非身为女人她会是知识份子{\r}\NWere she not a woman, she'd be considered an intellectual."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.37,0:28:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但我发现知识份子最无趣{\r}\NNothing bores me so much as an intellectual.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.14,0:28:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}所以你是个好舰队司令 亚格里巴{\r}\NMakes a better admiral of you, Agrippa.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.51,0:28:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这份文件 海军会比较有兴趣{\r}\NHere's something of more interest to the navy:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.28,0:28:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为达到目的克莉奥佩特拉 利用刑罚、毒药…{\r}\N"In obtaining her objectives, she has been known to use torture, poison...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.38,0:28:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}甚至她娇人的性吸引力{\r}\N...and even her own sexual talents, which are said to be considerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.06,0:28:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听说她的爱人多不胜数 也就是说名字多得说不完{\r}\NHer lovers, I am told, are listed more easily by number than by name.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.29,0:28:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她对男人很主动{\r}\NIt is said that she chooses in the manner of a man...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.50,0:28:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}并非被动等待{\r}\N...rather than wait to be chosen after womanly fashion."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.57,0:29:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}所以我们才不让…{\r}\NWell, there's more reason than we thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.34,0:29:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们单独相处{\r}\N...for not wanting to leave you two alone, eh, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.47,0:29:07.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}抱歉，鲁非欧，我没听见{\r}\NI'm sorry, I wasn't listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.64,0:29:09.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你信得过克莉奥佩特拉？{\r}\NAre you inclined to trust Cleopatra?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.21,0:29:12.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}信任？门都没有{\r}\NTrust? Not for a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.91,0:29:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我对信任一词一向定义模糊{\r}\N"Trust." The word has always made me apprehensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.52,0:29:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就像酒，后劲教我难以消受{\r}\NLike wine, whenever I've tried it, the aftereffects have not been good.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.89,0:29:23.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}所以我不喝酒…{\r}\NSo I've given up wine...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.72,0:29:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}也不信任他人{\r}\N...and trusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.89,0:29:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}各位，今天很累了{\r}\NOh, it's been a long and difficult day, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.16,0:29:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}往后几天或会更累{\r}\NThe next few may be even longer and more difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.73,0:29:35.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 晚安 - 晚安{\r}\N-Good night. -Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.91,0:30:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}弗拉维乌斯！{\r}\NFlavius!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.31,0:30:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}弗拉维乌斯！{\r}\NFlavius!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.90,0:32:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}秋天又来了，心爱的莱比雅{\r}\NIt is autumn again, my best-loved Lesbia
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.10,0:32:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}看，树叶不停的飘落…飘落{\r}\NLook, the torrents of Roman leaves Are falling, falling
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.41,0:32:31.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}跟着，爱人们在春之吻中苏醒{\r}\NAnd lovers revive in kisses The promise of spring
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.08,0:32:36.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}夜莺叫声中寒冬将远去…{\r}\NWhich will end the winter world With new nightingales calling
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.68,0:32:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我先试你的食物{\r}\NI taste your food, daughter of Isis...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.12,0:32:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有毒就毒我好了{\r}\N...and if there be harm in it, let the harm fall upon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.09,0:32:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}爱终将有凋萎的一天{\r}\NBut love must bring Despair one day
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.79,0:32:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当美丽与哀愁…{\r}\NAs beauty, sorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.30,0:32:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 为什么停下来？费比斯？ - 走廊外有骚动{\r}\N-Why do you stop, Phoebus? -In the corridor, there is movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.64,0:33:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马人用象般的脚踩地{\r}\NThat's how the Romans frighten the enemy...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.21,0:33:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 希望可以吓退敌人 - 不，有个人{\r}\N-...by stamping their elephant feet. -No, this is one man...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.41,0:33:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}后面有一班人跟着{\r}\N...followed by others.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.65,0:33:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 应该是凯撒 - 是吗？{\r}\N-Caesar, I would say. -Would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.99,0:33:17.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不能让凯撒失望{\r}\NWe must not disappoint the mighty Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.72,0:33:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马人对我的沐浴{\r}\NThe Romans tell fabulous tales of my bath...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.23,0:33:23.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}女仆…{\r}\N...and handmaidens...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.60,0:33:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}和道德观充满了幻想{\r}\N...and my morals.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.34,0:33:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉邀我作伴{\r}\NCleopatra's requested an audience with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.57,0:33:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 那是昨天的事，凯撒 - 我有重要的事{\r}\N-That was yesterday, Caesar. -I've been occupied.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.94,0:33:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}女王正在沐浴 凯撒能否稍后{\r}\NThe queen is occupied with her bath. Perhaps Caesar could return later...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.45,0:33:42.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 或明天再来？ - 恐怕不能捉住他{\r}\N-...or tomorrow. -I'm afraid not. Hold him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.65,0:33:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不，不要伤害他{\r}\NNo, don't hurt him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.75,0:33:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你是个好人，阿波罗德斯{\r}\NYou're a good man, Apollodorus.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.75,0:33:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}希望你能明白{\r}\NI hope you're appreciated.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.59,0:33:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在这里等我{\r}\NWait here for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.61,0:34:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}既然如此，让我们活下去并且相爱 不要理会什么{\r}\NAh, then let us live and love Without one thought
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.68,0:34:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}处女年华老去的闲话{\r}\NFor the gossip of virgins Now grown old and stale
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.45,0:34:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}太阳下山后依旧会升起{\r}\NSuns go down and may return
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.45,0:34:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但希望之光若熄灭{\r}\NBut once put out Our own brief light
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.72,0:34:23.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将是无尽的长眠{\r}\NWe sleep through One eternal night
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.89,0:34:26.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有人闯入！一个男人{\r}\NAn intruder! A man!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.63,0:34:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}原来是你{\r}\NOh, it's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.20,0:34:34.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你想见我？{\r}\NYou wanted to see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.80,0:34:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我昨天召你{\r}\NI summoned you yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.84,0:34:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}来王宫见我{\r}\N...to an audience in my throne room.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.37,0:34:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但未获准到那里{\r}\NI was told I was not permitted to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.91,0:34:48.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}太靠近你弟弟的指挥中心 以及他的手下{\r}\NIt's too close to the quarters occupied by your brother and the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.22,0:34:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我爱到哪儿就到哪儿！{\r}\NI will not be told where I can go and where I cannot go!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.55,0:34:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}显然你并不需要我{\r}\NSince there's nothing you want....
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.66,0:34:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}除了王位！{\r}\NExcept my throne!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.53,0:35:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}至少你盛装前来{\r}\NAt least you've dressed properly for my presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.57,0:35:07.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}穿了最好的盔甲？{\r}\NYour best armor?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.50,0:35:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}也许是吧，但不是因为尊重你{\r}\NAlmost, but I'm afraid it's not being worn in your honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.37,0:35:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我知道{\r}\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.27,0:35:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}今早你去拜祭亚历山大的坟{\r}\NThis morning, you paid a formal visit to the tomb of Alexander.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.08,0:35:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}独自凭吊石棺很久…{\r}\NYou remained alone beside the sarcophagus for some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.52,0:35:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我倒想知道你怎会知道{\r}\NI'd like to know how you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.72,0:35:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}低头凝视{\r}\NJust staring down at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.52,0:35:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还流下眼泪{\r}\NAnd then you cried.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.19,0:35:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒，你为何流泪？{\r}\NWhy did you cry, Caesar?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.63,0:35:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他朗诵的很好{\r}\NThat man recites beautifully.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.60,0:35:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 他是盲人吗？ - 不要伤害他{\r}\N-Is he blind? -Don't you hurt him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.60,0:35:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不会伤害将卡图卢斯 朗诵得这么好的人{\r}\NI won't. Not anyone who speaks Catullus so well.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.24,0:35:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}卡图卢斯不赞同你怎么不杀他？{\r}\NCatullus doesn't approve of you. Why haven't you had him killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.11,0:35:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}因为我赞同他{\r}\NBecause I approve of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.88,0:35:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我无意取悦你，凯撒{\r}\NMy desire to please you, Caesar Is very slight
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.15,0:35:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}更不管你是黑人或白人{\r}\NNor do I greatly care to know If you are black or white
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.42,0:36:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亚其勒斯在部署全军 开往亚历山卓{\r}\NAchillas is moving his entire army to Alexandria.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.29,0:36:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}今晚，他的兵力将会是你的二三十倍{\r}\NBy tonight, he'll outnumber you 20-to-1 , 30-to-1 .
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.26,0:36:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他会将皇家禁地重重包围{\r}\NHe'll have the royal enclosure entirely surrounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.06,0:36:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}除了靠海这一边{\r}\NExcept to the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.13,0:36:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你打算出海逃走，凯撒？{\r}\NDo you plan to sail away, great Caesar?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.80,0:36:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}目前没这个打算{\r}\NNot for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.10,0:36:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亚其勒斯明后天开始攻击{\r}\NAchillas may attack tomorrow, the next day...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.31,0:36:23.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 只等他下决定！ - 非常可能{\r}\N-...whenever it suits him! -Very probable.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.44,0:36:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒，即使是做梦…{\r}\NIn your wildest dreams, Caesar, how can you possibly hope to hold...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.58,0:36:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你怎可能以寡敌众？{\r}\N...the gates of this enclosure against such odds?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.85,0:36:34.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}看你还怎么说目前！{\r}\NAnd if you say once more, "For the time being"....
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.85,0:36:38.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我的军官说短则一周 长则无尽期{\r}\NMy officers say anything from a week to indefinitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.66,0:36:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你估计呢？{\r}\NWhat would you estimate?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.86,0:36:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你是说缺水{\r}\NBefore you're without water...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.03,0:36:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}断粮{\r}\N...without food...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.60,0:36:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还是全军覆没？ 一个接一个在屋顶被杀{\r}\N...your troops slaughtered, picked off from the rooftops...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.84,0:36:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在妓院中毒身亡{\r}\N...poisoned in the brothels?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.17,0:36:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}几天吧，凯撒，最多几天{\r}\NA few days, Caesar. At the most, a few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.01,0:36:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我相当同意{\r}\NI'm inclined to agree with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.51,0:37:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}知不知道卡图卢斯有首诗？{\r}\NYoung man, do you know this of Catullus?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.22,0:37:05.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}给我千个吻{\r}\NGive me a thousand And a thousand kisses
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.45,0:37:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}再多就数不清了{\r}\NWhen we have many thousand more We'll scramble them
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.29,0:37:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}忘记数字{\r}\NAnd forget the score
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.02,0:37:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}忌妒怎会自知{\r}\NSo evil envy will not know How high the count
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.06,0:37:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}忌妒的深度{\r}\NAnd cast its evil eye
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.20,0:37:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}即使在皇室也没有如此愉快{\r}\NIt couldn't have been as pleasant in the throne room.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.97,0:37:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我无意取悦你，凯撒…{\r}\N"My desire to please you, Caesar, Is very slight--"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.31,0:37:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不要动{\r}\NBe still!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.48,0:37:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒，我有句话… 非常重要{\r}\NCaesar, a word. It's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.02,0:37:41.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及船只停靠西港 装载人员和武器{\r}\NThe Egyptian galleys in the harbor have been taking on men and armaments.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.39,0:37:45.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 何时将对我们动手？ - 明日清早{\r}\N-When will they be prepared? -Tomorrow, with the morning wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.49,0:37:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}今晚将他们烧了{\r}\NBurn them tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.26,0:37:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}船只紧靠岸边{\r}\NTheir ships lie close to shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.40,0:37:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 火势可能蔓延到城里 - 希望是不会{\r}\N-The fire may spread to the city. -Let's hope it doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.73,0:37:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但不能冒被封锁的危险{\r}\NI can't risk a blockade.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.40,0:37:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}记住，今晚之前不要动手秘密做准备{\r}\NRemember, not before tonight. Prepare as secretly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.17,0:38:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我需要今天{\r}\NI need this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.41,0:38:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}祝你好运{\r}\NGood luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.41,0:38:09.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为何不可以在今晚之前动手？ 为何凯撒需要今天？{\r}\NWhy not before tonight, my lord? Why does Caesar need this day?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.18,0:38:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}目前，天机不可泄漏{\r}\NI can't give you that information, for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.76,0:38:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}弗拉维乌斯{\r}\NFlavius.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.90,0:38:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒，在这儿，刚到{\r}\NHere it is, Caesar. Just arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.80,0:38:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}神真会作弄我们，鲁非欧{\r}\NThe gods shouldn't tantalize us so, Rufio.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.97,0:38:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}比我希望的还好{\r}\NIt's even better than I’d hoped.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.71,0:38:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 快走，时间不多 - 凯撒万岁{\r}\N-Be on your way, you haven't much time. -Hail Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.63,0:39:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这称为癫痫症因为肌肉抽搐{\r}\NIt's called an epilepse because of the arching caused by muscular spasms...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.51,0:39:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}引起剧痛 古希腊人认为{\r}\N...the contortions. The early Greeks considered...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.68,0:39:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}患者因而得神明偏爱{\r}\N...those who suffered from it to be favored by the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.01,0:39:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}据说亚历山大帝{\r}\NThe great Alexander, they say...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.18,0:39:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有此癫痫症{\r}\N...had this falling sickness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.75,0:39:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听说凯撒也有{\r}\NAnd, so they say, the mighty Caesar too.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.36,0:39:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}陛下恕罪，西索吉诺斯图书馆！{\r}\NYour Majesty, forgive me. Sosigenes, the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.33,0:39:28.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 说清楚 - 罗马人放火{\r}\N-What are you saying? -The Romans set fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.10,0:39:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 烧埃及船舰！ - 是时候了{\r}\N-...to the Egyptian fleet. -It's about time.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.83,0:39:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你看，火势蔓延到城里了！{\r}\NCome see for yourself. The fire's spread to the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.03,0:39:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}烧着几栋房子{\r}\N-The city? -Just a few buildings...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.67,0:39:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}图书馆着火了{\r}\N...but the library is burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.94,0:39:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}大图书馆…{\r}\NThe great library.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.69,0:40:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亚里士多德的手稿…{\r}\NAristotle's manuscripts.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.63,0:40:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}柏拉图的评论、剧本、史料…{\r}\NThe Platonic commentaries, the plays, the histories.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.87,0:40:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}希伯来神明的圣经！{\r}\NThe Testament of the Hebrew god.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.81,0:40:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}珍贵的书籍！{\r}\NThe Book of Books.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.88,0:40:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}风将火势吹向商船 至少有四、五艘被烧掉{\r}\N-Wind blew into the merchant shipping. -Four or five burned and sank right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.49,0:40:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 我们的船只呢？ - 安全无事{\r}\N-And our ships? -Safe and dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.39,0:40:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但囚犯们包围住 我需要帮手{\r}\NPrisoners are surrendering in droves. I need help.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.39,0:40:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 没人手，马上还需要水手帮忙 - 站住！{\r}\N-Not one man. I may need your sailors. -Halt!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.76,0:40:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不要将我的武器拿走！{\r}\NTake your hands off me!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.90,0:40:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你该常常来袭击我的侍卫 打仗似乎使你更为美艳{\r}\NYou should attack my guards more often. Battle seems to become you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.41,0:40:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你变得愈来愈美丽{\r}\NYou grow more beautiful each time I see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.21,0:40:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}而你的头愈来愈秃！{\r}\NAnd you grow bolder.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.42,0:40:56.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}愈来愈忙{\r}\NAnd busier.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.68,0:41:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 此刻的确非常忙，恕不奉陪 - 有没有闻到烟味？{\r}\N-Actually, we're extremely busy-- -Do you smell smoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.75,0:41:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们必须烧毁埃及舰队{\r}\NWe found it necessary to burn the Egyptian fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.86,0:41:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}船原本在水上{\r}\NThe ships were in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.89,0:41:09.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有必要烧街道吗？{\r}\NDid you find it necessary to burn them in the streets?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.23,0:41:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}几只商船着火{\r}\NMerchant ships caught fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.20,0:41:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}桅杆塌向街上的屋{\r}\NThe burning masts fell. Some houses--
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.43,0:41:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}其中之一是亚历山卓的大图书馆{\r}\NOne of them, the great Library of Alexandria.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.47,0:41:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听说了，非常抱歉{\r}\NYes, I’ve been told. I'm extremely sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.31,0:41:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 若不介意，我不得不请你… - 我很介意{\r}\N-Now, if you don't mind, I must ask-- -I do mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.38,0:41:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你要不要将火扑灭？{\r}\NAre you putting the fire out?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.55,0:41:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们正在把埃及囚犯组成消防队{\r}\NWe're forming prisoners into fire brigades.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.32,0:41:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}难道罗马人只懂放火？{\r}\NOh, I see. Romans only start fires, is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.42,0:41:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}小孩不要来烦大人{\r}\NHave you broken out of your nursery to come irritate the adults?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.82,0:41:38.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}改天吧，现在很忙！{\r}\NAnother time, we're working.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.59,0:41:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 要不要将她赶走，凯撒？ - 用罗马人的天赋搞破坏！{\r}\N-Shall we remove her for you, Caesar? -Use that Roman genius for destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.80,0:41:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}把金字塔拆了，城市也夷平！{\r}\NTear down pyramids, wipe out cities!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.73,0:41:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们这些野蛮人竟然烧图书馆{\r}\NHow dare you and the rest of your barbarians set fire to my library?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.51,0:41:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}大玩征服者游戏，伟大的凯撒{\r}\NPlay conqueror all you want, mighty Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.01,0:42:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}尽管烧杀掳掠千万人…{\r}\NRape, murder, pillage thousands, millions of human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.28,0:42:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但你们这些野蛮人…{\r}\NBut neither you nor any other barbarian...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.98,0:42:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}无权摧毁人类文明！{\r}\N...has the right to destroy one human thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.12,0:42:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}够了！让我单独跟她谈谈{\r}\NEnough! Leave me alone with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.66,0:42:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}很快就会结束，到时我会通知你{\r}\NI will send for you when I finish. It won't be long.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.43,0:42:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}剑？标枪？{\r}\NSwords? Javelins?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.60,0:42:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还是放火？{\r}\NOr are you going to set me on fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.87,0:42:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}该是我们互相了解的时候了{\r}\NThe time has come for us to understand each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.31,0:42:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不管你怎样说，我就是凯撒{\r}\NWhatever else I may be, in your opinion, first of all, I am Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.51,0:42:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}而我是克莉奥佩特拉 埃瑟丝女神之女！{\r}\NAnd I am Cleopatra, queen, daughter of Isis!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.35,0:42:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我说你是什么…{\r}\NIf I say so and when I say so, you are what I say you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.85,0:42:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你就是什么！{\r}\N...nothing more.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.66,0:42:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒万岁{\r}\NHail Caesar!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.99,0:42:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你，多代近亲通婚所生的白痴{\r}\NYou, descendant of inbred generations of incestuous mental defectives...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.63,0:42:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 竟敢叫我们野蛮人！ - 野蛮人！{\r}\N-...how dare you call anyone barbarian. -Barbarian!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.50,0:42:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的先人是只会吹笛子的醉酒佬 一路靠贿赂登上王位{\r}\NDaughter of a drunkard who bribed his way to the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.97,0:43:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 你一将功成万骨枯，记得吗？ - 我受够了你的装腔作势{\r}\N-Your price was too high, remember? -I've had my fill with you pretenders...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.34,0:43:08.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 脚下尽是光荣的废墟 - 我在意的是未来{\r}\N-...parading on ruins of your past glories. -Only the future concerns me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.38,0:43:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 既然如此，照我的话去做 - 照你的话去做？{\r}\N-Keep out of my affairs, do as I say. -Do as you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.22,0:43:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}真的吗？{\r}\NLiterally?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.42,0:43:15.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就像你已征服了我？{\r}\NAs if I were something you had conquered?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.16,0:43:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只要我如此认为{\r}\NIf I choose to regard you as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.36,0:43:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我是不是该乖乖跟你合作…{\r}\NAm I to understand that you're free to do with me whatever you want...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.86,0:43:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你可以为所欲为？{\r}\N...whenever you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.43,0:43:29.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是的，这见解十分正确{\r}\NYes, I want that understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.84,0:43:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你干脆戴上皇冠…{\r}\NWon't you at least wear your laurel wreath...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.54,0:43:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我清楚记得是蒙凯撒宠幸？{\r}\N...so I can be reminded it's the divine Caesar that honors me so?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.58,0:43:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你讲得太多了{\r}\NYou talk too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.69,0:43:47.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我这样子{\r}\NI promise you...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.02,0:43:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你不会喜欢的{\r}\N...you won't like me this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.39,0:43:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒！月门受到袭击！{\r}\NCaesar! An attack on the moon gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.90,0:43:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}月门！武力袭击！{\r}\NThe moon gate. An attack in force!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.13,0:45:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}炮塔必需摧毁{\r}\NThose ballistas need eliminating.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.27,0:45:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}派出战龟{\r}\NSend out a turtle.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.01,0:45:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}备妥战龟！{\r}\NForm the turtle!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.62,0:46:33.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}该是进攻的好时机{\r}\NNow is the time for us to attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.85,0:46:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 不 - 但是我们已用了预备军{\r}\N-No. -We have a full legion in reserve.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.79,0:46:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}守在这里就可以了{\r}\NWe hold our positions here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.77,0:46:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}离黎明两小时守住这里就可以了{\r}\NTwo hours till dawn. We'll hold where we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.04,0:46:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 天亮之后呢？ - 你知道的{\r}\N-And what happens at dawn? -I thought you knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.98,0:46:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}太阳升起来啊{\r}\NThe sun comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.51,0:47:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}告诉部下我们已取得胜利{\r}\NTell the men they've won.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.58,0:47:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}犒赏守门有功的士卫{\r}\NLiberty and wine for defenders of the gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.25,0:47:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}所有后备兵力移至亚其勒背后{\r}\NAll reserves, cavalry, every man available, move out behind Achillas.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.25,0:47:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 两面包抄 - 包抄的另一边呢？{\r}\N-We have him in a vise. -What is the other half of this vise?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.76,0:47:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}鲁非欧和密斯里达的部队{\r}\NRufio and the armies of Mithradates. He left last night to meet them.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.26,0:47:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}密斯里达？他怎会那么快？{\r}\NMithradates? How could he get here this fast?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.13,0:47:52.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们出航埃及时他已出发{\r}\NI sent him when we sailed for Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.33,0:47:57.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}任何有理智的将军 都不会妄想靠两队军队拿下亚历山卓{\r}\NNo general in his right mind can hold Alexandria with two legions...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.30,0:48:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们不是常常那么说吗？{\r}\N...as you and others have repeatedly pointed out to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.83,0:48:27.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我尝你的酒，埃瑟丝女神之女{\r}\NI taste your drink, daughter of Isis...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.50,0:48:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若有毒，就毒死我吧{\r}\N...and if there be harm in it, let the harm fall upon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.84,0:48:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}洛托斯！{\r}\NLotus.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.75,0:48:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}喝过之后将杯边擦干净 知道为什么吗？{\r}\NYou wiped the rim of the cup after you tasted it. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.55,0:48:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 为什么？ - 以免被我的咀污染{\r}\NWhy? So my mouth would not soil it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.76,0:48:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}洛托斯{\r}\NLotus...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.09,0:48:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}再尝一口{\r}\N...taste it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.50,0:49:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}波第洛斯说要杀我！ 原谅我{\r}\NPothinus said he would have me killed. Forgive me, Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.11,0:49:10.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}陛下，原谅我！{\r}\NForgive me. Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.04,0:49:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我原谅你{\r}\NI forgive you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.92,0:49:17.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在喝吧{\r}\NNow drink it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.74,0:49:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}阿波罗德斯！{\r}\NApollodorus!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.11,0:49:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}阿波罗德斯！{\r}\NApollodorus!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.49,0:49:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}欢迎罗马元老院执政官{\r}\NGreat silence for Gaius Julius Caesar...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.16,0:50:01.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}朱利斯凯撒{\r}\N...consul of the senate of the people of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.63,0:50:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}全体肃立{\r}\NYou will all stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.79,0:50:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}以下所讲的{\r}\NLet what is said be recorded...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.92,0:50:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是代表罗马元老院之审判与裁定{\r}\N...as the judgment and decree of the Senate and people of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.26,0:50:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没有审判啊{\r}\NThere is no judgment here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.26,0:50:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}裁定也按克莉奥佩特拉的意思{\r}\NAnd the decree not Rome's, but Cleopatra's.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.50,0:50:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你被她骗了，凯撒{\r}\NShe has lied to you, Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.27,0:50:44.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她跟她的奴仆骗了你！{\r}\NShe and her slaves lie to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.54,0:50:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}尚未请你离席，波第诺斯{\r}\NYou have not been accused, Pothinus. Thus far.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.71,0:50:53.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}兹控告你煽动对罗马之战{\r}\NYou are now charged with inciting and abetting war against the Roman army.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.68,0:50:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}以及图谋暗杀克莉奥佩特拉{\r}\NYou are now charged with plotting to assassinate Queen Cleopatra.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.52,0:51:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}两项罪名成立，宣判死刑{\r}\NYou are guilty of both. You are sentenced to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.81,0:51:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}太光了，遮掉一些光线？{\r}\NIt's too bright in here. Shut out some of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.09,0:51:40.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒，连你也想杀我{\r}\NAre you going to kill me too, Caesar?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.59,0:51:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我的罪名是什么？{\r}\NWhat am I accused of?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.76,0:51:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}托勒密国王不再受罗马保护{\r}\NKing Ptolemy is hereby removed from the protective custody of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.27,0:51:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}立刻送返{\r}\NHe'll leave within the hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.40,0:51:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亚其勒斯将军的营中{\r}\N...and be conducted safely to the camp of Achillas.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.61,0:51:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}送我回我的部队？{\r}\NAchillas! You're going to send me back to my own troops?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.21,0:52:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他的军师席铎特斯亦将会同行{\r}\NHe is to be accompanied by his learned tutor, Theodotus.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.58,0:52:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听到没有？你也获救了！{\r}\NDo you hear that? You'll be saved along with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.72,0:52:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不要这么开心，小白痴！{\r}\NStop grinning, you little idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.35,0:52:11.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}恕我多口讲句 你明知亚其勒斯被包抄夹在…{\r}\NMay I speak? You know that Achillas is trapped...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.36,0:52:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}密斯里达和你的部队之中{\r}\N...between your own legions and the armies of Mithradates.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.76,0:52:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将我王送去等于送死{\r}\NTo send His Majesty to fight them may mean his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.26,0:52:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}此乃身为刖的风险{\r}\NAn occupational hazard for those who will be king.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.07,0:52:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}等等{\r}\NBut then certainly not I, Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.54,0:52:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但我不是一国之君 也不是将领，不懂战争{\r}\NI'm no king, nor general. What do I know of war?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.90,0:52:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只是个学者{\r}\NA simple scholar.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.14,0:52:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只是个史弱书生{\r}\NA man of thoughts and words.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.64,0:52:33.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不用多言！{\r}\NToo many words. Enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.98,0:52:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一切按宣判执行{\r}\NLet all be done properly as decreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.44,0:53:02.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}弗拉维乌斯{\r}\NFlavius.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.14,0:53:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将匕首还给阿波罗德斯{\r}\NFind Apollodorus. Return his dagger to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.01,0:53:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}先洗干净 上面沾满波第诺斯的血{\r}\NYou might clean it first. It has Pothinus all over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.68,0:53:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}好，好，我知道我累了 我会去睡{\r}\NYes, yes, I know I'm tired. I promise I'll sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.16,0:53:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你…啊 对不起，差点伤到你{\r}\NYou have my apologies for what almost happened to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.96,0:53:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒，可以说几句话吗？{\r}\NCaesar, will you talk with me for just a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.47,0:53:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}昨天很忙，昨晚没空{\r}\NYesterday was full. Tonight was long.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.87,0:53:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}今早事情又多{\r}\NThis morning has not been uneventful.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.37,0:53:34.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你事前知不知道{\r}\NDid you know that Apollodorus would kill Pothinus?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.14,0:53:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}阿波罗德斯要杀波第诺斯？ 他很耐心的等到宣判死刑{\r}\NHe was kind enough to wait until Rome had passed sentence of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.61,0:53:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我弟弟{\r}\NAnd my brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.68,0:53:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}和席铎特斯{\r}\N...and Theodotus?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.38,0:53:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}也可能被杀{\r}\NThey too will be killed, possibly.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.68,0:53:47.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}可能吧{\r}\NProbably.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.99,0:53:49.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}陛下抱歉，我真的很累了{\r}\NYour Majesty, I’m truly weary.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.69,0:53:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你早知道没有真正的危险{\r}\NYou knew all along, didn't you, that there was no real danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.69,0:53:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}密斯里达正在赶来{\r}\NThat Mithradates was on his way to reinforce you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.13,0:53:59.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你为什么不告诉我？{\r}\NWhy didn't you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.47,0:54:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我说我有备而来你不相信{\r}\NI said I was prepared. You wouldn't believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.80,0:54:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 不是我无礼，我真的要… - 我本来会信任你{\r}\N-I really must insist-- -I would've believed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.84,0:54:07.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 是你不信任我吧？ - 当然不是！{\r}\N-You didn't trust me. -Not for an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.24,0:54:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但，刚才{\r}\NAnd yet, in these last few minutes...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.58,0:54:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你确立了我的王位{\r}\N...you have made me undisputed queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.81,0:54:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}成为埃及唯一的统治者为什么？{\r}\NThe sole ruler of Egypt. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.52,0:54:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}明天或晚一点，我们可以谈谈{\r}\NPerhaps tomorrow, later in the day, we could talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.42,0:54:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 为什么，凯撒？ - 这最符合罗马的利益，拜托…{\r}\N-Why, Caesar? -It was best for Rome. Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.75,0:54:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 最符合埃及的利益 - 也对{\r}\N-Best for Egypt. -For Egypt too.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.49,0:54:27.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉，请你出去！{\r}\NCleopatra, get out. I beg of you, get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.72,0:54:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不需要那个{\r}\NThat will not be needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.19,0:54:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不需要隐瞒{\r}\NIt wasn't necessary for me to betray myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.69,0:55:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}本来我可以叫弗拉维乌斯{\r}\NI could have called out for Flavius.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.89,0:55:03.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你在墙上开了多少个洞窥看？{\r}\NHow many new spy-holes have you dug in the walls?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.03,0:55:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在我们也被偷窥？{\r}\NAre we being watched even now?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.43,0:55:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}看到弗拉维乌斯，叫他进来{\r}\NIf you see Flavius, you might send him to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.54,0:55:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 还想打发我走？ - 你到底还想要什么？{\r}\N-Still trying to dismiss me? -What is it you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.77,0:55:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只想帮你{\r}\N-What more do you want? -To be of help to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.64,0:55:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}从来都不会有任何帮助{\r}\NThere never has been help. There never will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.42,0:55:28.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在有了{\r}\NNow there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.89,0:55:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有一天我再也躲不了{\r}\NOne day it'll happen where I cannot hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.62,0:55:34.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在世人面前…{\r}\NWhere the world will see me fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.43,0:55:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当众倒下{\r}\NI shall tumble down before the mob...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.16,0:55:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}口吐白沫受人讪笑{\r}\N...and foam at the mouth and make them laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.97,0:55:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}被暴民撕成碎片{\r}\NAnd they'll tear me to pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.30,0:55:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}神也免不了这种疾病{\r}\NThe gods themselves had your sickness.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.64,0:55:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}汉尼拔…甚至亚历山大帝{\r}\NHannibal, even the great Alexander.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.68,0:55:51.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}最终还是倒下{\r}\NAnd in the end, they fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.98,0:55:54.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}被暴民撕成碎片{\r}\NWere torn to pieces by the mob.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.75,0:55:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你不会{\r}\NNot you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.25,0:56:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我会医好你的{\r}\NI will see to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.34,0:56:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我以罗马元老院和人民之名… 并依他们的意愿…{\r}\NIn the name of the Senate and the people of Rome and by their will.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.31,0:56:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃瑟丝女神宁可放弃她的地位 换取你的美貌{\r}\NIsis herself would surrender her place in heaven to be as beautiful as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.21,0:57:02.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你不该看我，任何人都不准{\r}\NYou're not supposed to look at me. No one is.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.25,0:57:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们不看，就不知道我看你{\r}\NIf they aren't looking, how do they know I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.39,0:57:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你该跪下{\r}\NYou should be kneeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.69,0:57:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}对着这么多到来探访的国王…{\r}\NWould that do before all these visiting kings?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.26,0:57:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}装作他们都看不见我们？{\r}\NMaking believe they're not watching us?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.23,0:57:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的膝盖全是骨头{\r}\NYou have such bony knees.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.00,0:57:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不只多骨，也不惯做这种事{\r}\NNot only bony, but unaccustomed to this sort of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.95,0:58:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如果我们明天一早出发…{\r}\NIf we're to get an early start in the morning--
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.56,0:58:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}明天有什么事？{\r}\NWhat will it be tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.66,0:58:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}更多小麦？{\r}\NMore wheat?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.43,0:58:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我见到的已比全罗马还要多{\r}\NWhat I’ve seen already could feed more legions than Rome ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.23,0:58:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}足以喂饱全世界{\r}\NThere's enough to feed the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.33,0:58:29.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}黄金更多{\r}\NMore gold then.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.17,0:58:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}何不将全世界买下？ 相信你有足够的财力{\r}\NWhy not buy the world? Surely you have enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.64,0:58:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}至少能比罗马养更多军队{\r}\NAt least enough to pay more legions than even Rome has ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.58,0:58:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}更多花岗岩、大理石{\r}\NMore granite, more marble...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.78,0:58:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}奴隶爱建什么便建什么{\r}\N...more millions of slaves to build whatever needs building.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.45,0:58:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}通印度的新路，往东方的捷径{\r}\NBetter routes to India, shorter routes to the East.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.52,0:58:49.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及无所不有{\r}\NWhat can there be in Egypt that I haven't seen?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.62,0:58:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及正因此而成为埃及{\r}\NEgypt itself. The reason for Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.76,0:58:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我的责任在罗马{\r}\NMy responsibility is Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.00,0:58:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亚历山大明白{\r}\NAlexander understood it...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.60,0:59:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}可以由埃及统治全世界{\r}\N...that from Egypt he could rule the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.97,0:59:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他很年轻，你更年轻{\r}\NHe was very young. And you, even younger.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.64,0:59:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这个年纪的梦全随时间淡去{\r}\NAt your age, such dreams have a reality which grows less in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.65,0:59:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒不再造梦了吗？{\r}\NCaesar no longer dreams?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.35,0:59:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}对我的身分来说很危险{\r}\NDangerous to a man of my calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.85,0:59:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我认为有必要{\r}\NNecessary, I would have thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.87,0:59:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不能离开罗马太久 那会有问题{\r}\NI can't stay away from Rome too long. There are problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.54,0:59:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}马克安东尼一直催我回去{\r}\NMessages from Marc Antony endlessly demanding my return.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.81,0:59:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}回程中，东、北两面还有战争{\r}\NAnd on my way back, wars to be fought in the east and north.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.15,0:59:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}即使在罗马也有人作对{\r}\NEven in Rome itself I'm not without opposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.92,0:59:56.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}用对付亚其勒斯的方法应付{\r}\NDo to them what you did to Achillas.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.76,0:59:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}性质不同{\r}\NThis is opposition of a different sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.26,1:00:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}像蜘蛛网般精巧{\r}\NThey weave it cleverly, lightly, like a cobweb.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.16,1:00:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}蜘蛛网要经常清除{\r}\NYou know what happens when cobwebs are not regularly swept away.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.36,1:00:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你信任马克安东尼？{\r}\NDo you trust this Marc Antony?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.74,1:00:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}世上我只有安东尼一个可以信任{\r}\NIf anyone in the world, I trust Antony.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.04,1:00:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}让他扫蜘蛛网，你留在我身边{\r}\NLet him brush away the cobwebs for you and stay with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.54,1:00:20.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你宣布了独裁一年{\r}\NYou've been declared dictator for a year.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.11,1:00:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在这段时间内可以任意行事{\r}\NYou can do what you want with your time.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.25,1:00:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}除了继续独裁，其他什么都可以{\r}\NEverything but make it stand still.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.29,1:00:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}回罗马途中{\r}\NIf-- When you return to Rome...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.26,1:00:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}要打的仗很重要吗？{\r}\N...these wars that have to be fought on the way, are they important?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.23,1:00:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没有一场战争是不重要的{\r}\NWell, there's no such thing as an unimportant war.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.30,1:00:43.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我读过你对高卢战役的评论{\r}\NI've been reading in your commentaries about your campaigns in Gaul.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.70,1:00:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我的文笔像不像卡图卢斯？{\r}\NHow does my writing compare with Catullus?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.47,1:00:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这个嘛…不一样的东西{\r}\NWell, it's different.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.81,1:00:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}乏味{\r}\NDull.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.81,1:00:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}或许描绘得太仔细了{\r}\NPerhaps a little too much description.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.45,1:00:57.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的话很圆滑 我的评论员布鲁特斯说…{\r}\NYou're being tactful. Some of my critics, Brutus, for one...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.15,1:01:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我的拉丁文造诣很差{\r}\N...tell me my Latin is not only ungrammatical, but common.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.79,1:01:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你放过他不只一次{\r}\NYou spared his life more than once.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.22,1:01:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听说布鲁特斯是你儿子{\r}\NPeople say it's because Brutus is your son.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.59,1:01:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}真的吗？{\r}\NIs that true?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.66,1:01:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我没有儿子{\r}\NI have no son.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.13,1:01:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 卡普妮雅，你的第三任妻子 - 第四任{\r}\N-Calpurnia, your third wife... -Fourth.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.10,1:01:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}结婚多久了？十二年？{\r}\N...married to you how long? 12 years?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.31,1:01:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}而凯撒仍没有继承人{\r}\NAnd still, Caesar has no son, no child at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.11,1:01:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}大家都知道卡普妮雅不孕{\r}\NIt is well-known that Calpurnia is barren.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.61,1:01:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不孕的女人{\r}\NA woman who cannot bear children...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.62,1:01:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如同干涸的河流{\r}\N...is like a river that is dry.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.12,1:01:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}讨论这话题没有意义{\r}\NI see no purpose in discussing the subject further.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.02,1:01:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}女人负有使枯木结果的责任{\r}\NA woman, too, must make the barren land fruitful.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.93,1:01:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}使荒地生气蓬勃{\r}\NShe must make life grow where there was no life.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.20,1:01:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就像尼罗河滋养大地{\r}\NJust as the Mother Nile feeds and replenishes the earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.17,1:01:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我就是尼罗河{\r}\NI am the Nile.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.71,1:02:03.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我将会有众多子孙{\r}\NI will bear many sons.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.22,1:02:06.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃瑟丝女神告诉我的{\r}\NIsis has told me.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.19,1:02:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我的乳房精于孕育爱与生命{\r}\NMy breasts are filled with love and life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.02,1:02:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}双臀曲线分明而浑圆{\r}\NMy hips are rounded and well apart.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.56,1:02:19.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}据说这种女人{\r}\NSuch women, they say...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.07,1:02:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}擅于生儿育女{\r}\N...have sons.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.86,1:02:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当你第一次独自站在这里时{\r}\NThat first time when you stood here alone...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.09,1:02:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为什么流泪？告诉我{\r}\N...why did you cry? Will you tell me now?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.20,1:02:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}因为我失去了某些东西{\r}\NBecause I had lost something.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.93,1:02:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 是什么？ - 我一生的{\r}\N-What? -A lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.70,1:02:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 时间 - 胡说{\r}\N-Mine. -Nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.21,1:03:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为征服世界，他死时仅三十二岁{\r}\NHaving conquered the world, he died at 32.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.94,1:03:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我已经五十二岁{\r}\NI am 52.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.24,1:03:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我余下的责任是不让人征服{\r}\NMy remaining ambition is to keep the world from conquering me.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.05,1:03:16.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的野心就是他的{\r}\NYour ambitions must always have been his.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.06,1:03:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一向如此{\r}\NThey still must be.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.12,1:03:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}三十二岁时在西班牙{\r}\NShall I tell you something? When I was 32 in Spain...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.23,1:03:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}见到他的雕像{\r}\N...I came upon a statue of Alexander.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.47,1:03:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我也落泪{\r}\NI wept then too.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.77,1:03:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}即使是当时…{\r}\NEven then.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.07,1:03:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我希望你将他的剑带回去{\r}\NI want you to have his sword to take back with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.64,1:03:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 埋得太深了 - 挖得出来{\r}\N-Too deeply embedded. -It can be removed.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.04,1:03:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埋藏得太久了{\r}\NIt's buried in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.25,1:03:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 亚历山大的衣钵… - 对凯撒来说太沉重了{\r}\N-And Alexander's mantle? -Too heavy for Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.45,1:03:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他的梦想{\r}\NHis dream then.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.49,1:03:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒，继承他的梦想{\r}\NMake his dream yours, Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.66,1:03:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他伟大的计划{\r}\NHis grand design.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.09,1:03:58.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}继续完成它{\r}\NPick it up where he left off.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.27,1:04:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}完成他的征服大业{\r}\NOut of the patchwork of conquests...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.90,1:04:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}统一全世界{\r}\N...one world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.00,1:04:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}世界上只有一个国家 地球上只有一个民族{\r}\NAnd out of one world, one nation.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.57,1:04:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}和平的过生活{\r}\NOne people on earth living in peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.18,1:04:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你终于说出对我的期望{\r}\NSo you have told me at last what it is you want of me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.78,1:04:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亦是我们所想的！{\r}\NOf us!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.35,1:04:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这个单一民族 全世界的首都是…{\r}\NAt the center, the capital of this world, one people, one nation...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.29,1:04:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亚历山卓？{\r}\N...Alexandria?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.69,1:04:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 它是被拣选的 - 但我是罗马人{\r}\N-He chose it. -I am Roman.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.59,1:04:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他是希腊人，无关紧要 既然我们是同一民族{\r}\NHe was Greek! What will it matter when we're all one people?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.60,1:04:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我五十二岁了！他三十二岁时失败！{\r}\NI am 52. He was 32 and failed.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.60,1:04:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们会成功！{\r}\NWe will succeed.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.63,1:04:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的梦想，你的野心！{\r}\NYour dreams, your ambitions.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.60,1:04:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一辈子不足以实现这个梦想和野心{\r}\NOne lifetime is not enough for such dreams, such ambitions.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.68,1:04:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亚历山大的衣钵{\r}\NThe cloak of Alexander cannot be too heavy...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.55,1:04:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及舆罗马合力就不会太沉重{\r}\N...for Rome and Egypt to carry together.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.32,1:04:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若他的剑埋得太深呢？{\r}\NAnd what if his sword is too deeply embedded?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.52,1:04:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的剑可以取代它，凯撒！{\r}\NYours will replace it, Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.32,1:05:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你将政治与热情混淆了{\r}\NYou have a way of mixing politics and passion.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.46,1:05:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不知何时开始如何终结{\r}\NWhere does one begin and the other leave off?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.20,1:05:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}对我，没有开始，也没有终结{\r}\NThat did not start, nor will it end with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.40,1:05:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不管命运如何{\r}\NCleopatra, whatever it is, however it comes out...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.54,1:05:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}总是我自已的命运{\r}\N...leave me my destiny.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.37,1:05:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的命运不再只是你的{\r}\NYour destiny is no longer just yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.98,1:05:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}它也是我的{\r}\NIt's mine too.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.58,1:05:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}很快就会有人 不但继承亚历山大的农钵…{\r}\NSoon, there will be someone to carry both the cloak of Alexander...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.65,1:05:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}也延续凯撒的权力…{\r}\N...and the sword of Caesar...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.16,1:05:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}与名声{\r}\N...and the name of Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.49,1:05:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他将以这个身分统治埃及…{\r}\NAnd in that name he will rule Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.23,1:05:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}或世界给予他的任何地方！{\r}\NAnd whatever part or all of the world that we give him...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.03,1:05:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们的孩子{\r}\N...our child...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.07,1:05:50.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将是你的继承人凯撒！{\r}\N...will be a son for you, Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.38,1:05:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我以埃瑟丝女神之名立誓{\r}\NBy Isis, I swear it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.12,1:06:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你可否迟些少回罗马？{\r}\NCould you put off your return to Rome...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.62,1:06:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不用太久的{\r}\N...just long enough?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.45,1:06:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我已尽快赶来{\r}\NI came as quickly as I could.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.22,1:06:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒之家随时欢迎安东尼{\r}\NAntony is welcome to Caesar's house as often and as quickly as he likes.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.63,1:06:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}身为凯撒的妻子希望你能…{\r}\NAs Caesar's wife, before truth is distorted into vicious gossip...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.30,1:06:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在谣言散播前知道 你丈夫已娶克莉奥佩特拉{\r}\N-...I wanted you to hear-- -That my husband has married Cleopatra.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.44,1:06:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这里有你最喜爱的新酒{\r}\NThere's some fresh wine. One of your many favorites.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.34,1:07:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}据闻婚礼依照埃及宗教礼俗举行{\r}\NThe ceremony, according to vicious gossip, was in the Egyptian religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.65,1:07:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}即使如此也不能当真{\r}\NEven if true, that can't be taken seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.48,1:07:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}婚礼中，他被正式宣布成为埃及的神{\r}\NDuring which he was formally declared an Egyptian god.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.49,1:07:10.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}终于成为神{\r}\NOfficially divine, at last.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.59,1:07:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒一定很高兴{\r}\NThat must have pleased Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.96,1:07:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}卡普妮雅我们大家都了解凯撒{\r}\NCalpurnia, we know Caesar, you and I.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.70,1:07:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这所谓的婚姻根据罗马法律并无效{\r}\NThis so-called marriage has no validity under Roman law.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.13,1:07:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一定有某种政治目的{\r}\NThere must be political purpose to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.43,1:07:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}或许是罗马与埃及结盟的象征{\r}\NPerhaps a symbolic ceremony to ratify Rome's alliance with Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.87,1:07:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}或许只是沉溺于某种野蛮民族的习俗{\r}\NPerhaps merely indulging some barbaric custom.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.44,1:07:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}尽管既忠诚又体贴{\r}\NYou've been loyal and kind.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.81,1:07:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}也于第一时间赶来{\r}\NYou came as quickly as you could.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.71,1:07:39.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但恶意的诺言{\r}\NUnhappily, vicious gossip travels even faster than you...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.65,1:07:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}比你与真相还快{\r}\N...and the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.02,1:07:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你有否听闻克莉奥佩特拉 已怀了凯撒的孩子？{\r}\NHave you heard, for instance, that Cleopatra is carrying Caesar's child?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.46,1:07:50.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没错，安东尼{\r}\NYes, Antony.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.80,1:07:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们大家…{\r}\NWe know him...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.86,1:07:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}都了解凯撒{\r}\N...you and I.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.42,1:08:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}未来的罗马{\r}\NThere shall be--
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.56,1:08:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}未来的罗马{\r}\NThere shall be...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.66,1:08:25.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将会是…{\r}\N...Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.76,1:08:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}强大、孤单而缺乏爱{\r}\NMighty and alone and unloved.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.03,1:08:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}女强人{\r}\NA mistress.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.54,1:08:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一个女强人会抚养你成人{\r}\NA mistress shall raise thee again from earth to heaven...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.24,1:08:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}世界将进入公正与爱的时代{\r}\N...and all the world shall know a golden age of justice and of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.01,1:08:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃瑟丝女神将有嫡子！{\r}\NA son shall be born to Isis!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.68,1:08:47.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃瑟丝女神将有嫡子！{\r}\NA son shall be born to Isis!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.69,1:08:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马将视他为王{\r}\NRome shall know him in cloth of gold.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.52,1:08:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}东方将见他身披圣袍{\r}\NThe East shall see him laden with jewels and treasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.06,1:08:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及与罗马之子{\r}\NA son of Egypt and of Rome!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.03,1:09:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他将在此面对他的命运！{\r}\NHere shall he find his destiny!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.74,1:09:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}遵照我的话去做{\r}\NDo exactly as I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.94,1:09:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}孩子降世{\r}\NWhen the child is born...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.51,1:09:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}涂油宣布为王子后{\r}\N...after he is anointed and named royal prince...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.41,1:09:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}直接把他带去给凯撒{\r}\N...take him to Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.42,1:09:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}带凯撒来…{\r}\NBring Caesar here.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.92,1:09:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不！ 照我的说话{\r}\NNo. Exactly as I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.42,1:10:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将孩子带给凯撒 当着他手下面前{\r}\NTake the child to Caesar, in front of his men.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.49,1:10:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}明白吗？{\r}\NDo you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.70,1:10:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当着罗马人面前{\r}\NIn front of all the Romans.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.17,1:10:11.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将孩子放在凯撒面前{\r}\NLay him at Caesar's feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.47,1:10:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒面前{\r}\NAt Caesar's feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.54,1:10:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我会照你的吩咐去做{\r}\NI will do just as you say.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.23,1:10:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不用怕，王者出生从未试过有任何差错{\r}\NFear not. We have never lost a Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.56,1:10:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}完全是荒诞无稽之谈{\r}\NThat remark was insubordinate and in bad taste!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.57,1:10:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒，罗马法律规条中{\r}\NCaesar, remember Roman law.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.88,1:10:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一旦当众抱起婴孩…{\r}\NIf you pick up this child you acknowledge it's yours...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.01,1:10:57.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他将被视为罗马人及你的继承人{\r}\N...and a citizen of Rome, as your heir.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.67,1:11:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一个男孩！{\r}\NA son.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.18,1:11:30.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我有儿子了！{\r}\NI have a son!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.72,1:11:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 凯撒万岁！ - 凯撒万岁！{\r}\N-Hail Caesar! -Hail Caesar!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.09,1:11:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他已被封为埃及国王{\r}\NHe's been made king of Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.09,1:11:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们为他改名为凯撒里奥{\r}\NThey have named their bastard Caesarion.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.96,1:11:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒里奥王子{\r}\NPrince Caesarion.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.73,1:11:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马王位继承人的好名字！{\r}\NWhat better name for the heir to the throne of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.03,1:11:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马没有王位{\r}\NThere is no throne of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.90,1:11:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒不允许帝制{\r}\NNor shall there be, nor would Caesar tolerate one.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.04,1:11:56.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}儿子{\r}\NBut a son!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.81,1:12:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我真替凯撒高兴 他一直想要个儿子{\r}\NWe know how much he's wanted one. I am happy for Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.91,1:12:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的高兴很容易理解{\r}\NYour happiness is understandable enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.75,1:12:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒公开宣称有了儿手{\r}\NNow that Caesar has publicly recognized a son...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.75,1:12:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}世人不再揣测布鲁特斯的身世{\r}\N...one need no longer wonder about Brutus.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.75,1:12:12.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}卡斯卡，若你的身分没人怀疑 是解除痛苦吗？{\r}\NIs it a relief not to be wondered about, Casca?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.59,1:12:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}公开的身为…{\r}\NTo be known openly as you are for what you are:
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.59,1:12:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}骗子、莽汉与懦夫{\r}\NLiar, swindler, bully and coward.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.96,1:12:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}布鲁特斯，你的话会使卡斯卡掉头而去{\r}\NBrutus, you'll turn Casca's head with your flattery.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.30,1:12:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一旦掉头的话他将投入 马克安东尼的阵营{\r}\NAnd Casca's head, if turned, will see Marc Antony.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.94,1:12:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他比凯撒的幼子还可怕{\r}\NA part of Caesar more to be feared than his infant son.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.64,1:12:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒逗留埃及这样久 是为罗马着想{\r}\NBut it is for the good of Rome that Caesar has stayed so long in Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.15,1:12:38.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不在罗马，人们视他为神{\r}\NIn his absence, the people have come to worship him as a god.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.58,1:12:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}何必回来跟大家一样做个凡人？{\r}\NWhy should he return to show himself as mortal as the rest?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.15,1:12:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有些人害怕凯撒的野心{\r}\NThere are those who fear Caesar's ambition.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.46,1:12:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}害怕他摧毁共和政体吗？{\r}\NBut what is there to fear? That he will destroy the republic?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.93,1:12:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是的，他会{\r}\NYes, he will.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.50,1:12:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他一定会{\r}\NI promise you he will.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.60,1:12:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}西塞罗，你的舌头虽老却依然锐利{\r}\NYour tongue is old but sharp, Cicero.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.37,1:12:59.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}小心它割下自己的脑袋{\r}\NBe careful how you waggle it. It may cut off your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.64,1:13:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我比较担心你的剑，安东尼{\r}\NIt will more likely be your sword, Antony.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.27,1:13:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}又利又快{\r}\N'Tis just as sharp and quicker...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.31,1:13:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谁都怕{\r}\N...and frightened of heads.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.45,1:13:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}今天元老院酒气冲天{\r}\NThere'll be a strong smell of wine in the Senate today.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.05,1:13:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}连呼吸都要小心{\r}\NWe must breathe with restraint.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.52,1:13:24.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维，凯撒之子名叫…{\r}\NOctavian, this what's his name, this son of Caesar...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.86,1:13:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那令你不安吗？{\r}\N...does it upset you?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.83,1:13:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不会{\r}\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.57,1:13:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你真是…{\r}\NYou run off at the mouth so...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.53,1:13:33.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}惜话如金{\r}\N...one thinks your words are as precious to you as your gold.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.70,1:13:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}金石良言，要用得其所{\r}\NLike my gold, I use them where they are worth most.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.38,1:13:42.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}至于操守，我女友有个女友…{\r}\NAnd your virtue? My friend has a friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.91,1:13:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那方面也一样{\r}\NThat too.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.35,1:13:49.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大难，当你死时…{\r}\NYou know, it's quite possible, Octavian, that when you die...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.39,1:13:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你会觉得白白浪费了这一生{\r}\N...you will die without ever having been alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.73,1:14:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我会丢下你跟儿子不辞而别吗？{\r}\NI can't leave without saying goodbye to my son and to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.20,1:14:36.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我跟你儿子认为…{\r}\NWe thought, your son and I, that if we came to you...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.37,1:14:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}过来找你可以相处多几分钟{\r}\N...we would have those few minutes more.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.31,1:14:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}儿子，我要你记住…{\r}\NA good thing to remember, my son:
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.28,1:14:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只要不放弃，别人就夺不走{\r}\NWhat you will not let go, no one will take from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.78,1:14:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}小凯撒万岁，再见{\r}\NHail and farewell, little Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.90,1:15:15.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我包在地毯里被带到你面前 是一世纪前的事吗？{\r}\NWas it a century ago when I was dropped at your feet, wrapped in a carpet?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.81,1:15:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还是昨晚的事？{\r}\NOr was it last night?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.86,1:15:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}何时派人来接我们？{\r}\NWhen will you send for us? When?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.29,1:15:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 很快 - 很快？有多快？什么时候？{\r}\N-Soon. -How soon? When?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.93,1:15:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我回到罗马都需要不少时间{\r}\NSo much time must go by before even I reach Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.03,1:15:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}到底有多快？{\r}\NAnd then how soon?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.60,1:15:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不容易，但不会太久{\r}\NWithin reasonable time.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.97,1:15:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}何谓太久？{\r}\NTime is never reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.21,1:15:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}时间就是敌人{\r}\NTime is our enemy, Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.27,1:15:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如果当是征服你会用什么策略？{\r}\NAm I to conquer it for you? What plan of battle do you suggest?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.55,1:15:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我要带你儿子去罗马{\r}\NI must bring your son to Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.82,1:16:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马该见见凯撒之子…{\r}\NRome must see Caesar's son...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.49,1:16:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒世界的未来统治者{\r}\N...who will one day rule over Caesar's world.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.29,1:16:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒？{\r}\NCaesar?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.46,1:16:12.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}风浪快将对你不利{\r}\NI'm afraid the tides will soon be against you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.98,1:16:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不只时间，连风浪也一样{\r}\NNot only time, but the tides.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.02,1:16:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}即使是神也无可奈何{\r}\NEven as divinities, there seems little we can do about either.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.67,1:16:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但直到两年后{\r}\NBut only after more than two years...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.70,1:16:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}经历了非洲和中亚无数战役{\r}\N...and many wars in Africa and Asia Minor...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.54,1:17:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒才得以渡海凯旋回意大利…{\r}\N...was Сaesar able to cross over to Italy and come home at last...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.08,1:17:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}治理国内的事{\r}\N...to celebrate his triumphs and see to his affairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.24,1:17:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为表扬他所立的功劳 元老院兹授与凯撒…{\r}\N"In recognition, the Senate has bestowed upon Caesar...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.61,1:17:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马终生独特领袖之荣衔{\r}\N...the rank, privilege and title of dictator of Rome for life."
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.88,1:17:38.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}终生独裁领袖！{\r}\NDictator for life!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.22,1:17:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}终于成为罗马真正的统治者{\r}\NAt long last, he is master of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.49,1:17:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}阿波罗德斯，快去把事情准备好{\r}\NApollodorus, everything must be made ready at once.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.82,1:17:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}船只、奴仆…{\r}\N-Ships, servants-- -We've been ready for some time.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.49,1:17:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}再没有不来迎接我们的借口了{\r}\NSurely now nothing can prevent his sending for us...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.66,1:17:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}即使只是受邀参观加冕典礼{\r}\N...if only to attend his coronation as he did mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.77,1:17:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 陛下… - 白白浪费了三年！{\r}\N-Your Majesty-- -Three long, wasted years!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.24,1:18:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}元老院为何等那么久{\r}\NWhy should the Senate have taken so long...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.91,1:18:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}才宣告举世皆知的事实？{\r}\N...to recognize what the world has already known?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.91,1:18:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒早就是罗马的统治者{\r}\NThat Caesar was master of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.65,1:18:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}鲁非欧想发表意见{\r}\NRufio wishes to speak.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.35,1:18:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}陛下似乎有所误解{\r}\NYour Majesty seems to misunderstand.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.62,1:18:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}很明显凯撒已获授与独裁领袖{\r}\NIt seems quite clear. Caesar has been declared dictator of Rome for life.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.62,1:18:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马人眼中{\r}\NTrue. However, to the Roman...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.46,1:18:22.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}独裁领袖与统治者有很大分刖{\r}\N...there is a vast difference between dictator and master.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.19,1:18:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}无人能自称为罗马的统治者{\r}\NNo man can call himself master of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.50,1:18:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为什么不？{\r}\NWhy not?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.50,1:18:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}换句话说罗马人不允许…{\r}\NIt has a meaning far too close to a word no Roman will tolerate:
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.50,1:18:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}国王存在{\r}\NKing.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.14,1:18:43.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那么做独裁领袖有何意义？{\r}\NAnd to be dictator of Rome for life?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.28,1:18:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}意味终身受罗马人民爱戴{\r}\NIs to be granted the lifelong respect and honor of the Roman people.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.89,1:18:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}独裁者能独裁何事？{\r}\NAnd the dictates of the dictator?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.12,1:18:55.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}事事皆要得到元老院同意{\r}\NMust in each case, of course, be approved by the Senate of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.36,1:18:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谢谢你，鲁非欧{\r}\NThank you, Rufio.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.20,1:19:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}敌人！敌人！敌人！ 敌人！敌人！敌人！{\r}\NThe enemy! The enemy! The enemy!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.32,1:19:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}敌人！{\r}\NSosigenes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.56,1:19:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我建议邀请克莉奥佩特拉 你一定觉得很奇怪{\r}\NYou must think it odd that I propose an invitation to Queen Cleopatra.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.43,1:19:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你觉得奇怪吗？{\r}\NDo you?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.03,1:19:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及毕竟已正式与罗马结盟{\r}\NEgypt, after all, has been officially declared ally of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.00,1:19:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但… 我还是讶异那么多人投赞成票{\r}\NStill, I confess I was surprised at some of those who voted in favor.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.27,1:19:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你吃惊吗？{\r}\NWere you?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.61,1:19:46.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}非常感激今日受邀观礼{\r}\NMay I express my gratitude for being permitted to attend today's session?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.74,1:19:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}见到众人根据自己的…{\r}\NIt was truly inspiring...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.75,1:19:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}意愿行事令人印象深刻{\r}\N...to witness the free will of free men so fearlessly expressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.79,1:19:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他极希望参加{\r}\NHe seemed most anxious to be present.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.12,1:20:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 我认为不妨一试 - 你也这样认为吗？{\r}\N-I saw no harm in granting him permission. -Didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.29,1:20:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}今天总算见识到埃及的富有{\r}\NAfter today, never again shall I doubt the extent of Egypt's wealth.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.70,1:20:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不喜欢西塞罗的暗示{\r}\NI don't like Cicero's implication.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.93,1:20:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及再有钱也买不到元老院一席{\r}\NThere's not enough gold in Egypt to buy the honor of a Roman senator.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.87,1:20:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但似乎足够买他那一票{\r}\NMore than enough, it seems, to buy his vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.21,1:20:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}卜卦上说什么？{\r}\NHow was it now?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.31,1:20:24.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马将视他为王？{\r}\N"Rome will know him in cloth of gold."
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.63,1:20:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}据报，街道上已万人空巷{\r}\NAccording to reports, the reception in the streets has been extraordinary.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.67,1:20:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}女王下令队伍缓慢前进{\r}\NThe queen has instructed the procession to move slowly...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.28,1:20:53.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}迎合群众的喝采{\r}\N...for the people's enjoyment.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.81,1:20:58.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉准备俘虏罗马的人心{\r}\NI might almost believe Cleopatra set out to capture the citizens of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.02,1:21:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}的确如此{\r}\NOne would have every reason for believing exactly that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.15,1:26:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗谬勒斯和雷穆斯之后 从未见如此盛况{\r}\NNothing like this has come into Rome since Romulus and Remus.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.04,1:27:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他好大胆啊！{\r}\NHow unafraid he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.91,1:27:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那孩子好大胆啊！{\r}\NHow unafraid he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.37,1:29:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她征服了罗马人民！{\r}\NYour queen has conquered the people of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.34,1:29:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}对了…没错{\r}\NThe people, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.72,1:30:01.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}走路要像个国王…抬头{\r}\NNow then, walk like a king. Head up.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.22,1:30:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听群众欢呼{\r}\NListen to them cheer.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.29,1:30:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}登上王座{\r}\NTake your throne.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.33,1:30:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}向左右两边答谢{\r}\NBow to the right, left.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.96,1:30:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不顺眼的，就目露凶光{\r}\NNow an angry glance at someone who's displeased you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.34,1:30:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}很好，看到了没有 我都发抖了{\r}\NVery good. I tremble. See me tremble?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.74,1:30:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不，不要露出微笑{\r}\NNo, don't smile.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.74,1:30:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这样他们就不怕你了{\r}\NNot when they're trembling. It makes them stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.68,1:30:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在，犯人会被一个个拉到你面前{\r}\NNow the prisoners are dragged before you, one by one.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.08,1:30:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你要装出威严的样子 否则便没意义了{\r}\NThis one has no power anywhere, therefore means nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.65,1:30:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}要被认作高贵的统治者你要怎么说？{\r}\NBut you wish to be known as a noble ruler. What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.69,1:30:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我赦免你{\r}\NI pardon you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.33,1:30:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}大声点赦免罪 要让大家都听到{\r}\NLouder, boy. You pardon somebody, you want it known.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.66,1:30:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我赦免你{\r}\NI pardon you!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.70,1:30:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这就对了 接下来是谁？{\r}\NAh, now, who comes here?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.74,1:30:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一个老朋友你信任他，但他背叛你{\r}\NOnce your friend. You trusted him, and he turned against you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.41,1:30:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他有钱、有权、有家世{\r}\NHe has power, wealth and family.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.84,1:30:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他跪在你面前{\r}\NHe kneels. He begs you to be his friend again.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.18,1:31:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}求你再信任他{\r}\NTo have you trust him again.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.38,1:31:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}怎么办呢，小国王？{\r}\NAnd then? What then, little king?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.80,1:31:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒一定要先解决这当务之急？{\r}\NCaesar must wish what needs commanding.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.37,1:31:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是要放干沼泽的水解除疟疾之害…{\r}\NTo drain the Pontine Marshes. To free Rome from malaria.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.74,1:31:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}满足我的肚皮？{\r}\NTo fill my belly.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.74,1:31:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还是将泛滥的台伯河改道…{\r}\NTo control the Tiber's floods.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.54,1:31:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}改善奥斯提港满足我的野心？{\r}\NTo improve the harbor at Ostia. To please my ambition.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.64,1:31:31.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不是为公众筑路、建图书馆…{\r}\NAnd must I wish roads to be built, libraries for public use?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.55,1:31:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为解放的奴隶取得公民权？{\r}\NThe free men of Italy to be equal citizens to those of Rome?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.65,1:31:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}其中许多是我们认可的德政{\r}\NMany of these have merits and merit our approval.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.79,1:31:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们认可的德政？ 凯撒是否像小学生一样{\r}\N"Merit your approval." Is Caesar to come before the Senate each day...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.26,1:31:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}每天向元老院交作业？{\r}\N...like a schoolboy with his lessons, now passing, now failing?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.50,1:31:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}难道可以不顾罗马人的福祉？{\r}\NDo you suggest the Senate no longer deliberate the welfare of Rome?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.73,1:31:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你不想依法行事？{\r}\NTo end the process of Roman law?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.00,1:31:56.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我就是法律！ 我的话就是罗马人的福祉！{\r}\NI must be the law! And my word must be the welfare of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.74,1:32:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不然，请取消这无意义的 独裁执政者衔头{\r}\NElse, take from me this meaningless title of dictator.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.08,1:32:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我掌握政权已久{\r}\NI've carried a sword for too long.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.48,1:32:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不能再空有其表了{\r}\NI cannot now pretend with an empty scabbard.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.95,1:32:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒应该记得授与你独裁者{\r}\NSurely Caesar recalls the symbolic nature of the title "dictator"...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.59,1:32:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}衔头的象征意义{\r}\N...at the time it was conferred.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.69,1:32:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那是向你表达无上的荣耀…{\r}\NIt was to honor Caesar above all men...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.30,1:32:22.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}以及罗马人对你战功的谢意{\r}\N...and to indicate Rome's gratitude for Caesar's triumphs in its name.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.03,1:32:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我记得，布鲁特斯 而你记得那些战功吗？{\r}\NBrutus, I recall them well, those triumphs.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.37,1:32:29.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}记得那些战功吗？{\r}\NDo you?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.17,1:32:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}以法萨力亚为例{\r}\NPharsalia, for one. You trembled in Antony's hand...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.34,1:32:36.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当安东尼要依法…{\r}\N...when Antony was hot to separate you from your head...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.61,1:32:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}把你处死…{\r}\N...with just cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.85,1:32:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是我下令饶你一命{\r}\NMy command spared your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.15,1:32:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没得商量的 并非只是意图，而是直接下令{\r}\NThere was no deliberating body. It was not my wish, but my command.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.89,1:32:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}说清楚一点，就是独裁！ 你今天才得以满口大道理{\r}\NBy my dictate that you stand here dribbling virtue out of your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.56,1:32:51.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}坐下{\r}\NSit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.13,1:32:56.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不，我不要无用的礼遇{\r}\NNo, I want no more meaningless privileges and considerations.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.23,1:32:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不要只有安抚作用的荣耀{\r}\NNo more honors designed to pacify me.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.34,1:33:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}宁愿做个…{\r}\NI would rather have nothing. Remain what I am at heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.71,1:33:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}热心服务的平凡人{\r}\NA humble man, anxious only to serve.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.04,1:33:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为何雕像的眼睛总是无神？{\r}\NWhy are the eyes of a statue always without life?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.92,1:33:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们有没有人看过尼罗河？{\r}\NHave any of you here seen the Nile?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.52,1:33:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}找时间到那儿走一趟{\r}\NSpare yourselves the journey.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.02,1:33:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}看克莉奥佩特拉闪亮的眼神{\r}\NShe carries it within her eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.89,1:33:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒，时候不早了{\r}\NI suggest, Caesar, that the hour is late.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.50,1:33:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}对罗马人来说，很晚了{\r}\NVery late for Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.60,1:33:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我在说话啊，凯西尔斯！我…{\r}\NI was speaking, Cassius! I was....
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.37,1:33:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我说到哪里？{\r}\NNow, where was I?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.00,1:33:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}热心服务{\r}\N"Anxious to serve."
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.34,1:33:42.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我一辈子都在为群众服务{\r}\NYes, I’ve served. Served for all of my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.58,1:33:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为罗马打遍了半个地球{\r}\NI've won for Rome more than half of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.78,1:33:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们今天的地位都是全因为我{\r}\NMost of you owe your honors and fortunes to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.05,1:33:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在，希望你们照我讲的话去做{\r}\NAnd now I want you to do as I say.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.69,1:33:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}尊我为…{\r}\NYou will appoint me...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.96,1:33:58.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马胪{\r}\N...emperor of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.27,1:34:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}无须再就座{\r}\NThere is no need to resume your seats.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.27,1:34:11.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}仅代表众人感谢陛下款待{\r}\NOn behalf of all, thank you, Majesty, for your hospitality.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.44,1:34:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}晚安{\r}\NGood night.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.78,1:34:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}多谢，晚安{\r}\NThank you and good night.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.49,1:34:35.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒，他们后悔被召唤来这里 会议还是在元老院进行较恰当{\r}\NThey resent being summoned here for meetings properly held in the Senate.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.47,1:34:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}后悔？{\r}\NResent it, do they?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.90,1:34:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不懂…{\r}\NI cannot understand...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.40,1:34:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}雕像的眼是不会有神的{\r}\N...that the eyes of a statue should be always without life.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.01,1:34:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们恨我{\r}\NThey resent me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.95,1:34:55.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}因我太张扬{\r}\NTo flaunt me like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.79,1:34:59.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们会阻挠你本该拥有的东西{\r}\NThey'll use it to keep from you that which is already yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.52,1:35:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}靠天赋人权？不是吗？{\r}\NBy divine right, is that not so?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.60,1:35:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没错{\r}\NYes. It is.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.63,1:35:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就依天赋人权吧！{\r}\NBy divine right.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.60,1:35:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在元老院的会议中照样达成我的目标{\r}\NWe shall have the Senate, in its deliberations, deliberate that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.22,1:35:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你确定你苦心追求的…{\r}\NAre you quite sure what it is you want...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.05,1:35:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}目标吗？{\r}\N...so desperately?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.62,1:35:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一直非常确定{\r}\NI've always been sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.46,1:35:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒呢？{\r}\NAnd Caesar?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.49,1:35:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谁能替他发言？{\r}\NDoes anyone speak for him?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.23,1:35:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谁都不能{\r}\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.57,1:35:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}晚安{\r}\NGood night.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.51,1:35:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}站在由凯撒耸立在这里的新女神像…{\r}\NTell me, Brutus, is it proper to stand before this new goddess...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.68,1:36:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 面前符合礼仪吗？ - 还是罗马人必须下跪？{\r}\N-...Caesar has set here in the temple? -Or must we, as Romans, kneel?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.52,1:36:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}看到了没有？ 旁边还有一个空着的神位{\r}\NNot yet. See there, where room has been left for another deity?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.92,1:36:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当凯撒的神像在 克莉奥佩特拉的神像旁耸立好后…{\r}\NWhen the god Caesar stands beside the goddess Cleopatra...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.03,1:36:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马人会匍匐在他俩面前{\r}\N...then Rome will crawl before them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.19,1:36:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}事情要发生的话就必会发生{\r}\NWhen that day comes, if it comes.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.16,1:36:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 他要求被加冕为王 - 当晚提过一次，他神志不清{\r}\N-He demanded we make him emperor. -Once. That one night, it was his sickness.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.27,1:36:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他神智会愈来愈差 终究将我们统统杀死{\r}\NHis sickness grows worse. In the end, it will kill us.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.27,1:36:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他一旦要求称帝之后便会自视为神！{\r}\NHe asked once to be made emperor, but he's since decreed himself a god!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.57,1:36:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是皇帝与神，不只是皇帝{\r}\NEmperor and god. No longer just king, but emperor and god!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.38,1:36:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 布鲁特斯，醒醒吧！ - 你要我怎么办？{\r}\N-Brutus, open your eyes! -What do you want of me?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.12,1:36:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}人民想到罗马的荣耀时{\r}\NWhen the people think upon the honor of Rome...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.02,1:36:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}想到的是布鲁特斯{\r}\N...they think upon one man: He is Brutus.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.39,1:36:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}背负那荣耀之责任{\r}\NBy that honor and by the responsibility you carry...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.46,1:36:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}从凯撒的手中拯救罗马吧！{\r}\N...Brutus, save Rome from Caesar!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.23,1:36:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你不能要求我毁了凯撒！{\r}\NYou cannot ask me to destroy him.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.93,1:36:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那就让凯撒毁了罗马吧！{\r}\NThen let Caesar destroy Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.55,1:37:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼刚结束一场与我朋友的会议 明日元老院将宣布一项好消息{\r}\NAntony has just come from a meeting of my friends with good news.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.99,1:37:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}卢西尔斯明天将在元老院发动封我为王{\r}\NTomorrow at the Senate, Lucius Cotta will move that I be made king.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.56,1:37:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}提案会被通过{\r}\NIt will pass.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.00,1:37:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不明白{\r}\NBut I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.83,1:37:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}国王及皇帝{\r}\NKing and emperor.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.17,1:37:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}会通过？{\r}\NAnd it will pass?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.07,1:37:28.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}过去几个月… 我悄悄运用{\r}\NThe last few months, I've been enjoying...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.77,1:37:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}独裁者特权{\r}\N...one of the few privileges of being dictator.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.51,1:37:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}指派元老院议员{\r}\NI have been appointing senators.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.64,1:37:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}超过半数议员是我指派的{\r}\NSlightly more than half the Senate has been appointed by me.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.48,1:37:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}正如密斯里达的军队{\r}\NOnce again, the army of Mithradates...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.92,1:37:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你永远有备而来{\r}\N...on its way all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.45,1:37:45.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}会通过的{\r}\NIt will pass.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.02,1:37:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}明天，三月十五日将是…{\r}\NTomorrow, the ides of March, a day to be remembered...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.33,1:37:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我登上罗马王位的纪念日{\r}\N...the Senate will declare me king of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.16,1:37:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没错，是国王，但非罗马王{\r}\NKing, yes, but not of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.16,1:37:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不是罗马王？什么意思？{\r}\NNot of Rome? What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.20,1:38:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们准备称你为罗马帝国国王 但不包括意大利{\r}\NThey'll offer you king of the Roman Empire, outside Italy.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.44,1:38:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们害怕…即使是你的朋友{\r}\NThey're afraid, Caesar. Even your friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.64,1:38:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}害怕人民{\r}\NAfraid of the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.51,1:38:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 或许假以时日… - 怕人民{\r}\N-Perhaps in time-- -To be afraid of the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.72,1:38:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}因为人民浪费时间！{\r}\NTo waste time on the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.88,1:38:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}除了罗马之外的国王？{\r}\NKing of all but Rome?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.05,1:38:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那还剩下什么？ 高卢的茅屋和不列颠的洞穴？{\r}\NWhat is there? The huts of Gaul? The caves of Britain?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.56,1:38:24.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}意大利以外的整个帝圈{\r}\NThe whole of the empire outside Italy.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.36,1:38:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不能接受！{\r}\NI will not accept.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.46,1:38:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们只给个空壳{\r}\NThey mean it to be an empty gesture.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.80,1:38:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}满足你的自大狂{\r}\NAnother title to please your fancy, flatter your ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.20,1:38:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}所言不差{\r}\NNothing more.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.14,1:38:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}真的会通过吗？{\r}\NAnd it will pass.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.58,1:38:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那么接受他，凯撒{\r}\NThen accept it, Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.98,1:38:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我从不接受一半的胜利{\r}\NI have never settled for half a victory.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.68,1:38:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不会的，全能的凯撒{\r}\NNor will you now. Caesar, mighty Caesar...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.39,1:38:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我所讲的正是你教我的{\r}\N...all I can say is what you've taught me:
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.36,1:38:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不断蚕食，终能鲸吞！{\r}\NTake a little, then a little more until finally you have it all.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.59,1:38:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}让他们称你为王{\r}\NLet them declare you king.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.83,1:39:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}即使只有中亚的一颗树{\r}\NEven if it's only of a tree in Asia Minor.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.10,1:39:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}其他的会接踵而来！{\r}\NThe rest will come to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.07,1:39:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}以前的经历再来一遍吗？{\r}\NTo redo once more everything I have already done?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.44,1:39:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}未征服之地在等你呢！{\r}\NIt's what you have never done, what you never conquered that waits for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.61,1:39:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马帝胪馕Ь队将听命于你{\r}\NThe great legions of Rome in the outer empire that will become your legions.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.71,1:39:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及的黄金与权力，你的埃及{\r}\NThe gold, the power of Egypt. Your Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.95,1:39:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你可以征服并拥有全世界！{\r}\NCaesar, you can conquer and hold the world as your own.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.59,1:39:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你不明白吗？{\r}\NWon't you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.43,1:39:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}国王和神都不是选出来的{\r}\NKings are not elected. Gods are not elected.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.70,1:39:38.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我明了，不只罗马整个意大利半岛…{\r}\NWhy, not only Rome but all of Italy upon which Rome stands...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.07,1:39:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}会像一滴汗珠滴进你手掌{\r}\N...must fall in your hands like a drop of sweat.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.94,1:39:43.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}随他们的意思封你为王{\r}\NLet them make you what they choose.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.14,1:39:46.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我和我的部队都效忠于你{\r}\NI'll serve with you. My legions with yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.78,1:39:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一起征服全世界 让亚历山大都自愧不如{\r}\NTogether we'll conquer a world beyond the wildest dreams of even Alexander.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.11,1:39:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}苏拉死后是什么样子？{\r}\NRome. What was Rome when Sulla died...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.22,1:39:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}夸萨斯在怕西亚战败后呢？{\r}\N...when Crassus lost the armies in Parthia?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.42,1:40:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这些人会像吓坏的狗一样{\r}\NThese same men came after me through the streets...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.42,1:40:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}跟在我后面 凯撒，救救我们！{\r}\N...howling like frightened dogs, "Caesar, save us!"
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.29,1:40:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}到时，我还会不屑…{\r}\NThey would've made me king then.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.80,1:40:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们称我为王{\r}\NI wouldn't let them then.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.64,1:40:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他被丢进墙来，死状可怖{\r}\NHe was thrown over the wall. It's not a pretty sight.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.48,1:40:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}钱庄老板泰塔斯！{\r}\NTitus, the moneylender.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.78,1:40:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他为何被杀和被丢进来？{\r}\NWhy should he be killed savagely and brought here?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.49,1:40:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}显然是警告我{\r}\NObviously, I am being warned.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.62,1:40:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}说不定下一个是我{\r}\NPerhaps I am next.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.66,1:40:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们胆敢威吓你…{\r}\NThey dare to threaten you?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.09,1:40:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 凯撒里奥！事发时他在哪里？ - 不远处{\r}\N-Caesarion. Where was my son--? -Not far away.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.13,1:40:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他被吓着了{\r}\NIt frightened him.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.47,1:40:53.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 雷彼德斯他现在有多少军队？ - 有十五队，但可能不只这数目{\r}\N-Lepidus, how many legions has he now? -Fifteen. Perhaps more.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.64,1:40:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 在哪里？ - 赛西亚{\r}\N-Where? -Scythia.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.68,1:40:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你我今晚与雷彼德斯共进晚餐{\r}\NYou and I will dine with Lepidus tonight.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.21,1:41:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谈妥军队与作战 列清该杀的人的名单{\r}\NWe'll talk of armies and battlefields and lists of men to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.35,1:41:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}明天元老院会议就随他们如何规划版图{\r}\NTomorrow in the Senate, let them offer the sands of Libya as my kingdom...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.89,1:41:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我一概接受{\r}\N...I will accept.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.93,1:41:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这是凯撒{\r}\NThis is great Caesar...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.67,1:41:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}受罗马爱戴的凯撒{\r}\N...beloved by Rome...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.57,1:41:57.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们有责任牺牲生命{\r}\N...and at least one of us...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.34,1:42:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}来维护罗马{\r}\N...who must die so that Rome may live.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.88,1:42:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若果真的要这样做 就不必感到羞耻与恐惧{\r}\NIf it must be done, then let us do it unashamed and unafraid.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.08,1:42:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若罗马拒绝有个国王…{\r}\NIf the world is to know that it is Rome that will not have a king...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.95,1:42:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们就自由、公然、光荣的… 在光天化日下去争取{\r}\N...then let us make it the honorable act of free men in the light of day.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.39,1:42:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}什么时候，布鲁特斯{\r}\NIn the light of what day, Brutus?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.76,1:42:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}明天？{\r}\NTomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.70,1:42:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就在元老院会议上{\r}\NIn the curia of the Senate?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.23,1:42:27.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们要带备武装吗？{\r}\NAnd shall we be armed, all of us?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.64,1:42:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}德西玛斯，你明天到凯撒家去 护送他到元老院{\r}\NDecimus, come to Caesar's villa early tomorrow to escort him to the Senate.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.48,1:42:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}辛巴，马克安东尼不能 跟凯撒一起进入会议室{\r}\NCimber, Marc Antony must not enter the curia with Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.98,1:42:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}找藉口引开他或谈谈雷彼德斯家的事{\r}\NOn a pretext, lead him aside to speak of what you heard at Lepidus' house.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.82,1:42:49.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我想起一件奇怪的事{\r}\NI remember something odd.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.56,1:42:52.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒问过我们{\r}\NAt one point, Caesar asked of each of us...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.33,1:42:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}喜欢什么死法{\r}\N...what manner of death we would choose.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.40,1:42:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}问到我时，他说{\r}\NAnd Caesar, when it came to him, looked straight at me and said:
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.17,1:43:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}猝死？{\r}\N"Sudden."
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.97,1:43:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}很奇怪吧？{\r}\NOdd, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.26,1:43:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我以为你还在睡觉{\r}\NI was afraid I'd find you still asleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.77,1:43:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒里奥还在睡 他昨晚睡不着{\r}\NCaesarion is. He was awake most of the night.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.27,1:43:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}暴风雨吓着他了？{\r}\NDid the storm frighten him?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.27,1:43:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他说没有，但他真的吓坏了{\r}\NHe said not, but it did. I could tell.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.44,1:43:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有时间进来吗？{\r}\NHave you time to come in?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.45,1:43:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}德西玛斯正在等着 他要送我去元老院{\r}\NDecimus awaits. He came by expressly to accompany me to the Senate.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.32,1:43:49.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}德西玛斯？他以前有这么做吗？{\r}\NDecimus? Has he done this before?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.02,1:43:51.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}狡诈的政治家{\r}\NA shrewd politician.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.85,1:43:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在这特别的日子他希望与我同行 以提高他的身价{\r}\NHe hopes to benefit by arriving with me, this day of days.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.66,1:43:58.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}让安东尼紧随你身边{\r}\NKeep Antony close by.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.00,1:44:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你也是？{\r}\NYou too?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.06,1:44:05.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马女人今日都忐忑不安{\r}\NThe ladies of Rome seem to have caught each other's fears this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:05.23,1:44:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}好像传染病一样{\r}\NLike a head cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.24,1:44:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}卡普妮雅今天还求我不要到元老院{\r}\NCalpurnia pleaded with me not to go to the Senate at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.67,1:44:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她为何不想你去？{\r}\NWhy? Why would she not want you to go?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.34,1:44:16.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只是昨夜的恶劣天气{\r}\NOh, the bad night. Nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.81,1:44:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她尖叫着从梦中惊醒{\r}\NShe awoke screaming in her sleep. The thunder, the lightning.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.48,1:44:24.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她梦见我被谋杀{\r}\NShe dreamed that she saw me murdered. That she saw me...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.92,1:44:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我，或我的雕像，全身都是血{\r}\N...or a statue of me covered in blood.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.36,1:44:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}仆人告诉她看见天堂有人身体着火{\r}\NThe servants told her of seeing men of fire in the heavens...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.06,1:44:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}怪事连连{\r}\N...odd happenings and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.26,1:44:35.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}广场上看见怪鸟{\r}\NStrange birds were seen in the Forum.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.20,1:44:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一只飞进元老院 衔着月桂枝{\r}\NOne flew into the Senate carrying a sprig of laurel which it dropped...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.54,1:44:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}放在庞培的雕像上{\r}\N...at the base of Pompey's statue.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.37,1:44:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}庞培？{\r}\NPompey?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.28,1:44:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 凯撒，我好害怕！ - 你该不会叫我避开吧？{\r}\N-Caesar, I'm afraid. -You must not tell me to stay away.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.91,1:44:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我也该害怕吗？{\r}\NShall I too be afraid?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.35,1:44:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒能因为暴风雨 而放弃他的江山吗？{\r}\NCan it be said of Caesar, he gave up the world because of a thunderstorm?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.75,1:45:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他的神威竟向迷信屈服？{\r}\NThat such divinity that was in him ran before mortal superstition?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.46,1:45:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我觉得你需要我{\r}\NI feel you need me now...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.76,1:45:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}而我却帮不上忙{\r}\N...and I cannot help you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.80,1:45:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那就帮我像以往般活下去 有别于众人…{\r}\NThen help me to live as I have lived, always differently from the rest.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.30,1:45:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一辈子在贪生怕死里苟且偷安{\r}\NThe others, for whom life is merely an endless fear of dying.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.07,1:45:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}愿众神…{\r}\NYour gods...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.98,1:45:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}与你同在，凯撒{\r}\N...and mine go with you, Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.98,1:45:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}除你之外，世上尽是小人{\r}\NThe world, except for you, is filled with little men.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.69,1:46:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}烈火熊熊{\r}\NFire burns.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:39.02,1:46:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}烈火熊熊{\r}\NFire burns.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.49,1:46:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}狂风不断{\r}\NThe winds of destruction blow.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.96,1:46:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}坚强{\r}\NRome...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:49.16,1:46:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}孤寂的罗马狂风不断袭击你！{\r}\N...mighty and alone, the winds of destruction blow down upon thee!
Dialogue: 0,1:46:53.37,1:46:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}暴风、冰雹{\r}\NStorms and hail shall cut down wheat...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.80,1:46:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}摧毁五谷、飞禽… 以及天下万物{\r}\N...shall cut down birds and living things of earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:58.87,1:47:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}连天上众神{\r}\NThe heavens...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.38,1:47:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}都难以幸免{\r}\N...and the gods themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.01,1:49:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我的儿子！{\r}\NMy son!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.83,1:49:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒！凯撒！{\r}\NCaesar! Caesar!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.53,1:49:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒！凯撒！凯撒！…{\r}\NCaesar! Caesar!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:23.50,1:52:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我迟了，太多事要办了{\r}\NI would've come sooner. There was much to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:25.83,1:52:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你做得很好{\r}\NAnd it seems you have done it extremely well.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:31.21,1:52:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就是这里吗？{\r}\NIs that where--?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.58,1:52:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}对{\r}\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.98,1:52:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在埃及，我们为英雄建纪念碑{\r}\NIn Egypt, we build eternal monuments to our dead heroes.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:43.02,1:52:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们则像烧垃圾般把他烧掉{\r}\NHere, you burn them like rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.15,1:52:47.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}再见{\r}\NGoodbye.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:47.49,1:52:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我带来几个十号军团的人 你很安全，不必害怕{\r}\NI've brought the 10th Legion and Rufio. You have nothing to fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.93,1:52:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}即使不必害怕也没有理由留下{\r}\NNothing to fear? That's no reason for staying.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.93,1:52:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}太多事发生得太快{\r}\NSo much has happened so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:59.40,1:53:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}必须收拾残局{\r}\NSuddenly I have the pieces of a broken world to pick up:
Dialogue: 0,1:53:02.94,1:53:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一定要乘夜出走吗？{\r}\NCaesar, you running off at night like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.01,1:53:07.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为什么我要留下来？{\r}\NDo you suggest that I stay? Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:08.18,1:53:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我累得无法解释{\r}\NDon't ask me to be clear about my feelings right now. I’m tired.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.45,1:53:15.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}即使精神爽利 我想也没法完全表达{\r}\NAnd with you, it's never easy to say my meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.39,1:53:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但你表达得很好，安东尼{\r}\NBut you speak so well, Antony.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:19.62,1:53:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听说你宣读凯撒遗嘱时很激动{\r}\NI've been told how excitingly you read Caesar's will...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:23.09,1:53:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}向哭泣着的凶手 自由、民主的罗马人民宣读{\r}\N...to the sobbing, murdering, free citizens of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:27.36,1:53:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}指定他侄儿屋大维继位！{\r}\NNaming as his heir his great nephew, Octavian!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.30,1:53:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我懂得凯撒的心愿与理由！{\r}\NI knew Caesar's will and the reasons for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:34.80,1:53:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若不指定屋大维继位{\r}\NIf Octavian hadn't been named...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:36.97,1:53:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们母子还能活多久？{\r}\N...how many hours or minutes would you and your son have survived?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:41.54,1:53:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如果凯撒是国王{\r}\NAnd if Caesar had become truly king...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:44.28,1:53:47.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他会指定屋大维吗？{\r}\N...do you believe he would still have named Octavian?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.65,1:53:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}无论如何，事情已结束了{\r}\NIn any case, it's over.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.99,1:53:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯萨…{\r}\NCaesar...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:53.92,1:53:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他的梦想跟他一并被谋杀{\r}\N...and the dream that was murdered with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.63,1:54:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}先是亚历山大的梦想{\r}\NFirst Alexander's...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.10,1:54:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}然后是凯撒的…{\r}\N...then Caesar's.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:03.40,1:54:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}都结束了{\r}\NNow over. Finished.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:05.63,1:54:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 首先，罗马必须恢复秩序 - 又是罗马{\r}\N-First, Rome must be put in order. -Rome again.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.47,1:54:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}布鲁特斯等凶手已逃脱了几个{\r}\NBrutus, Cassius and the others must be found and killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:11.44,1:54:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 必须逮捕回来处死 - 然后呢？{\r}\N-Then? -Then in death...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:13.08,1:54:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒死后理应享有生前应得的封号 甚至被奉为神明{\r}\N...Caesar must be granted the power and title he was denied in life. Deified, even.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:17.31,1:54:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}过世的国王，死去的神明 现在罗马安全了{\r}\NA dead king, a dead god. Safe enough even for Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:21.45,1:54:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒之子，凯撒里奥 有权要求受封为胪跤肷衩{\r}\NCaesarion as Caesar's son could claim both the title of king and his deification.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:27.19,1:54:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}又是哪个执法单位会执行这项授舆？{\r}\NAnd to what court of law would my son and I take our claim?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.36,1:54:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我会亲自向元老院提议{\r}\NI will present it to the Roman Senate myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:37.03,1:54:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我相信你会这样做{\r}\NI believe you would.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:40.00,1:54:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}被议士们讪笑之后…{\r}\NAnd after the noble senators have stopped laughing...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:43.51,1:54:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们母子是否该向罗马宣战？{\r}\N...do my son and I then declare war on Rome?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:46.98,1:54:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不，这需要另一位凯撒{\r}\NNo. For this, a Caesar would be needed.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:51.68,1:54:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你时间有限{\r}\NYou have very little time.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:56.62,1:54:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}另一位凯撒{\r}\NAnother Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.02,1:55:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谢谢你，我不会忘记你的恩情{\r}\NBut thank you. I shall remember your kindness to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.69,1:55:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 你太轻易放弃了 - 是吗？{\r}\N-You give up too easily. -Do I?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:07.56,1:55:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我到亚历山卓再与你详谈{\r}\NLet me come to Alexandria and talk more with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:10.70,1:55:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 随时欢迎 - 可能的话，就是今晚{\r}\N-Whenever you like. -Now. Tonight, if I could.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:17.07,1:55:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只要你铭记在心中{\r}\NIn any case, try to remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:44.99,1:56:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}（中场休息）{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:47.93,1:59:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼追捕行刺凯撒的凶手 差不多有两年时间{\r}\NFor more than two years did Antony seek out the assassins of Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:52.43,1:59:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他与凯撒的继位者{\r}\NAt last, at Philippi...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:54.47,1:59:58.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维合力 终于在菲利比{\r}\N...he was able to set against them his legions and those of Octavian...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:58.81,2:00:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}与叛党对垒{\r}\N...who was Caesar's heir.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:01.19,2:00:03.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯西尔斯第一个自杀{\r}\NCassius was the first to die...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:03.48,2:00:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}身亡{\r}\N...by his own hand.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:05.69,2:00:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}接下来是布鲁特斯以及其他人{\r}\NThen Brutus and the others.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:46.54,2:01:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼万岁！{\r}\NHail Antony!
Dialogue: 0,2:01:49.21,2:01:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼万岁！{\r}\NHail Antony!
Dialogue: 0,2:01:54.72,2:01:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼之军万岁！{\r}\NHail Antony's legion!
Dialogue: 0,2:02:10.49,2:02:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}记得，菲利比之仗{\r}\NYou remember Philippi.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:13.28,2:02:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是他打胜的{\r}\NHe won it.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:16.24,2:02:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}阁下{\r}\NMy lord.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:18.58,2:02:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 这边请 - 但我的帐蓬在这边{\r}\N-This way. -But my tent is this way.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:24.83,2:02:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}稍后再见他屋大维令我心生沮丧{\r}\NLater. I'll see him later. Octavian depresses me.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:29.46,2:02:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你答应过的{\r}\NYou promised.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:41.27,2:02:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}战事结束，我们赢了{\r}\NWell, the fighting's over. We've won it all.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:44.48,2:02:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你会迅速恢复健康{\r}\NYour health should improve quickly now.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:46.69,2:02:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就算死也该与你一起战死沙场{\r}\NEven if I die, my place is with you on the field.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:49.69,2:02:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 你不该拦着我 - 凯撒病得无法上马{\r}\N-You were wrong to prevent me. -Caesar was ill.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:52.49,2:02:55.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒？哦，我又忘了{\r}\NCaesar? Ah, yes. I keep forgetting.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:56.20,2:02:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我也继承了他的名字，改名凯撒{\r}\NI have inherited the name. I have made it mine.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:59.12,2:03:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有何不可？反正不会搞乱{\r}\NWhy not? You'll never be confused with the other one.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:03.58,2:03:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}至少你的队伍在我指挥下骁勇善战{\r}\NAt least your troops fought bravely, under my command.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:07.17,2:03:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亚格里巴已告诉我了{\r}\NAgrippa has kept me fully informed.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:10.17,2:03:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}海军将领为何在此？{\r}\NWhat were you doing there?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:11.92,2:03:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这是陆地上的肉搏战 不是海上的大船相撞{\r}\NThe battle was fought on land, between men, not wood bumping on water.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:15.93,2:03:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你因为预测会下大两 而带他来的吗？{\r}\NWhy did you bring Agrippa? Were you expecting rain?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:19.39,2:03:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}要不要选块靓地，我们单对单？{\r}\NShall we choose a piece of land, just you and I?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:22.60,2:03:25.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不准多言 我们有事要谈{\r}\NBe quiet. There are matters to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:25.27,2:03:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你反对亚格里巴留下吗？{\r}\NHave you an objection to Agrippa remaining?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:29.02,2:03:33.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我永远反对亚格里巴{\r}\NI object to Agrippa at all times.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:38.45,2:03:40.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}无奈的躺在这里{\r}\NLying here, indisposed...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:40.62,2:03:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你有很多时间考虑那个问题{\r}\N...you must have had time to consider the problem.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:43.95,2:03:47.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我想最好继续由三巨头执政{\r}\NI think it is best to continue the Triumvirate.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:47.25,2:03:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你、我和雷彼德斯{\r}\NYou and I and Lepidus.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:50.67,2:03:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}好啊{\r}\NVery well.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:52.67,2:03:56.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}雷彼德斯管非洲和各岛屿 你主掌西班牙和高卢{\r}\NLepidus shall have Africa and the islands. You, Spain and Gaul.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:56.76,2:04:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马和意大利则三人共治{\r}\NRome and Italy to be administered by the three of us, jointly.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:01.14,2:04:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 你呢？ - 其他的归我管理{\r}\N-And you? -All the rest.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:04.85,2:04:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}雷彼德斯在非洲，你在东方{\r}\NThen, with Lepidus in Africa and you in the East...
Dialogue: 0,2:04:08.39,2:04:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}恢复意大利罗马的秩序 就变成我的问题{\r}\N...bringing order to Rome and Italy will be my problem.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:11.73,2:04:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 看起来是如此 - 西班牙和高卢的税收不足{\r}\N-So it seems. -Spain and Gaul aren't enough.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:14.48,2:04:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我需要钱{\r}\NI'll need money.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:16.03,2:04:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 罗马又已经有抗税暴动 - 我听说了{\r}\N-There have been tax riots in Rome. -So I’ve heard.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:21.07,2:04:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}说定了{\r}\NDone.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:25.79,2:04:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一言为定{\r}\NAnd done.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:51.60,2:04:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你认为凯撒会同意吗？{\r}\NWould Caesar approve, do you think?
Dialogue: 0,2:04:53.86,2:04:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当然，可能埃瑟丝的黑面纱 会令他不高兴{\r}\NDefinitely. Perhaps the veil of Isis would have bothered him a bit.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:58.44,2:05:00.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}三年了{\r}\NThree years...
Dialogue: 0,2:05:00.53,2:05:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马人只记得金币上他的头像{\r}\N...and Rome remembers him only by the image on a gold coin.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:04.66,2:05:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我带回来的那种金币吗？{\r}\NAre they those I brought back with me?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:07.45,2:05:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维下令铸造{\r}\NWhen Octavian had them struck off...
Dialogue: 0,2:05:09.62,2:05:12.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}以纪念凯撒的神威{\r}\N...it was to commemorate Caesar's deification.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:12.83,2:05:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}顺便连神威也继承{\r}\NSo that he could inherit Caesar's divinity together with all the rest.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:17.80,2:05:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}神死后也无法改遗嘱{\r}\NEven a dead god cannot rewrite his will.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:20.84,2:05:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼有向元老院提议 封凯撒里奥为王{\r}\NAntony did present Caesarion's claims to the Senate.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:24.01,2:05:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他实现了部分诺言{\r}\NHe kept that much of his promise.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:27.43,2:05:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他亦将实现其他的{\r}\NAnd he will keep the rest of it.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:29.81,2:05:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒过世已三年{\r}\NAfter almost three years since Caesar's death...
Dialogue: 0,2:05:32.98,2:05:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}菲利比之战也过了一年{\r}\N...more than a year since Philippi?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:35.19,2:05:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼会来，他需要埃及{\r}\NAntony will come. He will need Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:38.78,2:05:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及就是你{\r}\NEgypt is you.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:41.15,2:05:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}正是这个意思，安东尼需要我{\r}\NThat's what I meant, of course. Antony will need me.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:51.33,2:05:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谈钱就令我头痛{\r}\NFinances! My head hurts when you talk of money.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:54.04,2:05:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}换个话题吧{\r}\NChange the subject.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:55.79,2:05:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马消息{\r}\NAll right. News from Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:59.59,2:06:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维逼雷彼德斯出走{\r}\NOctavian has forced Lepidus out of his command and into exile.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:07.64,2:06:12.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}真后悔喝了那么多酒{\r}\NI wish I hadn't-- I wish I had not drunk so much today.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:12.27,2:06:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我也是{\r}\NSo do I.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:14.90,2:06:17.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我令你担心吗，鲁非欧？{\r}\NDo I trouble you, Rufio?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:18.11,2:06:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是的{\r}\NYes, you do.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:22.45,2:06:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒从不酒醉 没有事能让他头昏{\r}\NI'll wager Caesar was never befuddled by wine. Nothing befuddled Caesar
Dialogue: 0,2:06:26.37,2:06:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼，跟帕西亚之争将是苦战{\r}\NThe campaign against Parthia won't be easy.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:28.99,2:06:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 我们还剩多少部队？ - 难以估计{\r}\N-How many legions have we left? -It's hard to tell.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:32.16,2:06:35.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 逃兵很多，实力偏低 - 逃兵？{\r}\N-So many desertions. -Desertions?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:35.46,2:06:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}出不到军饷{\r}\NThey haven't been paid in months.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:40.00,2:06:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}记得我们入侵希腊时吗？{\r}\NYou remember when we started into Greece?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:42.55,2:06:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我跟士兵同住同食{\r}\NI lived with them, ate with them. I was one of them.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:45.84,2:06:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在跟他们距离好远，远得像回忆{\r}\NThey seem distant to me now, as if they were a memory.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:53.52,2:06:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们必须有钱出军饷{\r}\NWe must find the gold to pay them...
Dialogue: 0,2:06:56.52,2:07:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}粮食、补给、战舰、盔甲…{\r}\N...the wheat to feed them, supplies, ships, armor.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:00.73,2:07:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}说得容易，何来有钱？{\r}\NAnd where do you suggest we look for all these?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:04.28,2:07:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 或许，在往东一点… - 叙利亚？{\r}\N-I thought perhaps further to the east. -Syria?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:08.16,2:07:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 或许稍稍往南一点 - 伊索匹亚？{\r}\N-Perhaps more to the south. -Ethiopia?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:11.58,2:07:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}稍微往北一点…{\r}\NTo the north--
Dialogue: 0,2:07:12.83,2:07:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 不准你提她 - 我没有啊！{\r}\N-I forbid you to mention her! -I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:14.83,2:07:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 我不会像乞丐一样爬着去找她 - 为什么她没有主动资助？{\r}\NI won't crawl to her! Why hasn't she offered assistance?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:17.92,2:07:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 或许她不知道 - 她当然知道，她无所不知{\r}\N-She may not know. -She knows everything.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:20.54,2:07:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 就算为答应我为她所做的一切… - 或许她想亲自表达{\r}\N-If only out of gratitude-- -Perhaps she'll express it in person.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:23.92,2:07:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}让她来找我，我那么不如凯撒吗？{\r}\NThen let her come to me. Am I so much less than Caesar?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:26.88,2:07:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她贵为埃及女王，而且你答应过…{\r}\NNor is she less than Cleopatra, queen of Egypt, and you promised--
Dialogue: 0,2:07:30.43,2:07:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}女王！女王！脱光衣服还不是女人？{\r}\NQueen. Strip them naked, they're no longer queens.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:33.35,2:07:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}裸体将军又如何识别阶级？{\r}\NIt is also difficult to tell the rank of a naked general.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:37.40,2:07:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没军队的将军无异裸体{\r}\NAnd generals without armies are naked, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:41.65,2:07:44.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}好吧，折衷一下{\r}\NAll right. I'll meet her halfway.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:45.03,2:07:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我派你{\r}\NI'll send you to her.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:46.74,2:07:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 命令她来见我 - 如果是命令我就不必去了{\r}\N-You order her to come. -If I am to order her, I need not journey.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:50.78,2:07:52.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 那么就召见她 - 那更不好{\r}\N-Then summon her. -Even worse.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:52.58,2:07:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那就求她、拜托她 诱惑她随你怎说{\r}\NThen beg, entreat, cajole, find the word you like...
Dialogue: 0,2:07:55.66,2:07:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}洒香水、扮思春总之叫她来见我！{\r}\N...pour perfume, whinny like a stallion. But see that she comes to me.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:00.67,2:08:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我明白你的处境{\r}\NI understand your position, Rufio.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:03.50,2:08:05.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当然你也了解我的{\r}\NSurely you must understand mine.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:06.05,2:08:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不想加入他众多妃嫔之中{\r}\NI do not intend to join that long list of queens...
Dialogue: 0,2:08:09.80,2:08:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}幸得安东尼恩宠就高兴得发抖{\r}\N...who have quivered happily at being summoned by Lord Antony.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:13.60,2:08:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我并不是说召见{\r}\NBut surely I didn't say "summoned."
Dialogue: 0,2:08:15.93,2:08:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你说邀请他的意思就是召见{\r}\NYou said "invite." He meant "summon."
Dialogue: 0,2:08:19.40,2:08:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}再说，我也是埃及女王{\r}\NIn any case, I am the queen of Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:22.82,2:08:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我想留在埃及国土内{\r}\NAnd I choose to remain on Egyptian soil.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:26.24,2:08:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}塔瑟斯并不远，陛下{\r}\NTarsus is not the other end of the world, Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:29.86,2:08:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}离开埃及一步就算远了{\r}\NIf it were one step from Egypt, that would be too far.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:34.54,2:08:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我只会在埃及{\r}\NI will meet with Lord Antony...
Dialogue: 0,2:08:39.17,2:08:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}见安东尼阁下{\r}\N...but only on Egyptian soil.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:42.79,2:08:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}总要找个两全其美的地方{\r}\NMy lady, a way must be found, a time, a place to satisfy you both.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:47.55,2:08:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一定要这样吗，鲁非欧？{\r}\NMust it, Rufio?
Dialogue: 0,2:10:05.67,2:10:07.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉？{\r}\NCleopatra.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:31.53,2:10:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉！{\r}\NCleopatra!
Dialogue: 0,2:10:38.20,2:10:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是的{\r}\NIt is.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:40.16,2:10:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一定是！{\r}\NIt must be.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:59.56,2:11:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她说除非在埃及，否则绝不{\r}\NShe said never, except on Egyptian soil.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:02.10,2:11:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当女人说绝不时…{\r}\N"Never." Something women say to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:04.85,2:11:07.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}代我迎接克莉奥佩特拉！{\r}\NWelcome Queen Cleopatra on my behalf.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:07.19,2:11:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在这种状况之下… 宫里今晚加办舞会来欢迎她{\r}\NExtend my invitation to a banquet in her honor.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:10.61,2:11:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 你不认为可能… - 你还不信啊，鲁非欧？{\r}\N-Don't you think--? -Still not convinced Rufio?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:13.53,2:11:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}快点，很多事要忙叫厨师来见我{\r}\NHurry back, there's much to be done. Have the cooks sent to me.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:53.98,2:11:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}对不起，鲁非欧，你搞错了{\r}\NForgive me, noble Rufio. It is you who do not understand.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:57.78,2:12:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}女王在船舱里就仍算是在埃及领土{\r}\NQueen Cleopatra, at present in her chamber, is on Egyptian territory...
Dialogue: 0,2:12:02.62,2:12:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她不打算落船{\r}\N...and intends to remain on it.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:04.58,2:12:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}容我提醒你{\r}\NMost learned Sosigenes, forgive me...
Dialogue: 0,2:12:07.41,2:12:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这里是塔瑟斯 不是亚历山卓{\r}\N...but this is Tarsus, not Alexandria.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:09.79,2:12:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你是在塔瑟斯，而我在埃及{\r}\NYou are on Tarsus, noble Rufio. I am on Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:13.88,2:12:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}今明两晚，安东尼若想见陛下{\r}\NTonight and tomorrow night, if Lord Antony desires to meet Her Majesty...
Dialogue: 0,2:12:18.51,2:12:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}欢迎他莅临埃及{\r}\N...he will come to her, to Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:23.51,2:12:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我会设法说服安东尼前来{\r}\NI shall do my best, learned friend, to prevail upon Lord Antony to attend.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:23.43,2:14:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}马克安东尼，你动作真快{\r}\NMarc Antony, how prompt you are.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:26.43,2:14:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不快就不可原谅了{\r}\NIf I had not been, it would be unforgivable of me.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:29.43,2:14:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我一直在这里等你登船{\r}\NI had hoped to be here to welcome you as you came aboard.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:32.73,2:14:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这件事一样不可原谅{\r}\NIf you had been, it would be unforgivable of me.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:35.65,2:14:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}别太严肃，偶然放纵一下自己{\r}\NBe more tolerant. Forgive yourself now and then.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:41.57,2:14:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}三年了，你怎么会愈来愈美艳？{\r}\NAlmost three years. Have you possibly become more beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:45.41,2:14:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}三年了吗？{\r}\NAlmost three? That long?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:48.28,2:14:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}时间过得真快{\r}\NThe time has passed so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:50.41,2:14:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的项链上，好像是金币{\r}\NYour necklace. It seems to be made of gold coins.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:54.58,2:14:57.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒的金币{\r}\NCoins of Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:57.42,2:15:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 好看吗？ - 很好看{\r}\N-Do you find it attractive? -Very.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:00.25,2:15:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你穿着得像个…{\r}\NAnd I find what you're wearing most becoming.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:03.67,2:15:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}希腊人{\r}\NGreek, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:05.09,2:15:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我喜欢希腊的东西{\r}\NI have a fondness for almost all Greek things.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:07.97,2:15:12.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我有希腊血统，多谢你的奉承{\r}\NAs an almost all-Greek thing, I'm flattered.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:16.77,2:15:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罕见的项链{\r}\NAn unusual necklace.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:19.11,2:15:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}全由凯撒金币造咸{\r}\NNothing but gold coins of Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:21.65,2:15:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 哪儿买的？ - 我订造的{\r}\N-How did you come by it? -I had it made.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:24.57,2:15:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一直戴在身上{\r}\NI wear it always.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:26.76,2:16:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}令人赞叹的宴会{\r}\NA fabulous feast.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:29.34,2:16:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}搭船航行总是会觉得不自在{\r}\NOne is so limited when one travels by ship.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:32.85,2:16:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}华丽的船{\r}\NThis fabulous ship...
Dialogue: 0,2:16:34.85,2:16:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}加上艳丽的女王{\r}\N...together with its queen, the fabulous Cleopatra.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:39.65,2:16:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}马克安东尼绝非寂寂无名之人{\r}\NThe name of Marc Antony is not exactly unknown to the world.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:44.02,2:16:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 为何一两年前相会以来… - 快三年了{\r}\N-In the last year or so since we met-- -Almost three.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:48.24,2:16:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如今是三分之一个罗马巨头{\r}\NBy now you have become one-third the master of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:53.03,2:16:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你就是不许自己忘了他吗？{\r}\NYou don't permit yourself to forget him, is that it?
Dialogue: 0,2:16:56.37,2:16:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不许自己，这话真奇怪{\r}\NThat's an odd way of putting it. "Don't permit myself"?
Dialogue: 0,2:16:59.92,2:17:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}非把他戴在颈上不可吗？{\r}\NIs it necessary to wear him around your neck?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:03.46,2:17:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你忘了三年来{\r}\NYou forget, Antony, in these almost three years...
Dialogue: 0,2:17:07.17,2:17:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的日子多充实{\r}\N...how full your own life has been.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:09.93,2:17:13.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}独力统治，你也不可能闲着{\r}\NThey can't have been uneventful for you. You rule Egypt alone.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:14.10,2:17:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}很忙，但不充实{\r}\NOh, they have been busy, but not full.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:17.06,2:17:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}两者并不一样{\r}\NThere's a difference.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:18.73,2:17:22.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}白天时间永远都不够…{\r}\NThere cannot be enough hours in the days of a queen...
Dialogue: 0,2:17:22.60,2:17:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}晚上却是长夜漫漫{\r}\N...and her nights have too many.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:25.19,2:17:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 只好靠回忆来填满 - 回忆凯撒？{\r}\N-So I fill them with memories. -Of Caesar?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:28.49,2:17:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他，以及他…{\r}\NAnd of a dream...
Dialogue: 0,2:17:30.61,2:17:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}几乎实现的梦想{\r}\N...that almost came true.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:32.57,2:17:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你可能记得…{\r}\NYou may remember.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:34.20,2:17:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我记得那天晚上在罗马似乎仍能实现{\r}\NI remember that night in Rome, saying it could still come true.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:38.83,2:17:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那晚你跟许多人说了许多话{\r}\NYou said so much that night to so many.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:58.72,2:18:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我已将他们打发走了{\r}\NLet me get rid of them all.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:00.43,2:18:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为什么？我事先安排了希腊舞{\r}\NWhy? I have arranged an entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:03.31,2:18:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}以便欢迎希腊酒神{\r}\NA dance in the Greek fashion to welcome the god Bacchus.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:07.61,2:18:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若我走，他们全都会离席{\r}\NIf I make a great show of going, they'll have to leave too.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:11.24,2:18:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我再回来{\r}\NThen I can return...
Dialogue: 0,2:18:13.95,2:18:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们可以… 私下谈谈，只有你和我{\r}\N...and we can talk alone, you and I.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:17.62,2:18:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 你何时回来？ - 一小时，最多两小时{\r}\N-When would you return? -In an hour, no more than two.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:22.00,2:18:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 你会留多久？ - 直到无话可谈为止{\r}\N-How long would you stay? -Until we had nothing more to say.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:27.50,2:18:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你是游泳健将吗？我们黎明起航{\r}\NAre you a strong swimmer? We sail at sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:33.55,2:18:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不懂{\r}\NI don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:35.64,2:18:39.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}回亚历山卓，回埃及{\r}\NHome to Alexandria, to Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:39.68,2:18:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你老远跑来停留一晚 只为嘲弄我！{\r}\NYou've come all this way for one night. All to make a fool of me.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:44.81,2:18:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}留下来过夜{\r}\NPerhaps you would feel less a fool...
Dialogue: 0,2:18:47.15,2:18:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}可会不那么像被嘲弄？{\r}\N...if you stayed the night with me, is that it?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:52.57,2:18:54.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我说过{\r}\NI've told you before.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:54.99,2:18:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在你面前我变得 难以用说话表达自己{\r}\NWith you, words do not come easily to me.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:58.37,2:19:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我心里很多话说不出来{\r}\NThere is too much unsaid within me that I cannot say.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:01.20,2:19:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你不说我怎知道{\r}\NThen I cannot know it.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:03.16,2:19:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你也有很多说不出的话吧{\r}\NThere is much unsaid within you too.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:05.37,2:19:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}可能每个人都一样{\r}\NThat is probably true of everybody.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:08.34,2:19:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}留一会儿吧{\r}\NStay for a while.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:10.67,2:19:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}相识虽久，相知不多，给我时间{\r}\NI have known you so long but so little. Give me time.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:15.43,2:19:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不能，罗马和埃及加起来…{\r}\NNot I. Not Egypt and Rome together.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:18.51,2:19:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}即使神也无法给你时间{\r}\NNot even the gods have time to give you.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:23.35,2:19:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但是，安东尼，你应把握时势{\r}\NBut, Antony, use what you have.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:26.06,2:19:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不要在塔瑟斯陪诸神游戏{\r}\NDon't waste it by playing at god here in Tarsus...
Dialogue: 0,2:19:31.11,2:19:35.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}而屋大维在罗马快变成神了{\r}\N...while Octavian in Rome becomes a god.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:55.31,2:22:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}舞会应该结束了吧{\r}\NThe dance, I take it, is over.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:58.40,2:22:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}起来{\r}\NSit up.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:00.23,2:23:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我看你是不是戴着回忆入睡{\r}\NI want to see whether you sleep with your memories.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:09.24,2:23:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}心中有话说不出口…{\r}\NWith so much left unsaid within you...
Dialogue: 0,2:23:12.45,2:23:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}活动手脚有助纾缓压力{\r}\N...it must be a relief to break and tear things.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:16.12,2:23:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 我现在有话要说 - 改天吧{\r}\N-I want to say something now. -Perhaps some other time.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:20.05,2:23:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在！{\r}\NNow!
Dialogue: 0,2:23:23.92,2:23:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯萨{\r}\NCaesar.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:27.76,2:23:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}征伐再征伐…{\r}\NConquer and conquer.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:30.43,2:23:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}世界都臣服于脚下{\r}\NBring the world to its knees.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:33.27,2:23:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}却仍不是凯撒，你明白吗？{\r}\N"You're not a Caesar. Did you know that?"
Dialogue: 0,2:23:37.85,2:23:39.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}勇冠三军…{\r}\NBe braver than the bravest...
Dialogue: 0,2:23:39.69,2:23:42.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}智慧过人，却仍不是凯撒{\r}\N...stronger than the strongest. Still no Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:43.15,2:23:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不管怎努力，凯撒都早你一步{\r}\NCaesar's done it first and better. Ruled better, loved better, fought better.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:47.45,2:23:50.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不管统治、德政、战略他都优胜于你{\r}\NRun where you will, you can't get out. There's no way out.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:50.99,2:23:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不管走到哪里，都无路可逃 永远笼罩在凯撒的阴影下！{\r}\NThe shadow of Caesar will cover you and cover the universe for all of time.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:00.29,2:24:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你在罗马时说{\r}\N"Whenever you like," you said in Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:02.67,2:24:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}随时欢迎到亚历山卓来{\r}\N"Come to Alexandria whenever you like."
Dialogue: 0,2:24:05.22,2:24:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我说就是今晚{\r}\N"Now, tonight," I said.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:07.09,2:24:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}向凯撒为你安排的王位致敬{\r}\NTo bow to the throne upon which Caesar put you.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:10.35,2:24:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谈论新战术 那是凯撒无法超越还抄袭的{\r}\NTo talk of a new treaty. Caesar's can't be improved. Copy it.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:14.02,2:24:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谈凯撒之子 谈至今犹在，你们共同的梦想{\r}\NOf Caesar's son. Of the dream you shared with Caesar that still fills your life.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:18.48,2:24:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亚历山卓是你们 向世界发号施令的地方{\r}\NAlexander's design for a world to be ruled by you and Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:24.32,2:24:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}马克安东尼何在？{\r}\NWhere is Antony?
Dialogue: 0,2:24:26.11,2:24:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}马克安东尼何在？{\r}\NWhere is Marc Antony?
Dialogue: 0,2:24:28.15,2:24:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}伟大的安东尼！神圣的安东尼！{\r}\NAntony the Great! The divine Antony!
Dialogue: 0,2:24:31.70,2:24:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他在此{\r}\NHere.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:33.62,2:24:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他{\r}\NHe's...
Dialogue: 0,2:24:35.66,2:24:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在此{\r}\N...here.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:37.62,2:24:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}迟凯撒一步… 就在凯撒的右手…{\r}\NOne step behind Caesar. At the right hand of Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:41.63,2:24:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在凯撒的阴影里{\r}\NIn the shadow of Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:45.67,2:24:48.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在他之后，有多少人爱过你？{\r}\NTell me, how many have loved you since him?
Dialogue: 0,2:24:49.01,2:24:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一个？十个？所有人？ 还是一个都没有？{\r}\NOne? Ten? Anyone? No one?
Dialogue: 0,2:24:52.18,2:24:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们吻你时是凯撒的唇碰你吗？ 黑暗中你呼唤的是他的名字？{\r}\NHave they kissed you with Caesar's lips? Is it his name you cry out in the dark?
Dialogue: 0,2:24:56.52,2:25:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}之后…他是否回来找你？ 你是否向回忆请求原谅？{\r}\NAfterwards, has he reproached you and have you begged forgiveness?
Dialogue: 0,2:25:01.52,2:25:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}借酒壮胆，自怜自艾{\r}\NYou've come here, then, running over with wine and self-pity...
Dialogue: 0,2:25:05.86,2:25:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这算是征服凯撒？{\r}\N...to conquer Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:08.07,2:25:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}长久以来，我生命中充满了你{\r}\NFor so long now, you've filled my life...
Dialogue: 0,2:25:12.95,2:25:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}像心中随时听见的噪音{\r}\N...like a great noise I hear everywhere in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:18.54,2:25:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我要摆脱你，不想你…{\r}\NI want to be free of you, of wanting you...
Dialogue: 0,2:25:22.21,2:25:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不想再担惊受怕{\r}\N...of being afraid.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:26.25,2:25:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}恐怕凯撒不会答应{\r}\NYet, Caesar would not permit it.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:50.45,2:25:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但我永远{\r}\NBut I will never...
Dialogue: 0,2:25:53.41,2:25:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}忘不了你{\r}\N...be free of you.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:11.13,2:26:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当你乘坐大石兽{\r}\NFrom the first instant I saw you...
Dialogue: 0,2:26:13.51,2:26:16.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}抵达罗马时…{\r}\N...entering Rome on that monstrous stone beast...
Dialogue: 0,2:26:16.97,2:26:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}石兽在太阳下闪耀{\r}\N...shining in the sun...
Dialogue: 0,2:26:19.72,2:26:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}像金色的小玩具{\r}\N...like a little gold toy.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:22.81,2:26:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我很忌妒凯撒{\r}\N...how I envied Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:24.98,2:26:26.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我突然生病了{\r}\NWent suddenly sick with it.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:27.11,2:26:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不是他的战功，不是他的头衔{\r}\NNot his conquests or his triumphs.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:29.36,2:26:31.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不是群众的欢呼…{\r}\NNot his titles or the roaring of the mob.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:32.65,2:26:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}而是因为你而妒忌他{\r}\NI envied him you.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:38.03,2:26:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}第一次在罗马见到你我就记得你{\r}\NWhen we first met in Rome, I remembered you.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:41.75,2:26:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}并觉得永世难忘{\r}\NI wondered that I could ever have forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:44.62,2:26:46.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}难忘我？{\r}\NRemembered me?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:46.75,2:26:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}多年前，你还是个骑兵军宫的时候{\r}\NYears ago, when you were a young cavalry officer...
Dialogue: 0,2:26:49.67,2:26:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}驻守在亚历山卓宫殿旁{\r}\N...stationed at the palace in Alexandria under that fat Roman general.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:53.80,2:26:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}指挥官是个胖将军他叫什么名字？{\r}\N-What was his name? -Gabinius.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:56.64,2:26:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}加比尼尔斯{\r}\NGabinius.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:59.51,2:27:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我当时十二岁，已经爱上你{\r}\NI was 12 years old, and I loved you.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:03.64,2:27:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 胡说 - 真的{\r}\N-Nonsense. -It's true.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:06.19,2:27:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}相恋之人总希望未曾爱过{\r}\NLovers always want so much never to have loved before.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:11.48,2:27:12.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}很可能如此{\r}\NIt's possible, you know.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:13.07,2:27:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}揣测谁先爱谁，便成了游戏{\r}\NIt becomes a game. Who loved whom first?
Dialogue: 0,2:27:15.91,2:27:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我就猜过{\r}\NI did.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:18.83,2:27:23.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当初若见过我，你一定很怕我{\r}\NIf you noticed me at all then, you were probably terrified of me.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:23.83,2:27:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是啊，大家说罗马人会杀小孩{\r}\NWith good reason. Everybody knows Romans cut up little children...
Dialogue: 0,2:27:27.71,2:27:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}并拿来喂马{\r}\N...and feed them to their horses.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:34.84,2:27:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们把这次当是一个开始{\r}\NWe'll make this our beginning.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:37.84,2:27:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}从今夜起{\r}\NBeginning with tonight...
Dialogue: 0,2:27:40.01,2:27:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你不能再忌妒凯撒{\r}\N...you must never envy Caesar...
Dialogue: 0,2:27:42.81,2:27:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}或任何人，任何事{\r}\N...or anyone, anything again.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:55.70,2:27:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}毕竟{\r}\NAfter all...
Dialogue: 0,2:27:57.86,2:28:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这不是新闻{\r}\N...this is nothing new.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:00.37,2:28:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}多年以来…{\r}\NFor so many years...
Dialogue: 0,2:28:02.41,2:28:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼一直是{\r}\N...Antony has fed upon the crumbs...
Dialogue: 0,2:28:04.70,2:28:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}朱利斯凯撒的爪牙{\r}\N...that fell from Julius Caesar's table.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:09.58,2:28:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我认为…{\r}\NI say...
Dialogue: 0,2:28:11.71,2:28:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}干柴烈火{\r}\N...they are deserving of each other.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:14.46,2:28:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就让他们留在埃及…{\r}\NLet him stay in Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:16.63,2:28:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}虚耗生命好了{\r}\NLet him fritter away his life as he chooses...
Dialogue: 0,2:28:18.89,2:28:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但罗马人的财产和政府却不能虚耗{\r}\N...but not the possessions and the empire of the Roman people!
Dialogue: 0,2:28:22.85,2:28:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马人！{\r}\NThe Roman people!
Dialogue: 0,2:28:25.73,2:28:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}什么是罗马人的荣耀与财产？{\r}\NThe Roman people. What are glory and possessions to them?
Dialogue: 0,2:28:29.48,2:28:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只要安东尼高兴{\r}\NIs their Antony content?
Dialogue: 0,2:28:32.73,2:28:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们就高兴{\r}\NThen so are they.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:36.57,2:28:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼有没有将帝国{\r}\NDoes their Antony sweep their empire...
Dialogue: 0,2:28:39.74,2:28:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}置于克莉奥佩特拉床下？{\r}\N...under Cleopatra's bed?
Dialogue: 0,2:28:42.95,2:28:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}爱戴他的罗马人只会叹口气 还是随他高兴！{\r}\NHis adoring Romans sigh and remain content.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:48.62,2:28:52.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}无论距离多远{\r}\NLet him stay however distant for however long...
Dialogue: 0,2:28:52.29,2:28:54.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}多久没有想起他们…{\r}\N...with never a thought of them.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:54.63,2:28:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马人还是敬爱他{\r}\NThe Roman people hold him close to their hearts.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:57.92,2:28:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}远？{\r}\NDistant?
Dialogue: 0,2:29:00.01,2:29:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}或许离罗马很远{\r}\NPerhaps from Rome but not from Caesar, I think.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:03.18,2:29:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但离凯撒及凯撒之子不远{\r}\NNor from Caesar's son.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:04.81,2:29:07.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}朱曼尼卡斯，你说我吗？{\r}\NGermanicus, do you speak of me?
Dialogue: 0,2:29:07.81,2:29:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不，屋大维，我说凯撒{\r}\NNo, Octavian, I speak of Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:10.65,2:29:12.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我也是凯撒{\r}\NI am Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:13.44,2:29:15.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只有当安东尼{\r}\NOnly while Antony remains...
Dialogue: 0,2:29:15.90,2:29:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}远离罗马时{\r}\N...distant from Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:20.70,2:29:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼{\r}\NAntony!
Dialogue: 0,2:29:22.70,2:29:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不会在亚历山卓逗留太久{\r}\NStay not too long in Alexandria!
Dialogue: 0,2:29:28.96,2:29:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}朱曼尼卡斯{\r}\NGermanicus...
Dialogue: 0,2:29:31.50,2:29:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不会在罗马逗留太久{\r}\N...stay not too long in Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:55.48,2:29:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 此事安东尼知道多少？ - 都知道，或许更多{\r}\N-How much of this is known to Antony? -All of it and more.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:58.99,2:30:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我定期以书面通知他状况{\r}\NI've written him regularly. Letters, dispatches by personal messenger.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:03.57,2:30:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他怎回答？{\r}\NAnd what has he answered?
Dialogue: 0,2:30:05.83,2:30:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他回答说他对政治不再有兴趣{\r}\NHe wrote he was no longer interested in the matters I described.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:09.75,2:30:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他也不想回罗马{\r}\NThat he would not return to Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:12.00,2:30:16.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他对可能的损失相当清楚{\r}\NThat he understood quite clearly what was at stake, what he would lose.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:16.25,2:30:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但他不愿意离开你{\r}\NBut that he would not leave you.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:38.48,2:30:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}啊，对了，试试山羊的{\r}\NLet's try the goat.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:44.86,2:30:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}好啦，再试一次山羊的 这边，不要太多{\r}\NLet's have that goat again. There. Not too much.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:48.70,2:30:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这边{\r}\NThere.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:51.75,2:30:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}牛奶{\r}\NThe milk of a cow...
Dialogue: 0,2:30:54.37,2:30:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}羊奶、驴奶哪一种最能软化胡须？{\r}\N...of a goat and of an ass. Which is best for softening the beard?
Dialogue: 0,2:30:59.00,2:31:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维一星期才刮一次胡子 是真的吗？{\r}\NIs it true Octavian shaves but once a week?
Dialogue: 0,2:31:03.13,2:31:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}即使如此一阵风就吹光他的汗毛{\r}\NEven then, he has merely to face the wind and let the fuzz blow away.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:07.14,2:31:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你知道朱曼尼卡斯从罗马来了吗？{\r}\NYou knew, didn't you, Germanicus was here from Rome?
Dialogue: 0,2:31:10.89,2:31:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}知道{\r}\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:12.64,2:31:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你喜欢胡须吗？ 我年轻时留过胡子，亮红色的{\r}\NHave you strong feelings about beards? I had one. Bright red.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:16.60,2:31:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你为何不见他？{\r}\NWhy haven't you seen him?
Dialogue: 0,2:31:26.03,2:31:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你一去…{\r}\NWhen you go...
Dialogue: 0,2:31:28.95,2:31:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}要很久吗？{\r}\N...must it be for very long?
Dialogue: 0,2:31:31.45,2:31:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我要带些海绵回去{\r}\NI must take some of these with me. They don't have them.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:34.83,2:31:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}以前我在罗马时{\r}\NAt least, they didn't when I was last...
Dialogue: 0,2:31:37.58,2:31:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没这东西{\r}\N...in Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:47.09,2:31:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们为我挖陵寝时…{\r}\NWhile they were digging the foundation of my tomb...
Dialogue: 0,2:31:51.10,2:31:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}找到一面古墙{\r}\N...the workers found an old wall.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:53.98,2:31:58.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有些有几百年的文字：{\r}\NSomeone had scratched on it hundreds of years ago:
Dialogue: 0,2:31:58.94,2:32:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你昨晚没来，我无法入睡{\r}\N"You were not here last night, and I could not sleep.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:03.61,2:32:06.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}今晚你会来吗？{\r}\NWill you be here tonight?"
Dialogue: 0,2:32:07.95,2:32:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你想他们有否再见面？{\r}\NDo you suppose they ever met again?
Dialogue: 0,2:32:12.66,2:32:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}目前我想捉住的、看到的… 拥有的、为之存在的…{\r}\NEverything that I shall ever want to hold or look upon or have or be...
Dialogue: 0,2:32:16.79,2:32:19.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只有与你同在这里{\r}\N...is here now with you.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:20.13,2:32:22.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我也不想对不起自己{\r}\NI must not be sorry for myself.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:22.80,2:32:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}对此事，女王并不比 国王或王子占优势{\r}\NQueens are sometimes no better at that than kings, or even princes.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:29.84,2:32:32.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不公平{\r}\NIt doesn't seem fair.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:33.35,2:32:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在的感觉我早在{\r}\NWhat I feel I should have felt long ago when I was very young.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:38.69,2:32:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}年轻时感受过{\r}\NWhen I could say to myself that this was how love was...
Dialogue: 0,2:32:42.36,2:32:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当时我想爱就该是这样{\r}\N...and how it would be.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:44.82,2:32:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但在长久的等待后忽然觉悟{\r}\NBut to have waited so long, to know so suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,2:32:49.99,2:32:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在这么久以后…{\r}\N...this late...
Dialogue: 0,2:32:51.99,2:32:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}爱会伤人，锥心之痛{\r}\N...how it hurts. How love can stab the heart.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:05.84,2:33:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}小心屋大维{\r}\NBe careful with Octavian.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:09.13,2:33:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他该小心我{\r}\NLet him be careful with me.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:11.39,2:33:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马不希望你俩开战{\r}\NThe Romans want no war between the two of you.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:14.76,2:33:17.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}再说，你还未准备好{\r}\NIn any case, you are not ready yet.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:17.64,2:33:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}世界充满爱，不会再有战争{\r}\NWar? The world is filled with love. There'll be no more wars.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:21.35,2:33:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你该得到你应得的{\r}\NYou must have your share.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:23.65,2:33:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}头衔、权利应该确立清楚{\r}\NYour titles and powers must be spelled out exactly.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:27.65,2:33:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在东方你该有绝对的权威{\r}\NThere can be no question of your complete authority in the East.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:34.16,2:33:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼，我日子该怎么过？{\r}\NAntony, how will I live?
Dialogue: 0,2:33:37.25,2:33:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}跟我一样过{\r}\NThe same as I.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:40.21,2:33:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}彼此每交换一个气息…{\r}\NOne breath upon the other.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:42.79,2:33:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们的距离{\r}\NEach bringing us...
Dialogue: 0,2:33:44.79,2:33:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}每拉近了一点{\r}\N...one breath closer.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:48.38,2:33:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你一离开，我就魂不守舍{\r}\NYou take so much of me with you so far.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:52.55,2:33:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}记住记住，他们要你忘记我{\r}\NRemember, remember. They'll want you to forget.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:55.56,2:33:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}怎么忘记？{\r}\N-Please-- -Forget? How?
Dialogue: 0,2:34:00.06,2:34:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我一步…{\r}\NI can never be more far away from you...
Dialogue: 0,2:34:04.06,2:34:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}都不离开{\r}\N...than this.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:17.24,2:34:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他会先到布林迪森{\r}\NHe will come first to Brindisium.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:19.41,2:34:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亚格里巴和我计划盛大迎接他{\r}\NAgrippa and I plan to welcome his arrival with a great ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:24.58,2:34:29.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼该知道罗马人…{\r}\NAntony must see how dear to the hearts of the Romans, of us all...
Dialogue: 0,2:34:29.26,2:34:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}包括我们，是多么敬爱他{\r}\N...he is and has been.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:31.26,2:34:34.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他离开了一段很长的时间{\r}\NHe has been away for a very long time.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:34.93,2:34:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}或许可以劝他多留一会{\r}\NPerhaps we can persuade him to stay with us even longer.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:38.97,2:34:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有可能，屋大维雅 如果你来布林迪森会有帮助{\r}\NPerhaps, Octavia, if you came to Brindisium, you could help.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:43.60,2:34:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你可能忘记了 还未到六个月…{\r}\NYou may have forgotten. It is only six months since--
Dialogue: 0,2:34:46.98,2:34:50.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}请亚格里巴和祖先饶恕你{\r}\NBegging the pardon of Agrippa and our ancestors...
Dialogue: 0,2:34:50.28,2:34:53.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不同意年轻寡妇该放弃生活{\r}\N...I do not agree that a young widow must retire from life.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:54.11,2:34:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}丈夫过世后，你从未离开过我家{\r}\NYou haven't left my house since your husband died.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:57.62,2:35:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若只是为着健康，这改变就…{\r}\NIf only for the sake of your health, the change alone....
Dialogue: 0,2:35:04.67,2:35:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那么，请亚里格巴和祖先饶恕{\r}\NThen, begging the pardon of Lord Agrippa and our ancestors...
Dialogue: 0,2:35:08.96,2:35:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我期待这个改变{\r}\N...I would look forward very much to the change.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:14.55,2:35:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没人像她那样明艳动人{\r}\NNothing, no one, could possibly shine more brightly in the sun.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:19.26,2:35:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不只安东尼{\r}\NNot only Antony.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:21.06,2:35:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}每个人都想染指屋大维雅{\r}\NI know of no man who would not hold out his greedy fists for Octavia.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:24.85,2:35:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这个人质足够{\r}\NAfter all, what greater pledge could I offer...
Dialogue: 0,2:35:28.31,2:35:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}表达诚意了吧？{\r}\N...of my goodwill toward him?
Dialogue: 0,2:35:30.78,2:35:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为了和平他不得{\r}\NAnd how could Antony better show his love of peace and Rome...
Dialogue: 0,2:35:34.57,2:35:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不接受{\r}\N...than by accepting?
Dialogue: 0,2:35:36.32,2:35:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉呢？{\r}\NAnd Cleopatra?
Dialogue: 0,2:35:39.53,2:35:42.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你建议请她参加婚礼？{\r}\NAre you suggesting we invite her to the wedding?
Dialogue: 0,2:35:43.04,2:35:45.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}记得她在罗马时{\r}\NYou remember when Julius Caesar returned...
Dialogue: 0,2:35:45.83,2:35:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}朱利斯凯撒的下场吗？{\r}\N...and those months while she was in Rome?
Dialogue: 0,2:35:48.50,2:35:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他的心中、脑里都有毒{\r}\NThere was a poison in his heart, in his brain.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:51.80,2:35:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我知道他有癫痫症{\r}\NYes, the falling sickness. But more than that.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:55.38,2:35:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 但克莉奥佩特拉是主因 - 我记得很清楚{\r}\N-Cleopatra. -I remember well.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:58.43,2:36:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 安东尼不是凯撒 - 这点我很感激{\r}\N-Antony is no Caesar. -I am grateful for that.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:03.02,2:36:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就算他与屋大维雅成婚 他会忘了克莉奥佩特拉吗？{\r}\NGranted that he marries Octavia, will he forget Cleopatra?
Dialogue: 0,2:36:07.35,2:36:11.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 她又会允许他忘记吗？ - 不大可能会{\r}\N-Will she permit him to forget? -Most probably not.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:57.78,2:37:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 我能说话吗？ - 快告诉我{\r}\N-Have I permission to speak? -Tell me, quickly.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:01.20,2:37:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}布林迪森传来的罗马消息{\r}\NA galley came to Pelusium with news from Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:04.16,2:37:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼与屋大维达成重大协议{\r}\NAntony and Octavian have sealed a great pact.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:07.25,2:37:10.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼多掌握十队军队和整个东方{\r}\NAntony has 10 more legions and all of the East for his domain.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:11.04,2:37:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将宣布罗马与埃及结盟{\r}\NEgypt will be declared ally of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:13.29,2:37:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}成功了！{\r}\NIt is done.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:16.88,2:37:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 还有其他消息… - 不，没有了，阁下{\r}\N-There is more. -No. No more, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:20.13,2:37:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 他害怕 - 还有其他消息吗？{\r}\N-He's afraid. -Is there anything more?
Dialogue: 0,2:37:24.51,2:37:28.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}陛下请恕罪，有一场婚事{\r}\NForgive me, Divine Majesty. There has been a marriage.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:29.35,2:37:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一场政治婚姻{\r}\NA marriage of state.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:32.23,2:37:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维凯撒之妹{\r}\NBetween Octavia, the sister of Caesar...
Dialogue: 0,2:37:36.23,2:37:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维雅与安东尼结婚{\r}\N...and Lord Antony.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:42.99,2:37:44.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还有其他事吗？{\r}\NAnything more?
Dialogue: 0,2:37:45.41,2:37:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们目前在雅典{\r}\NThey're presently in Athens.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:47.08,2:37:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一年内，屋大维雅会回罗马{\r}\NSometime within the year, Lady Octavia is to return to Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:51.00,2:37:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼会来签署结盟条约{\r}\NAntony will come Alexandria to negotiate the alliance of Rome and Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:10.18,2:38:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}退下{\r}\NLeave me.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:15.44,2:38:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不{\r}\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:18.94,2:38:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}全部退下{\r}\NCompletely alone.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:55.23,2:38:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼！{\r}\NAntony!
Dialogue: 0,2:41:36.68,2:41:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你喜欢这个水钟吗？{\r}\NDo you find it pleasing, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,2:41:41.31,2:41:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是的，非常喜欢{\r}\NOh, yes. Very.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:43.19,2:41:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}雅典制造的{\r}\NIt was made here in Athens.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:45.48,2:41:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没有罗马的实用{\r}\NNot as practical as our Roman ones, of course.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:48.86,2:41:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凡事求美是希腊人要命的缺点{\r}\NThe Greeks have such a weakness for beauty.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:04.79,2:42:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}晚餐不合你心意吗？{\r}\NDoes the dinner not please you, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,2:42:07.84,2:42:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不是，只是我不饿{\r}\NVery much. I'm not particularly hungry.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:10.42,2:42:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}什么事能让你较开心呢？{\r}\NIf anything would please you more--
Dialogue: 0,2:42:13.55,2:42:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我已经很开心了，屋大维雅{\r}\NBelieve me, I am pleased.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:17.68,2:42:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你已经尽力{\r}\NThe gods know you do nothing but please me...
Dialogue: 0,2:42:21.52,2:42:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}讨我欢心{\r}\N...in every way.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:30.24,2:42:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}多米提斯有消息吗？{\r}\NWord from Domitius?
Dialogue: 0,2:42:32.15,2:42:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他被挡在城门外{\r}\NHe never even reached the palace.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:34.32,2:42:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不能进入皇宫{\r}\NHe was not permitted through the city gate.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:42.08,2:42:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}恕我失陪{\r}\NIf I may be excused.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:45.21,2:42:46.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你不必回避{\r}\NThere's no need for you to go.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:47.21,2:42:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}每次听到男人讨论国事{\r}\NWhen I hear matters of state discussed by men...
Dialogue: 0,2:42:50.51,2:42:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}总是担心着{\r}\N...invariably I find myself wondering about...
Dialogue: 0,2:42:53.34,2:42:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}酒怎么会变酸{\r}\N...why the wine has gone sour.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:56.18,2:42:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}晚安，鲁非欧{\r}\NGood night, Rufio.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:58.72,2:43:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}晚安，阁下{\r}\NGood night, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:08.82,2:43:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}多米提斯被拒于城外{\r}\NDomitius turned away at the gate.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:11.74,2:43:13.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}第几个了？{\r}\NThat makes how many?
Dialogue: 0,2:43:14.15,2:43:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}今年第五个使者被拒{\r}\NFive of your ambassadors turned away within this year.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:17.87,2:43:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若你照我的意思前往…{\r}\N-If you'd gone when-- -It was the only favor I ever asked of you.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:21.91,2:43:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你答应过我的请求{\r}\NYou granted it.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:24.12,2:43:28.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}与埃及的协约要尽快签订 很久没有黄金和粮食运来了{\r}\NThe treaty with Egypt must be made. We've received no wheat, no gold--
Dialogue: 0,2:43:28.29,2:43:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不能前去与她谈判{\r}\NI cannot go to her to negotiate a treaty!
Dialogue: 0,2:43:31.30,2:43:33.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她只肯跟你谈{\r}\NShe'll have no one else.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:34.38,2:43:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若连我{\r}\NAnd what if she should...
Dialogue: 0,2:43:36.55,2:43:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}也被拒呢？{\r}\N...turn me away?
Dialogue: 0,2:43:39.68,2:43:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不可能吧{\r}\NThat would be quite impossible.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:45.35,2:43:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你对她真的没有感情了吗？{\r}\NHave you ever really left her?
Dialogue: 0,2:43:49.82,2:43:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不{\r}\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:06.29,2:44:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我已经等了三天 要跟你单独谈谈{\r}\NThree days I've waited for an audience with you alone.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:09.46,2:44:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谈什么？{\r}\NWhat is the purpose?
Dialogue: 0,2:44:11.21,2:44:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}全部出去，我要跟殿下私下谈{\r}\NGet out, all of you. I'll see her privately.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:13.55,2:44:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 你站的地方是埃及圣殿 - 我知道这是哪儿！{\r}\N-You're before the throne of Egypt. -I know where I am!
Dialogue: 0,2:44:16.43,2:44:17.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那么请说出你的目的{\r}\NState your purpose!
Dialogue: 0,2:44:18.09,2:44:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不想公开讨论{\r}\NMatters I won't discuss publicly.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:20.47,2:44:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不与不明人士私下谈判{\r}\NI do not grant private audiences to unidentified persons.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:26.52,2:44:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我是马克安东尼{\r}\NI am Marcus Antonius.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:29.35,2:44:33.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我知道你是谁 但你现在的身分是什么？{\r}\NI know who you are. What are you, at the moment?
Dialogue: 0,2:44:33.53,2:44:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马帝国统治者之一兼大使 主掌意大利以东的领土{\r}\NEnvoy of Rome, proconsul of all the Roman Empire to the east of Italy.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:38.61,2:44:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}好吓人的头衔{\r}\NAn impressive title.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:40.49,2:44:42.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}值得私下会谈了吗？{\r}\NWorthy, perhaps, of a private audience?
Dialogue: 0,2:44:43.08,2:44:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但若不与埃及签订条约{\r}\NWithout a treaty of alliance with Egypt...
Dialogue: 0,2:44:45.62,2:44:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你无法统治你的领土吧？{\r}\N...you could not hold the territories under your command. True?
Dialogue: 0,2:44:50.92,2:44:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}可能{\r}\NPossibly.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:52.42,2:44:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那么你是来求我的{\r}\NThen, Lord Antony, you come before me as a suppliant.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:56.09,2:44:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你要是这么想，我也没办法{\r}\N-If you choose to regard me as such. -I do.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:59.84,2:45:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}哀求者该有哀求者的姿态{\r}\NYou will therefore assume the position of a suppliant before this throne.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:04.85,2:45:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}跪下！{\r}\NYou will kneel.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:08.35,2:45:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 什么？ - 下跪{\r}\N-I will what? -On your knees.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:13.82,2:45:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你竟敢要罗马帝国三巨头之一…{\r}\NYou dare ask the proconsul of the Roman Empire--
Dialogue: 0,2:45:17.32,2:45:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我也要求过朱利斯凯撒{\r}\NI asked it of Julius Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:19.91,2:45:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我命令你！{\r}\NI demand it of you!
Dialogue: 0,2:45:34.21,2:45:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在…{\r}\NNow...
Dialogue: 0,2:45:35.84,2:45:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}可以跟你签订条约{\r}\N...you may have the treaty you asked for...
Dialogue: 0,2:45:39.09,2:45:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只要遵照以下条件{\r}\N...on the following conditions:
Dialogue: 0,2:45:41.47,2:45:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}以罗马三巨头之一的身分{\r}\NBy your authority as proconsul of Rome...
Dialogue: 0,2:45:44.51,2:45:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}把犹太、约旦、阿美尼亚{\r}\N...you will cede to Egypt immediately the following territories:
Dialogue: 0,2:45:48.35,2:45:52.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}腓尼基、西奈、阿拉伯、塞浦路斯{\r}\NJudea, Jordan, Armenia, Phoenicia, the provinces of Sinai and Arabia...
Dialogue: 0,2:45:52.90,2:45:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}与克里特群岛割让给埃及{\r}\N...the islands of Cyprus and Crete.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:58.28,2:46:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你要求的是三份一个罗马帝国！{\r}\NYou ask for one-third of the Roman Empire!
Dialogue: 0,2:46:01.41,2:46:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}换句话说{\r}\NPut it another way.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:03.45,2:46:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我给了你三份之二{\r}\NI give to you two-thirds.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:08.45,2:46:10.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}真慷慨…{\r}\NMost generous.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:10.29,2:46:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不能接受！{\r}\NI cannot accept.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:12.87,2:46:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我建议你再考虑一下{\r}\NI suggest you deliberate further.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:16.17,2:46:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}或许跟罗马的上级商量商量{\r}\NPerhaps consult with your superior in Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:20.80,2:46:22.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}上级？{\r}\NMy superior?
Dialogue: 0,2:46:22.26,2:46:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维{\r}\NOctavian.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:24.47,2:46:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒屋大维啊！{\r}\NCaesar Octavian?
Dialogue: 0,2:46:33.48,2:46:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还未叫你退下！{\r}\NYou have not been dismissed!
Dialogue: 0,2:46:40.65,2:46:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在可以退下了{\r}\NYou are now dismissed.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:34.25,2:47:38.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}全部出去，我要跟陛下密谈{\r}\NOutside, all of you. Her Majesty and I will speak in private.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:39.09,2:47:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}出去！不然杀了你们来喂马！{\r}\NOut! Before I chop you up and feed you to my horses.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:42.71,2:47:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这就是罗马人吓小女孩的方法{\r}\NThat's how Romans frighten little girls.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:45.72,2:47:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们喜欢吓小女孩，出去吧{\r}\NThey like to frighten little girls. Wait outside.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:00.73,2:48:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我之所以娶屋大维雅 是因为她哥哥坚持…{\r}\NI married Octavia at her brother's insistence...
Dialogue: 0,2:48:03.53,2:48:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}以这样来示好确保和平的权宜之策{\r}\N...as a gesture of faith, of peace. A bargain sealed.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:06.78,2:48:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}权宜？洞房夜只跟新娘握手？{\r}\NWith a kiss? Or did you simply shake hands on your wedding night?
Dialogue: 0,2:48:11.28,2:48:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我还未到罗马群众已在欢庆这件婚事 教我如何拒绝？{\r}\NRome was celebrating the marriage even before I arrived. How could I refuse?
Dialogue: 0,2:48:15.91,2:48:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}说不啊{\r}\NBy saying no.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:17.83,2:48:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}对我的要求你不是一概说不吗？{\r}\NAs you have said no to all my demands.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:20.75,2:48:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你那些根本是无理的要求 打落水狗！{\r}\NThey're unreasonable! The kind laid down for a helpless enemy!
Dialogue: 0,2:48:24.72,2:48:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你还不算是落水狗呢{\r}\NYou're not helpless...yet.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:27.05,2:48:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不能割让那些领土 那等于要我公然跟罗马决裂{\r}\NI can't cede the territories. It would lead to a break between Rome and me.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:32.72,2:48:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这正是我的目的{\r}\NWhy do you think I asked for them?
Dialogue: 0,2:48:34.93,2:48:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这正中屋大维下怀{\r}\NIt would be playing into Octavian's hands, what he hopes for.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:38.06,2:48:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}实为不智{\r}\NIt would not be wise!
Dialogue: 0,2:48:39.86,2:48:41.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}何谓不智？{\r}\NWhat is wise?
Dialogue: 0,2:48:41.90,2:48:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将罗马、意大利 和全世界拱手让给屋大维？{\r}\NTo hand over Rome, Italy, the world to Octavian?
Dialogue: 0,2:48:45.49,2:48:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}公然对他卑躬屈膝？{\r}\NTo grovel publicly before his authority?
Dialogue: 0,2:48:48.53,2:48:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}把他的妹妹抱上床{\r}\NTake his sister to wed and to bed.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:51.62,2:48:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}求他原谅你{\r}\NAs if to beg forgiveness...
Dialogue: 0,2:48:53.62,2:48:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}沾上埃及荡妇？{\r}\N...for having stayed so long with your Egyptian harlot.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:03.46,2:49:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}哪件事让你生那么大的气？ 与屋大维讲和？{\r}\NWhat has angered you? That I dealt with Octavian how I could...
Dialogue: 0,2:49:06.76,2:49:10.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还是与他妹妹结婚？ 忌妒还是政治手段？{\r}\N...or that I married his sister to do it? Jealousy or politics? Which?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:10.43,2:49:13.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}都是！而且你对两者都懵然不知！{\r}\NBoth! And damn you for not understanding either.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:14.14,2:49:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不用你来教训我{\r}\NI wouldn't look to you for instruction.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:16.35,2:49:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}所以你像奴隶一样 乖乖的让屋大维扣上枷锁{\r}\NWhich is why you have come back chained to Octavian like a slave.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:20.02,2:49:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 奴隶？ - 这枷锁也颇精致{\r}\N-Slave! -And with such exquisite chains.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:23.73,2:49:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}轻声细语，三从四德{\r}\NSo softly spoken, so virtuous.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:27.57,2:49:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听说她睡觉时裹得紧紧的{\r}\NShe sleeps, I hear, fully clothed.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:34.16,2:49:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我回来了，这不是已说明一切？{\r}\NI come back. That's all that should concern you.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:37.00,2:49:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}真的吗？{\r}\NShould it?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:38.25,2:49:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}主人一声召唤 你还不是回到他或她身边！{\r}\NHow long before your master snaps his finger and you run back to him, or her?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:46.34,2:49:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我只有一个主人{\r}\NI have only one master.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:49.01,2:49:51.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我对你的爱{\r}\NMy love for you.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:51.30,2:49:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不{\r}\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:53.26,2:49:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的主人从来就不是爱{\r}\NYour master must not be love.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:56.39,2:49:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}从来就不是爱{\r}\NNever love.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:59.10,2:50:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有了爱，你就忘了一切{\r}\NGive yourself to love and you give yourself to forgetfulness...
Dialogue: 0,2:50:03.02,2:50:06.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}忘了身分，忘了雄心壮志{\r}\N...of what you are and who you are and what you want.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:07.11,2:50:10.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你要的不只这些？{\r}\NAnd what you want is worth so much more?
Dialogue: 0,2:50:11.32,2:50:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不要爱来当我的主人{\r}\NI will not have love as my master.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:14.37,2:50:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 那就不爱！ - 也不要屋大维当主人{\r}\N-Then you will not have love. -Nor will I have Octavian.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:19.54,2:50:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 不需要害怕 - 看你说得颇有自信{\r}\N-Never fear. -How confident you are.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:23.58,2:50:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那，屋大维的主人是什么？{\r}\NAnd has Octavian a master?
Dialogue: 0,2:50:26.17,2:50:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他的野心，当罗马的皇帝和神{\r}\NHis ambition: to rule the Roman world as emperor and god.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:29.88,2:50:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就是罗马的天下{\r}\NThe Roman world, to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:32.80,2:50:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他的阻碍又是什么？{\r}\NAnd what stands in his way?
Dialogue: 0,2:50:35.85,2:50:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 你和我 - 和我儿子{\r}\N-You and I. -And my son!
Dialogue: 0,2:50:38.93,2:50:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒的法定继承人{\r}\NThe rightful heir to the name and glory of great Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:42.94,2:50:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但被屋大维篡夺了{\r}\NOctavian has already stolen those and he will now destroy...
Dialogue: 0,2:50:48.36,2:50:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在他要利用他妹妹… 毁掉罗马人对你的爱戴{\r}\N...in the name of his sister, the love Rome has for you.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:51.44,2:50:53.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你跟她结婚{\r}\NAnd by your marriage to her...
Dialogue: 0,2:50:54.03,2:50:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我就成了你的娼妇{\r}\N...he has made of me, unmistakably, your whore.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:58.24,2:51:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不要怕屋大维？{\r}\NNever fear Octavian?
Dialogue: 0,2:51:01.58,2:51:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不怕的人是他{\r}\NIt is he, now, who I think must be unafraid.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:10.80,2:51:13.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}攻城掠地是我的专长{\r}\NShow me a city and I'll tell you how to take it.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:13.38,2:51:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}骁勇善战是我的本领{\r}\NI'll find an army's weak points and hit them hard where they are.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:16.97,2:51:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但要我坐下来咬耳朵{\r}\NBut make me to sit down and talk in whispers of this and that...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:21.18,2:51:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谈论是与非，我真的不在行{\r}\N...with an emphasis here and a shrug there, and I'm soon confounded and defeated.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:27.40,2:51:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}依我的专长发挥{\r}\NMeaning to do the best...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:30.48,2:51:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}才能所向无敌{\r}\N...I suppose I could not have done worse.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:38.37,2:51:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还赶得及{\r}\NThere is still time.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:41.45,2:51:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若问我的心愿{\r}\NLet someone ask me what I want:
Dialogue: 0,2:51:44.92,2:51:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只想与世无争跟你住在这里{\r}\NTo live with you in peace and love.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:48.50,2:51:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}全面投降{\r}\NDo you have...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:50.67,2:51:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你有什么条件？{\r}\N...conditions for total surrender?
Dialogue: 0,2:51:53.80,2:51:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}跟凯撒一样{\r}\NFirst, as did Caesar...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:56.76,2:52:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}按照埃及礼仪跟我结婚{\r}\N...you will marry me according to Egyptian ritual.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:00.56,2:52:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这不是条件是恩赐{\r}\NThat's not a condition, that's a reward.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:03.06,2:52:05.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你宣布凯撒里奥{\r}\NYou'll declare, by your authority...
Dialogue: 0,2:52:05.64,2:52:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}成为埃及国王{\r}\N...Caesarion to be king of Egypt...
Dialogue: 0,2:52:08.27,2:52:10.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们以他的名义共同执政{\r}\N...and we will rule together in his name.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:11.23,2:52:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}绝对同意{\r}\NHappily granted.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:13.40,2:52:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我提过的领土都割让给埃及{\r}\NYou will cede to Egypt all the territories I have demanded.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:20.78,2:52:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}必须这样！{\r}\NYou must.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:22.91,2:52:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}即使只为确保你的权力与地位{\r}\NIf only to assert your own authority and power.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:26.67,2:52:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}否则，我们迟早一无所有{\r}\NOtherwise, inevitably, in time we will lose everything.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:31.04,2:52:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你看不出来吗？{\r}\NCan't you see that?
Dialogue: 0,2:52:35.09,2:52:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我眼中{\r}\NI can see nothing...
Dialogue: 0,2:52:37.59,2:52:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只看到你{\r}\N...but you.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:45.39,2:52:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我无法再原谅安东尼！{\r}\NI am no longer content to forgive Antony!
Dialogue: 0,2:52:48.19,2:52:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}根据蛮族礼仪娶个埃及人{\r}\NTo marry this Egyptian according to their barbaric rites!
Dialogue: 0,2:52:51.48,2:52:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马法例不会承认！ 当初凯撒自己…{\r}\NMeaningless under Roman law! Great Caesar himself--
Dialogue: 0,2:52:54.65,2:52:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼想有样学样{\r}\NYes. Bit by bit, Antony crawls behind his memory.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:58.61,2:53:00.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但请问朱曼尼卡斯…{\r}\NBut tell us this, Germanicus:
Dialogue: 0,2:53:00.53,2:53:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒有没有将三份一个罗马帝国…{\r}\NDid great Caesar also toss one-third of the Roman Empire...
Dialogue: 0,2:53:04.58,2:53:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}送到克莉奥佩特拉怀里？{\r}\N...into Cleopatra's undoubtedly deserving lap?
Dialogue: 0,2:53:08.21,2:53:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当年凯撒占领的地方 今日主权仍争论不休{\r}\NThe territories in dispute were subjugated by Julius Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:12.34,2:53:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒之子应该有合法统治权{\r}\NThe right to rule over them is the heritage of his son.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:16.63,2:53:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}依凯撒之名我赐予托勒密凯撒里奥{\r}\NAnd in the name of the mighty Caesar I grant to King Ptolemy Caesarion...
Dialogue: 0,2:53:20.97,2:53:22.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这个权利{\r}\N...that right.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:24.72,2:53:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}让世人了解罗马的伟大{\r}\NLet it be known the greatness of Rome lies not in what she takes...
Dialogue: 0,2:53:28.85,2:53:30.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在给予而不在侵占{\r}\N...but in what she gives.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:35.07,2:53:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他说，罗马的伟大在给予{\r}\N"Rome's greatness lies in what she gives," he says.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:39.11,2:53:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}轻轻松松慷他人之慨{\r}\NThen calmly gives what is not his.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:42.20,2:53:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉{\r}\NAnd Cleopatra takes...
Dialogue: 0,2:53:45.45,2:53:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}予取予求下去{\r}\N...and will take more.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:47.33,2:53:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}战祸终将来临{\r}\NAnd war will come.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:50.37,2:53:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她知，我知{\r}\NShe knows and I know...
Dialogue: 0,2:53:52.92,2:53:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}难免一战{\r}\N...that war will come.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:55.50,2:53:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但我不主战{\r}\NBut I will not speak for it...
Dialogue: 0,2:53:58.05,2:54:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}也不与安东尼为敌{\r}\N...nor will I speak against Antony.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:02.68,2:54:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我将等待被逼上战场{\r}\NI must be forced into war.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:05.76,2:54:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马人民会逼我开战{\r}\NThe people of Rome must force this war upon me.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:09.35,2:54:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我要等民愤涌进元老院{\r}\NThey must storm the doors of the Senate, crying for it.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:14.19,2:54:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}行动快的话，在罗马人知道之前{\r}\NIf we move quickly, the Romans won't know we've crossed the Mediterranean...
Dialogue: 0,2:54:18.07,2:54:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们已越过地中海登陆希腊了{\r}\N...until we land in Greece.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:19.86,2:54:22.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你和鲁非欧将军立刻上船{\r}\NYou and General Rufio will start embarking the troops at once.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:22.91,2:54:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是的，陛下{\r}\NYes, Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:26.20,2:54:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如果决定将敌军引入希腊…{\r}\NIf it is decided to move our armies into Greece.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:29.08,2:54:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}已经决定了{\r}\NIt has been decided.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:31.08,2:54:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我的手下{\r}\NMy men do not...
Dialogue: 0,2:54:33.04,2:54:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不擅航海{\r}\N...travel well by sea.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:34.50,2:54:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们专长打陆战，在陆上行军{\r}\NThey fight on land. They move on land.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:37.42,2:54:40.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的手下要听从我的指挥{\r}\NYour men will do as they are told, as mine will.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:40.42,2:54:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我手下仍听我指挥！他们还不是…{\r}\NMy men will do as they're told by me. They have not yet become--
Dialogue: 0,2:54:47.31,2:54:49.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们还是罗马人{\r}\NThey are still Roman.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:50.52,2:54:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但是{\r}\NHowever...
Dialogue: 0,2:54:52.73,2:54:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我只知听命行事{\r}\N...since I do as I'm told....
Dialogue: 0,2:54:55.98,2:54:59.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}最终决定权还是在安东尼阁下{\r}\NThe final decision will, of course, be Lord Antony's.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:59.36,2:55:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}相信你很快会作出定夺{\r}\NAnd I'm sure that in time he will make it.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:03.40,2:55:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}退下{\r}\NThat is all.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:12.16,2:55:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当着各军官面前 你最好不要和我争执{\r}\NIt would be wiser not to disagree in the presence of our officers.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:17.46,2:55:19.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的军官们{\r}\NYour officers.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:19.92,2:55:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你到底要我做什么定夺？{\r}\NWhat final decision have you decided I am to make?
Dialogue: 0,2:55:23.22,2:55:26.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为什么反对调兵去希腊？{\r}\NWhy do you oppose transporting our armies to Greece?
Dialogue: 0,2:55:26.68,2:55:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不想和罗马开战{\r}\NBecause I do not want war against Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:29.35,2:55:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}马克安东尼带领十万军队{\r}\NOne hundred thousand men led by Marc Antony.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:32.73,2:55:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维不笨，他不会开战{\r}\NOctavian is no fool. He won't fight.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:35.77,2:55:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他不想，但他不得不… 就在登陆的地点，会立即开战{\r}\NHe'll have to, instantly, on the spot where they land.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:39.19,2:55:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马不会对你宣战！{\r}\NRome will not declare war against you.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:42.44,2:55:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不同意{\r}\NI do not agree.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:45.24,2:55:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我没有征询你的意见！{\r}\NI have not asked for your opinion.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:47.82,2:55:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}至少现在没有{\r}\NNot for some time.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:49.49,2:55:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}见到三百艘新造的战舰就不同了{\r}\NNot since I doubted the necessity of building 300 ships.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:53.41,2:55:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}备战的目的是停战{\r}\NThe way to prevent war is to be ready for it.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:57.04,2:56:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}建三百艘战舰而不打仗？{\r}\NHave 300 warships ever been built for war without war?
Dialogue: 0,2:56:00.92,2:56:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不打仗一样可以整顿军容啊！{\r}\NWe shall have what we want without it.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:04.42,2:56:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}陛下，请听我说{\r}\NYour Majesty, please hear me.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:07.34,2:56:10.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我相信战事已是箭在弦上{\r}\NI think we are very near the edge.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:10.85,2:56:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}拉弓的人不是我们{\r}\NStrings are being pulled, and not by us.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:14.18,2:56:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们毫无选择正被操控{\r}\NWe are being managed and maneuvered without our choosing.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:17.69,2:56:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维雅派来的代表{\r}\NThe deputation sent on behalf of Lady Octavia...
Dialogue: 0,2:56:20.94,2:56:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是在罗马极受敬重的人士{\r}\N...chosen from the most highly revered men of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:24.53,2:56:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们所能带回罗马的全是安东尼的…{\r}\NWhy? They can take back to their people nothing but Lord Antony's...
Dialogue: 0,2:56:29.95,2:56:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}倔辱与及一纸不必要的休书{\r}\N...forgive me, insulting and unnecessary divorce of her...
Dialogue: 0,2:56:34.83,2:56:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}以及他的避而不见{\r}\N...and his rejection of them.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:39.08,2:56:43.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我下的命令，我负责{\r}\NIt was done at my bidding. The responsibility is mine.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:45.55,2:56:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但做此事的人是我{\r}\NThe doing was mine.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:50.47,2:56:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你有何建议？{\r}\NWhat do you propose?
Dialogue: 0,2:56:51.93,2:56:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我去罗马，尽量和屋大维及人民沟通{\r}\NLet me go to Rome and approach Octavian, possibly the Roman people...
Dialogue: 0,2:56:56.23,2:56:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}使他们相信我们爱好和平{\r}\N...and assure them that we want peace.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:01.31,2:57:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}去啊{\r}\NGo then.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:03.48,2:57:04.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}去罗马啊{\r}\NGo to Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:17.79,2:57:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}保重{\r}\NSosigenes!
Dialogue: 0,2:57:22.17,2:57:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}保重{\r}\NTake care.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:28.88,2:57:30.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那老人是个忠臣{\r}\NHe's very dear to you, that old man.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:30.72,2:57:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的担忧写在脸上{\r}\NYour concern and worry are written all over you.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:33.72,2:57:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}对不起，但你流露出关怀的神情{\r}\NForgive me, but it's a kind of love that you're showing.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:37.52,2:57:41.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就等他们照 自己的意思去说吧，去谈判吧{\r}\NLet them talk. Let them negotiate all they want.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:41.35,2:57:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}时间站在我们这边 我们只会愈来愈强大{\r}\NTime is on our side. We can only grow stronger.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:59.62,2:58:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}议事堂内{\r}\NThese walls must not believe their ears...
Dialogue: 0,2:58:02.71,2:58:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}竟这样一片死寂{\r}\N...to hear such silence...
Dialogue: 0,2:58:07.09,2:58:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}右边鸦雀无声{\r}\N...from the right...
Dialogue: 0,2:58:10.38,2:58:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}左边也鸦雀无声{\r}\N...from the left.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:13.09,2:58:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}人民的怒吼清晰可闻{\r}\NThe call of the Roman people can be clearly heard...
Dialogue: 0,2:58:16.56,2:58:19.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}元老院各位大官{\r}\N...yet the Roman Senate...
Dialogue: 0,2:58:19.23,2:58:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}却毫无反应{\r}\N...has no answer.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:22.85,2:58:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那么，我们就这样静静坐着{\r}\NShall we then just sit...
Dialogue: 0,2:58:27.11,2:58:29.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}并听着{\r}\N...and listen?
Dialogue: 0,2:58:30.11,2:58:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}奥古斯都凯撒，我们都愿意 向克莉奥佩特拉宣战…{\r}\NThere is not one of us that would not willingly make war upon Cleopatra.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:35.95,2:58:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}怎样宣战？{\r}\NBut how...
Dialogue: 0,2:58:37.66,2:58:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}同时却又想避开向深受罗马爱戴{\r}\N...without also making war upon Marc Antony...
Dialogue: 0,2:58:40.50,2:58:43.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}而又深爱罗马的马克安东尼宣战{\r}\N...loved by Rome and loving Rome?
Dialogue: 0,2:58:43.58,2:58:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}受罗马爱戴，也深爱罗马…{\r}\N"Loved by Rome and loving Rome."
Dialogue: 0,2:58:48.55,2:58:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我手上有一份安东尼最新的遗嘱{\r}\NI have here the last will and testament...
Dialogue: 0,2:58:52.68,2:58:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听听他怎样爱罗马{\r}\N...of Antony, who so loves Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:59.06,2:59:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你们自己看{\r}\NRead for yourselves...
Dialogue: 0,2:59:01.18,2:59:04.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他怎样爱罗马！{\r}\N...how dearly Antony loves you, loves Rome...
Dialogue: 0,2:59:05.10,2:59:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他亲笔签署的最新遗嘱{\r}\N...in this, his last will under his seal.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:11.36,2:59:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}最近才由埃及送来{\r}\NOnly lately brought from Egypt...
Dialogue: 0,2:59:13.86,2:59:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}放于圣殿 安东尼指示{\r}\N...and deposited in our holy temple at Antony's request...
Dialogue: 0,2:59:18.12,2:59:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}受人尊敬的西索吉尼斯做的{\r}\N...by the distinguished Sosigenes.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:20.70,2:59:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}超凡之人所做超凡的事{\r}\NAn extraordinary mission for an extraordinary man.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:24.29,2:59:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}多么有智慧，多么切合 克莉奥佩特拉的心意，多么受她信赖{\r}\NSo wise, so close to Cleopatra, so trusted by her.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:29.42,2:59:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}看啊！ 最终列入了…{\r}\NRead in Antony's will...
Dialogue: 0,2:59:32.34,2:59:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼的遗嘱{\r}\N...at the end.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:34.38,2:59:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不要忘记你心爱的安东尼 的最终要求{\r}\NCommit to memory the last request of your beloved Antony.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:38.93,2:59:42.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那是他对罗马爱的见证！{\r}\NIt bears witness to his love for Rome.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:49.02,2:59:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当他死时，里头说…{\r}\NWhen he is dead, it says...
Dialogue: 0,2:59:53.49,2:59:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当马克安东尼死时…{\r}\N...when Marc Antony has died...
Dialogue: 0,2:59:57.24,3:00:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他希望被葬在…{\r}\N...it is his wish to be buried...
Dialogue: 0,3:00:00.79,3:00:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他挚爱的亚历山卓！{\r}\N...in his beloved Alexandria!
Dialogue: 0,3:00:06.21,3:00:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在埃及{\r}\NIn Egypt!
Dialogue: 0,3:00:07.96,3:00:10.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}与埃及人一起{\r}\NAmong Egyptians.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:10.55,3:00:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}紧靠他的埃及娼妇！{\r}\NBeside his Egyptian whore!
Dialogue: 0,3:00:16.97,3:00:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我说的是否事实？{\r}\NIs what I say the truth?
Dialogue: 0,3:00:19.85,3:00:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我说的难道不是事实吗？{\r}\NDo I speak the truth?
Dialogue: 0,3:00:30.69,3:00:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}宣战！宣战！{\r}\N-War! -War!
Dialogue: 0,3:00:32.61,3:00:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}宣战！宣战！宣战！宣战！…{\r}\NWar! War! War!
Dialogue: 0,3:01:11.36,3:01:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}各位眼前的是战争的金矛{\r}\NI hold before you the Golden Spear of War.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:15.78,3:01:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}元老院无反对{\r}\NPlaced into my hands without dissent...
Dialogue: 0,3:01:18.91,3:01:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}授权落于我手中{\r}\N...by the command and will of the Senate of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:22.70,3:01:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在轮到各位 罗马子民来指引我{\r}\NAnd now it is you, the people of Rome, who must direct me.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:28.04,3:01:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}敌人在哪里？{\r}\NWhere is the enemy?
Dialogue: 0,3:01:30.67,3:01:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及在哪里？告诉我！{\r}\NWhere is Egypt? Show me the way!
Dialogue: 0,3:01:42.22,3:01:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不！{\r}\NNo!
Dialogue: 0,3:01:44.18,3:01:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不！{\r}\NNo!
Dialogue: 0,3:01:46.64,3:01:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是那里！{\r}\NThere!
Dialogue: 0,3:01:48.64,3:01:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及在那里！{\r}\NThere is Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:09.33,3:02:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}于是，罗马人再次自相残杀{\r}\NAnd so once more, the Romans warred upon each other.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:13.50,3:02:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就好像安东尼索预言…{\r}\NAnd just as Antony had foretold...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:16.13,3:02:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维的军队{\r}\N...the forces of Octavian came to meet them...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:19.01,3:02:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}开到登陆的地点{\r}\N...on the spot where they landed...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:21.55,3:02:25.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就在希腊的爱克提安{\r}\N...which was at Actium, in Greece.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:26.22,3:02:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}明天日出决一死战{\r}\NAction begins with the rise of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:28.64,3:02:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的战略扼要凶猛但适合陆战{\r}\NYour plan is brave and simple. It's possible on land...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:31.89,3:02:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}打海战就显得不智{\r}\N...but we debate its wisdom upon the sea.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:34.61,3:02:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}敌军以海犯陆，且以寡敌众{\r}\NI have an enemy on land with fewer troops, on sea with fewer ships.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:38.73,3:02:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}看他怎样发挥他的智慧！{\r}\NLet him debate the wisdom of his position.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:41.07,3:02:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我可以选择陆战或海战 而我选择了海战！{\r}\NI have a happy choice. To destroy him wet or dry. I have chosen wet.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:48.37,3:02:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}尤法诺，到女王船上汇报军情{\r}\NI think it best, Euphranor, you report to Cleopatra aboard her vessel in the harbor.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:53.08,3:02:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你可以找一百个藉口{\r}\NThere you may point out to her...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:55.21,3:02:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}向她说明我的方法不可行{\r}\N...the reasons why my brave simplicity has failed.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:59.80,3:03:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但我首先废除你指挥的职务{\r}\NIn any case, you are relieved of your battle command.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:14.44,3:03:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你何时决定把所有战力…{\r}\NThis final commitment of yourself, your ships, of all of us...
Dialogue: 0,3:03:18.65,3:03:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}用在海上与屋大维决一雌雄？{\r}\N...to fight at sea, when did you decide?
Dialogue: 0,3:03:22.28,3:03:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 对不起，鲁非欧，我不得不… - 坎尼迪斯和我几个月以来…{\r}\N-Forgive me. I had-- -We've worked hard for many months.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:25.62,3:03:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}训练了一支来自二十几个国家 将近二十万人的部队{\r}\NWe've trained an army of 200,000 men from 20 countries.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:29.99,3:03:33.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 不会浪费的，战胜之后… - 二十万步兵和骑兵{\r}\N-They won't be wasted-- -Of which, tonight, 20,000 of them...
Dialogue: 0,3:03:33.62,3:03:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}挤在船上 拖到海上，承受风浪之苦！{\r}\N...will be herded onto those ships and dragged out to sea, puking and afraid.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:38.38,3:03:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 这是什么理论？ - 因为我军令如山{\r}\N-Why, my lord? Why? -Because I have decided it will be so!
Dialogue: 0,3:03:43.34,3:03:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我认为这是种荣耀{\r}\NI consider it an honor...
Dialogue: 0,3:03:44.93,3:03:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}可以和安东尼阁下 在任何地方并肩作战{\r}\N...to fight beside Lord Antony at any time, anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:49.60,3:03:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这才像罗马的口吻，拉莫斯{\r}\NSpoken like a Roman, Ramos.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:53.52,3:03:56.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你代替鲁非欧，留在我身边{\r}\NAnd you shall fight at my side, in Rufio's place.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:58.23,3:04:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}鲁非欧，你留在女王船上{\r}\NRufio, you will remain with Her Majesty aboard her vessel.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:03.11,3:04:04.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}遵命{\r}\NAs you command.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:04.65,3:04:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}坎尼迪斯，你留在陆上{\r}\NCanidius, you will remain with the land forces...
Dialogue: 0,3:04:07.62,3:04:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}尽情隔山观虎斗{\r}\N...cheering from the hilltop, if you like.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:11.54,3:04:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}遵命{\r}\N-As you command. -Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:14.75,3:04:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一定要遵从命令{\r}\NAs I command.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:19.88,3:04:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}解散！{\r}\NYou're all dismissed.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:40.27,3:04:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼！{\r}\NAntony.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:44.90,3:04:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}发生了什么事？{\r}\NWhat has happened?
Dialogue: 0,3:04:47.07,3:04:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我吗？{\r}\NTo me?
Dialogue: 0,3:04:49.82,3:04:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你质问我发生什么事？{\r}\NYou have happened to me.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:36.54,3:05:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}远处望到屋大维的战旗了吗？{\r}\NDo the lookouts have Octavian's insignia?
Dialogue: 0,3:05:38.79,3:05:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 日出就看见他的金鹰了 - 恐怕日落只剩一堆金羽毛{\r}\N-A golden eagle. Sighted at sunrise. -By sunset we'll have those gold feathers.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:45.96,3:05:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}令屋大维知道我们出来应战！{\r}\NLet Octavian know we're coming!
Dialogue: 0,3:05:48.76,3:05:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}让敌军见识我军的气势！{\r}\NLet the enemy hear the voice of Antony's legions!
Dialogue: 0,3:06:17.75,3:06:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他在路上发个信号给凯撒{\r}\NHe's on his way. Signal my lord Caesar's ship.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:20.50,3:06:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼有升起战旗吗？{\r}\NDoes it fly his insignia?
Dialogue: 0,3:06:22.46,3:06:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一定要严守我的命令！{\r}\NMy orders are to be followed exactly as issued.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:30.26,3:06:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}愿主保佑安东尼不要改变战略{\r}\NAnd may the gods grant that Antony has not changed his plan of battle.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:41.56,3:06:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他冲过去了{\r}\NThere he goes...
Dialogue: 0,3:06:43.52,3:06:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}和从前打仗一样直扑中央{\r}\N...as he's done 100 times on land. Straight for the center.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:47.65,3:06:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如果在陆地上我们可以保护侧翼{\r}\NIf only it were on land, and we were there to protect his flanks.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:51.70,3:06:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}可惜我们不是{\r}\NBut we're not.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:57.91,3:07:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将所有部署向在女王船上的{\r}\NThis and all dispositions are to be signaled...
Dialogue: 0,3:07:00.20,3:07:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}尤法诺汇报{\r}\N...to Admiral Euphranor aboard Cleopatra's barge.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:02.67,3:07:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}尤法诺？他不是负责指挥…{\r}\NBut Euphranor's in command of--
Dialogue: 0,3:07:04.71,3:07:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}指挥模型玩具船{\r}\NIn command of moving toy ships on a painted ocean...
Dialogue: 0,3:07:09.59,3:07:13.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}给女王了解最新的战况{\r}\N...so that Egypt's queen can more clearly follow her war upon water...
Dialogue: 0,3:07:13.84,3:07:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}打杖的是安东尼和两万罗马子弟兵{\r}\N...to which she has committed Marc Antony and 20,000 Romans.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:27.82,3:07:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若真照他所讲的…{\r}\NJust as he said he would.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:29.69,3:07:33.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼和他的护航舰直扑屋大维{\r}\NAntony and his escorts, by themselves, are after Octavian.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:33.36,3:07:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 他已经突围到中央了 - 是他们让他进去的{\r}\N-He's already broken through their center. -They let him through.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:36.66,3:07:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}然后从旁包抄{\r}\NThey Roman line will close behind him.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:38.66,3:07:40.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若夹击战开始，他们就无法…{\r}\NNot if we engage, as Antony said.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:40.66,3:07:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不会打夹击战的亚格里巴 会下令他们退后{\r}\NThey won't engage. Agrippa will pull them back and back, behind Antony...
Dialogue: 0,3:07:45.75,3:07:47.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼追屋大维时他们一直跟在后面{\r}\N...as Antony chases Octavian.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:50.46,3:07:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有什么最新战况？{\r}\NWhat report?
Dialogue: 0,3:07:51.96,3:07:56.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼已经穿过罗马中央战线{\r}\NLord Antony is already through the center of the Roman line.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:58.43,3:08:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为了追屋大维{\r} {\fn黑体\fs24}他已经深入敌方舰群{\r}\NHe is now deep within the Roman fleet, in pursuit of Octavian.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:15.03,3:08:17.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}快！快！{\r}\NFaster! Faster!
Dialogue: 0,3:08:28.96,3:08:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们加了速{\r}\NThey've increased their own speed. We're too heavy to catch them.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:32.80,3:08:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll slow them down.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:35.55,3:08:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}准备开炮，炮手！{\r}\NStart the ballistas. Javelin throwers.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:38.76,3:08:41.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}瞄高一点，宁愿射过头{\r}\NAim high. Overshoot rather than under.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:45.98,3:08:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}开炮！炮手！{\r}\NBallistas. Javelins.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:52.90,3:08:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}开炮！{\r}\NBallistas!
Dialogue: 0,3:09:06.25,3:09:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维的船比埃及的快很多{\r}\NOctavian's ships are so much faster than our Egyptian tubs.
Dialogue: 0,3:09:10.42,3:09:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为什么亚格里巴不躲开？{\r}\NWhy doesn't Agrippa keep him away from Antony's ballistas?
Dialogue: 0,3:09:28.85,3:09:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}炮手！{\r}\NBallistas!
Dialogue: 0,3:09:49.79,3:09:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}炮手！{\r}\NBallista!
Dialogue: 0,3:10:00.43,3:10:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}炮手！{\r}\NBallista!
Dialogue: 0,3:10:03.22,3:10:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}阁下！阁下！{\r}\NMy lord! My lord!
Dialogue: 0,3:10:05.72,3:10:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}击中敌舰，摧毁一侧船桨！{\r}\NA direct hit on the enemy! A bank of oars has been destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,3:10:12.52,3:10:15.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他从舷侧冲过来了！{\r}\NHe's coming around broadside.
Dialogue: 0,3:10:15.36,3:10:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}准备碰撞！{\r}\NWe've got him!
Dialogue: 0,3:10:16.90,3:10:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}撞他然后上船杀了他！{\r}\NCollision course. We'll ram him, board and destroy him.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:16.42,3:11:18.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维！{\r}\NOctavian!
Dialogue: 0,3:11:20.96,3:11:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维！ 你追随凯撒的时候到了！{\r}\NOctavian! Now is your time to be a Caesar!
Dialogue: 0,3:11:50.16,3:11:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 他躲在哪里？ - 屋大维不在这艘船上{\r}\N-Where is he hiding? -My Lord Octavian is not on board.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:57.92,3:12:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在包围安东尼{\r}\NAnd now we close the trap.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:00.34,3:12:03.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}全力进攻！{\r}\NNow we hit my Lord Antony with everything we have.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:25.99,3:12:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没有安东尼的消息？{\r}\NNo word of Lord Antony?
Dialogue: 0,3:12:28.16,3:12:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他该已制服了屋大维{\r}\NBy now he must have Octavian. You said he rammed Octavian's ship.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:31.87,3:12:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不是说他撞毁了屋大维的船吗？{\r}\NIt may be Lord Antony rammed a ship flying Octavian's insignia.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:35.96,3:12:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若那真的是屋大维的船…{\r}\NBut if it is Octavian's ship, if Octavian is on board--
Dialogue: 0,3:12:39.38,3:12:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就算安东尼杀了他 他仍被其他敌军包围{\r}\NIf he finds and kills Octavian, he's still surrounded by the Roman fleet.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:44.21,3:12:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 派遣支援部队！ - 没有支援部队！{\r}\N-Then send him help. -I've none to send.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:50.72,3:12:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们截断我们的舰队{\r}\NThey're pulling our ships apart now.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:53.35,3:12:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼孤军作战{\r}\NThey've got Antony alone and cut off...
Dialogue: 0,3:12:55.85,3:12:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}像群野狗围攻受伤的熊！{\r}\N...closing in on him like a pack of dogs on a wounded bear.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:21.48,3:14:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 安东尼的船？ - 被击毁了{\r}\N-Lord Antony's ship? -Gone.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:26.07,3:14:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 屋大维的呢？ - 起火燃烧，无计可施{\r}\N-And Octavian's ship? -Burning, helpless.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:38.29,3:14:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将军，你认为…{\r}\NWould you say, admiral...
Dialogue: 0,3:14:42.04,3:14:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼是否已阵亡？{\r}\N...that Lord Antony is dead?
Dialogue: 0,3:14:56.43,3:14:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}返回埃及的话，风向如何？{\r}\NHow is the wind for Egypt?
Dialogue: 0,3:14:58.68,3:15:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}很好{\r}\NFair.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:05.02,3:15:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}立刻回航{\r}\NWe'll sail at once.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:15.62,3:15:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}划桨手就位！起锚！ 航向埃及！{\r}\NMan the oar banks. Hoist anchor. We sail for Egypt!
Dialogue: 0,3:15:52.36,3:15:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}坎尼迪斯阁下！{\r}\NMy Lord Canidius!
Dialogue: 0,3:16:09.25,3:16:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}永远记住爱克提安一役…{\r}\NRemember always, that after the battle of Actium...
Dialogue: 0,3:16:13.72,3:16:18.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维、安东尼双双战死{\r}\N...with Octavian dead and Antony dead...
Dialogue: 0,3:16:18.68,3:16:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}胜利者{\r}\N...you saw the victor...
Dialogue: 0,3:16:20.93,3:16:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}却驾着金船逃之夭夭{\r}\N...sail away on her golden barge.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:33.40,3:16:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉走了…{\r}\NShe's going.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:35.95,3:16:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉走了…{\r}\NCleopatra's going!
Dialogue: 0,3:16:42.37,3:16:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}丢低我们！{\r}\NLeaving me!
Dialogue: 0,3:16:44.08,3:16:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}阁下{\r}\NMy lord.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:45.87,3:16:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我军伤亡惨重 盔甲所余无几{\r}\NMy lord, our casualties are heavy. We have little armor left.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:49.50,3:16:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}部队需要重组、打气{\r}\NOur men need regrouping, someone to give them courage.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:52.63,3:16:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}伤兵哀号，残存的需要支援{\r}\NThe dying are calling for you. The living need your help.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:56.34,3:16:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不能丢下他们不理…{\r}\NYou can't leave them.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:58.68,3:17:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听我说！{\r}\NListen to me!
Dialogue: 0,3:17:31.71,3:17:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}救命！{\r}\NHelp!
Dialogue: 0,3:17:35.63,3:17:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}救命！{\r}\NHelp!
Dialogue: 0,3:17:56.94,3:17:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒，好消息！{\r}\NCaesar, news!
Dialogue: 0,3:17:58.78,3:18:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉走了 安东尼追在后面{\r}\NGreat news! Cleopatra is leaving the battle. Antony is following her.
Dialogue: 0,3:18:02.57,3:18:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们大获全胜！{\r}\NWe have won a great victory.
Dialogue: 0,3:18:14.96,3:18:18.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}停桨！{\r}\NWeigh oars!
Dialogue: 0,3:19:49.31,3:19:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}陛下正急于见你，请下去{\r}\NHer Majesty is most anxious to see you. Will you come below?
Dialogue: 0,3:19:55.81,3:19:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}抑或是你留在这儿 我请她上来？{\r}\NPerhaps if you wish to remain here, she will come to you.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:00.94,3:20:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}要不要准备食物？酒？{\r}\NShall I send you food? Wine?
Dialogue: 0,3:20:09.49,3:20:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}陛下的命令{\r}\NHer Majesty's orders.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:12.16,3:20:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她怕你{\r}\NShe's afraid you might...
Dialogue: 0,3:20:14.33,3:20:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}伤害自己{\r}\N...harm yourself.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:00.02,3:22:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}请坐{\r}\NPlease.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:04.27,3:22:08.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维越过叙利亚进入埃及{\r}\NOctavian has crossed from Syria into Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:09.49,3:22:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}几星期后会到达这里{\r}\NHe can be here in a matter of weeks.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:12.12,3:22:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亚历山卓只余下两个部队{\r}\NThere are two full legions here in Alexandria...
Dialogue: 0,3:22:15.29,3:22:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}肯听命于你{\r}\N...who have remained loyal to you.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:18.25,3:22:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们等着…{\r}\NThey and their officers...
Dialogue: 0,3:22:21.21,3:22:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你下令{\r}\N...are waiting for you to command them.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:25.30,3:22:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若不要与我说话 至少跟鲁非欧谈谈？{\r}\NIf not to me, won't you speak to Rufio at least...
Dialogue: 0,3:22:29.63,3:22:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}或是找个你肯开口的人？{\r}\N...or to anyone you choose?
Dialogue: 0,3:22:33.80,3:22:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼，只等你一声令下！{\r}\NAntony, just say what you want done and it will be.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:41.19,3:22:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你很久没望我了{\r}\NIt's been so long since you've looked at me. Don't turn away...
Dialogue: 0,3:22:45.57,3:22:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}别转过头去{\r}\N...even like this...
Dialogue: 0,3:22:48.32,3:22:51.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的眼中充满了仇恨{\r}\N...with your eyes filled with hate.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:52.03,3:22:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}燃烧着怒火{\r}\NHow they burn with hate.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:57.49,3:22:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为什么？安东尼，为什么？{\r}\NWhy, Antony? Why?
Dialogue: 0,3:23:00.50,3:23:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}因为我逃走？{\r}\NBecause I ran away?
Dialogue: 0,3:23:02.71,3:23:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们说你已阵亡！{\r}\NThey told me you were dead!
Dialogue: 0,3:23:08.71,3:23:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那我{\r}\NWhat...
Dialogue: 0,3:23:10.22,3:23:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还能怎样？{\r}\N...could I do?
Dialogue: 0,3:23:13.72,3:23:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你突然消失了{\r}\NWhere could I go...
Dialogue: 0,3:23:16.18,3:23:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我还能去哪儿？{\r}\N...in a world suddenly without you...
Dialogue: 0,3:23:20.52,3:23:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}除了我的儿子和我的国家{\r}\N...except to my son and my country...
Dialogue: 0,3:23:24.02,3:23:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒里奥和埃及{\r}\N...Caesarion and Egypt?
Dialogue: 0,3:23:27.02,3:23:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我要保护他们对抗屋大维{\r}\NI wanted to save them from Octavian.
Dialogue: 0,3:23:30.78,3:23:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你也会想我逃走的{\r}\NYou would have wanted me to go.
Dialogue: 0,3:23:33.61,3:23:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你会命令我逃走的{\r}\NYou would have commanded me to go.
Dialogue: 0,3:23:37.08,3:23:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}告诉我你会这么做！{\r}\NTell me you would have!
Dialogue: 0,3:23:44.25,3:23:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们告诉我你已经阵亡了！{\r}\NThey told me you were dead.
Dialogue: 0,3:23:48.25,3:23:51.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们告诉我你已经阵亡了！{\r}\NThey told me you were dead.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:00.14,3:24:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们说得对{\r}\NYou were quite right.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:02.85,3:24:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我已经死了{\r}\NI am dead.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:35.97,3:24:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}盖尔斯朱利斯凯撒{\r}\NThe armies of Gaius Julius Caesar...
Dialogue: 0,3:24:38.14,3:24:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一直向亚历山卓前来{\r}\N...are advancing without opposition upon Alexandria.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:41.47,3:24:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}盖尔斯朱利斯凯撒？{\r}\NGaius Julius Caesar?
Dialogue: 0,3:24:44.60,3:24:47.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维篡夺了他的全名！{\r}\NSo now Octavian has stolen all of the name.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:47.85,3:24:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒阁下希望转达 他对女王毫无偏见{\r}\NCaesar wishes it known he has no quarrel with Cleopatra of Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:52.78,3:24:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那就叫他打道回府啊{\r}\NThen let him take his armies out of here and go home.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:56.36,3:25:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}战争或和平{\r}\NHe has charged me to say that the choice of war or peace...
Dialogue: 0,3:25:00.24,3:25:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}由埃及自行抉择{\r}\N...now rests with Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:01.78,3:25:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}至于他，他诚心希望和平{\r}\NAnd that for himself, he desires only peace.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:05.83,3:25:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他无条件讲和的要求是什么？{\r}\NAnd what are his terms for this unconditional peace?
Dialogue: 0,3:25:10.38,3:25:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一份小小的纪念品…{\r}\NA small token.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:13.05,3:25:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}以表示一点心意…{\r}\NA demonstration. A gesture.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:16.38,3:25:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}代表克莉奥佩特拉女王的诚意{\r}\NAn indication of Queen Cleopatra's goodwill and good faith.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:20.01,3:25:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维到底要什么？{\r}\NWhat does Octavian want?
Dialogue: 0,3:25:23.60,3:25:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}马克安东尼{\r}\NMarc Antony.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:28.39,3:25:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼{\r}\NThe...
Dialogue: 0,3:25:30.40,3:25:32.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}颈上的人头？{\r}\N...head of Marc Antony?
Dialogue: 0,3:25:49.92,3:25:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这个给他，作为我的答案{\r}\NTake this to him as my answer.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:55.00,3:25:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}埃及人很慷慨{\r}\NEgyptian generosity.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:57.51,3:26:01.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维要一个人头，我给他一对{\r}\NOctavian may have two heads for the price of one.
Dialogue: 0,3:26:01.59,3:26:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}要便要两个{\r}\NEither two...
Dialogue: 0,3:26:03.93,3:26:05.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}否则一个也没有{\r}\N...or none.
Dialogue: 0,3:26:54.11,3:26:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听说你来这儿睡觉{\r}\NI'm told you come here to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,3:26:57.69,3:26:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不是睡觉{\r}\NNot to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,3:26:59.94,3:27:01.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是度过漫漫长夜？{\r}\NTo pass the night then.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:01.95,3:27:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我并不寂寞{\r}\NI'm not alone.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:05.45,3:27:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}老人家与我交换历史{\r}\NThe old boy and I exchange memories of life.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:08.83,3:27:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}等于同屋主…或该说同墓主{\r}\NIt's like having a roommate, or should I say, "tomb-mate"?
Dialogue: 0,3:27:13.33,3:27:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若凯撒是你，他可会躲在这儿{\r}\NIf he were in your place, would I find Caesar here?
Dialogue: 0,3:27:16.75,3:27:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}身边只有月光和顾影自怜？{\r}\NHidden away, wrapped in moonlight and endless self-pity?
Dialogue: 0,3:27:20.88,3:27:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}又是自怜？找个新说法吧！{\r}\NSelf-pity again! You repeat yourself! Find new reproaches!
Dialogue: 0,3:27:24.01,3:27:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你只是借酒装疯{\r}\NUntil now it has just been a part of your being drunk.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:27.39,3:27:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为安东尼大唱悲歌{\r}\NSinging sad songs for Antony.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:29.77,3:27:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}时间应该用来与屋大维谈判{\r}\NYour time would be better spent negotiating with Octavian.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:35.65,3:27:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}把我的头交给亚格里巴吧 反正我也没什么损失{\r}\NWhy did you not give my head to Agrippa? It's no great loss to me.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:39.03,3:27:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听闻死第二次是不会痛的 还可以为你带来利益{\r}\NDying the second time is painless and possibly an advantage to you.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:43.15,3:27:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}或许能与罗马重缔盟约{\r}\NThe basis, perhaps, of a great new alliance with Rome.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:45.99,3:27:48.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不想跟罗马重缔盟约{\r}\NI do not want a great new alliance with Rome.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:49.24,3:27:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那你要什么？{\r}\NWhat do you want?
Dialogue: 0,3:27:52.29,3:27:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我是来找马克安东尼的{\r}\NI have come for Marc Antony.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:54.71,3:27:57.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的残兵、鲁非欧、我两母子{\r}\NWhat is left of his army, Rufio, my son and I...
Dialogue: 0,3:27:57.71,3:28:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}和全埃及都在等他{\r}\N...all of Egypt are waiting for him.
Dialogue: 0,3:28:01.13,3:28:03.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}时间无多了{\r}\NThere is little time.
Dialogue: 0,3:28:03.97,3:28:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}马克安东尼？{\r}\NMarc Antony?
Dialogue: 0,3:28:06.89,3:28:09.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这里没这个人{\r}\NThere is no one here by that name...
Dialogue: 0,3:28:10.18,3:28:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这活人{\r}\N...alive.
Dialogue: 0,3:28:31.04,3:28:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}什么时候？{\r}\NTime for what?
Dialogue: 0,3:28:34.33,3:28:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}等安东尼身穿盔甲{\r}\NFor Marc Antony to appear in shiny armor...
Dialogue: 0,3:28:37.33,3:28:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}双手握剑{\r}\N...swords flashing in both hands?
Dialogue: 0,3:28:39.71,3:28:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}亚格里巴、屋大维{\r}\NAgrippa. Octavian.
Dialogue: 0,3:28:41.67,3:28:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}站远些！ 庆祝吧！救世主安东尼来了！{\r}\NStand back! Rejoice! Marc Antony will save the day!
Dialogue: 0,3:28:52.72,3:28:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你说安东尼？{\r}\NAntony, you say?
Dialogue: 0,3:28:54.85,3:28:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他死于爱克提安{\r}\NHe died at Actium...
Dialogue: 0,3:28:57.40,3:28:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他逃走了{\r}\N...running away.
Dialogue: 0,3:28:59.81,3:29:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他想在水面行走{\r}\NHe tried to run on the water, the story goes...
Dialogue: 0,3:29:02.53,3:29:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但你拒绝扶他一把{\r}\N...but you weren't there to hold his hand!
Dialogue: 0,3:29:10.53,3:29:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}鲁非欧…我的部下…{\r}\NRufio, my legions, waiting.
Dialogue: 0,3:29:14.25,3:29:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们在等什么？{\r}\NFor what?
Dialogue: 0,3:29:16.66,3:29:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}等我问他们对我的看法{\r}\NTo ask me what they carry in their eyes...
Dialogue: 0,3:29:19.25,3:29:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还是我自己对自己的看法？{\r}\N...in their hearts, in their sleep, as I have in mine.
Dialogue: 0,3:29:22.00,3:29:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为什么你不壮烈牺牲？{\r}\NWhy are you not dead?
Dialogue: 0,3:29:25.09,3:29:27.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为什么不躲在深深的海底？{\r}\NWhy do you live? How can you live?
Dialogue: 0,3:29:27.34,3:29:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为什么{\r}\NWhy do you not lie in the deepest hole of the sea...
Dialogue: 0,3:29:30.64,3:29:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不光荣的战死？{\r}\N...bloodless and bloated and at peace with honorable death?
Dialogue: 0,3:29:42.77,3:29:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你因为逃跑而求我原谅{\r}\NYou begged forgiveness from me for running away.
Dialogue: 0,3:29:47.07,3:29:51.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}以母亲、一国之君的 身分向我哭诉原因{\r}\NYou wept and gave your reason. A mother to her child, a queen to her country.
Dialogue: 0,3:29:51.37,3:29:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但我能向谁哭诉，求谁谅解？{\r}\NWhere and how can I weep and beg? From whom?
Dialogue: 0,3:29:54.45,3:29:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谁？向千千万万死去的同袍？{\r}\NThe thousands and thousands who can no longer hear me?
Dialogue: 0,3:30:00.58,3:30:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我该解释吗？{\r}\NShall I give my reason?
Dialogue: 0,3:30:03.29,3:30:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还是简单一句：因为爱？{\r}\NShall I say simply, I loved?
Dialogue: 0,3:30:07.63,3:30:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当我看见你逃走时 我失去所有知觉{\r}\NWhen I saw you go, I saw nothing.
Dialogue: 0,3:30:09.72,3:30:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只关心你走了…{\r}\NFelt, heard, thought nothing except your going.
Dialogue: 0,3:30:12.76,3:30:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不理同袍生死 不关心埃及或罗马{\r}\NNot the dying and dead, not Rome, not Egypt...
Dialogue: 0,3:30:15.68,3:30:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不理胜败、荣誉 羞辱朋友敌人、过去未来{\r}\N...not victory or defeat, honor or disgrace...
Dialogue: 0,3:30:18.68,3:30:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只关心我的爱人走了 我一定要追随她{\r}\N...only that my love was going and I must be with her.
Dialogue: 0,3:30:22.15,3:30:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我的爱，我的主人在呼唤！{\r}\NThat my love, my master, called.
Dialogue: 0,3:30:25.48,3:30:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我只能紧紧追随{\r}\NAnd I followed.
Dialogue: 0,3:30:27.40,3:30:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}直到那时…{\r}\NAnd that only then...
Dialogue: 0,3:30:29.82,3:30:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我回头…{\r}\N...I looked back...
Dialogue: 0,3:30:32.99,3:30:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}了解…{\r}\N...and I saw.
Dialogue: 0,3:30:46.88,3:30:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你以前说得多么正确{\r}\NHow right you were.
Dialogue: 0,3:30:49.92,3:30:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}假如爱…{\r}\N"Have as your master anyone, anything...
Dialogue: 0,3:30:55.26,3:30:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}从不是你的主人{\r}\N...but never love."
Dialogue: 0,3:30:58.39,3:31:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我错了{\r}\NHow wrong.
Dialogue: 0,3:31:00.43,3:31:02.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}大错特错{\r}\NHow wrong I was.
Dialogue: 0,3:31:03.73,3:31:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼，你追随的爱在这里{\r}\NAntony, the love you followed is here.
Dialogue: 0,3:31:08.44,3:31:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}作为对罗马帝国的献礼？{\r}\NTo be had upon payment of an empire.
Dialogue: 0,3:31:10.99,3:31:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没有你{\r}\NWithout you, Antony...
Dialogue: 0,3:31:13.74,3:31:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不想活在这世上{\r}\N...this is not a world I want to live in...
Dialogue: 0,3:31:16.99,3:31:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}更别论东征西讨了{\r}\N...much less conquer.
Dialogue: 0,3:31:21.25,3:31:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}因为世上{\r}\NBecause for me...
Dialogue: 0,3:31:23.87,3:31:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}再也找不到爱{\r}\N...there would be no love anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,3:31:29.09,3:31:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你想的话，我陪你一齐死{\r}\NDo you want me to die with you? I will.
Dialogue: 0,3:31:34.09,3:31:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还是你愿意与我活下去？{\r}\NOr do you want me to live with you?
Dialogue: 0,3:31:38.93,3:31:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}那要看你如何抉择{\r}\NWhatever you choose.
Dialogue: 0,3:31:54.86,3:31:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}选择活下去…会否太迟了？{\r}\NAre we too late, do you think, if we choose to live?
Dialogue: 0,3:31:59.33,3:32:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}永远{\r}\NBetter too late...
Dialogue: 0,3:32:01.70,3:32:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}也不嫌迟{\r}\N...than never.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:03.93,3:33:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}城里流传一个恐怖的传闻{\r}\NMy lady, there is disturbing news from the city.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:06.94,3:33:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有人吓得离开了家园{\r}\NThe people are frightened. Some are beginning to leave their homes.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:11.48,3:33:15.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}有人在晚上到处张贴传单{\r}\NDuring the night, hundreds of notices were secretly posted everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:15.32,3:33:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}早上发现被贴在市集{\r}\NThey were found stuck up in the marketplace.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:18.20,3:33:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}甚至庙墙上也有涂鸦{\r}\NEven painted on temples and other holy places.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:21.08,3:33:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}署名屋大维盖尔斯朱利斯凯撒{\r}\NSigned by Octavian Gaius Julius Caesar Augustus...
Dialogue: 0,3:33:26.79,3:33:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}答应只要投降 就不会受伤害{\r}\N...promising the Egyptian people peace if they surrender to him...
Dialogue: 0,3:33:30.84,3:33:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若不投降，就只有死路一条{\r}\N...and destruction if they do not.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:33.05,3:33:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我已下令清除所有传单{\r}\NI've had all of the notices removed and I've ordered the death penalty...
Dialogue: 0,3:33:36.76,3:33:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}并将散播谣言 说安东尼的部队将谋反的人处死{\r}\N...for anyone who spreads the false rumors that Antony's men might desert him.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:42.10,3:33:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若谣传属实，将处什么刑罚？{\r}\NAnd what penalty if the rumors might come true?
Dialogue: 0,3:33:47.77,3:33:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你怎么知道？{\r}\NHow do you know?
Dialogue: 0,3:33:49.94,3:33:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我了解罗马人{\r}\NI know the Romans.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:52.23,3:33:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只有一种将军不会被遗弃{\r}\NThere is only one commander they will never desert.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:55.53,3:33:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他的名字叫胜利{\r}\NHis name is "Victory."
Dialogue: 0,3:33:58.70,3:34:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但你才刚刚让安东尼离开似乎…{\r}\NBut yet, just now, you let Lord Antony go as if--
Dialogue: 0,3:34:07.16,3:34:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若你见过他，他一如以往{\r}\NIf you could have seen him, how proud he was...
Dialogue: 0,3:34:11.54,3:34:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}气宇轩昂{\r}\N...unafraid...
Dialogue: 0,3:34:14.71,3:34:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}毫无惧色{\r}\N...as he used to be.
Dialogue: 0,3:34:18.09,3:34:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我的部下都自由了吗？ 他们都离开了吗？{\r}\NAll of my attendants, have they been given their freedom? Have they gone?
Dialogue: 0,3:34:22.47,3:34:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还没有，他们还想再打扫一遍{\r}\NYes. They wanted once more to tidy up.
Dialogue: 0,3:34:25.56,3:34:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维可以自己来打扫啊{\r}\NOctavian can do his own housecleaning.
Dialogue: 0,3:34:28.48,3:34:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}叫侍卫队长带三个精兵过来{\r}\NThe captain of the guards and three of his best men are to report to me...
Dialogue: 0,3:34:32.98,3:34:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在先假扮成商人{\r}\N...disguised as merchants.
Dialogue: 0,3:34:35.02,3:34:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}保护凯撒里奥{\r}\NThey are to escort Caesarion out of Egypt...
Dialogue: 0,3:34:39.45,3:34:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}离开埃及{\r}\N...for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,3:34:41.74,3:34:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}陛下，你自己呢？{\r}\NAnd you?
Dialogue: 0,3:34:43.70,3:34:45.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}请再三考虑{\r}\NYour Majesty, please reconsider.
Dialogue: 0,3:34:46.20,3:34:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}尤法诺有两艘快艇在东面港口{\r}\NThere are two of Euphranor's ships, very fast, in the east harbor.
Dialogue: 0,3:34:49.62,3:34:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将我包在地毯里带上船？{\r}\NAnd would you roll me on board in a carpet?
Dialogue: 0,3:34:53.29,3:34:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不{\r}\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,3:34:55.34,3:35:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}再也没有凯撒可以找了 至少我已找不到我的凯撒了{\r}\NThere are no more Caesars to go to, at least not for me.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:00.63,3:35:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 那么你还是打算要… - 留在亚历山卓{\r}\N-Then it is still your intention-- -To remain in Alexandria.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:05.05,3:35:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}躲在最难找的地方{\r}\NIn the last possible place anyone would look.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:09.02,3:35:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}躲在最没可能的地方{\r}\NLiterally, the last possible place.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:13.10,3:35:16.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}陛下，我从不怀疑你的决定…{\r}\NYour Majesty, I have never questioned your decisions.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:16.61,3:35:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在不是讨论这问题的时候{\r}\NThis is not the time to begin.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:18.65,3:35:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}让我留下来陪你{\r}\NLet me stay with you.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:20.44,3:35:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}夏蜜安和艾拉会照顾我{\r}\NCharmian and Eiras will look after me.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:23.16,3:35:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}万一安东尼回来…{\r}\NIf Lord Antony should--
Dialogue: 0,3:35:27.33,3:35:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼回来时{\r}\NWhen Lord Antony returns...
Dialogue: 0,3:35:30.79,3:35:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你到这里告诉他我的下落{\r}\N...you will be here to tell him where to find me...
Dialogue: 0,3:35:34.04,3:35:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我等他{\r}\N...waiting for him.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:37.21,3:35:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}再一起想个…{\r}\NTogether, we will then do...
Dialogue: 0,3:35:39.67,3:35:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}最好的办法{\r}\N...what he thinks best.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:41.92,3:35:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听清楚了吗？{\r}\NIs that clear?
Dialogue: 0,3:35:46.30,3:35:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 清楚了 - 还有其他事吗？{\r}\N-Yes, my lady. -Was there anything more?
Dialogue: 0,3:35:51.85,3:35:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我一直深爱着你{\r}\NI have always loved you.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:55.52,3:35:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我早就知道了{\r}\NAnd I have always known.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:10.24,3:36:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马从没见过这种军队！ 我们应该挑战整个亚洲{\r}\NRome has never known such an army. We should be taking on all of Asia.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:14.92,3:36:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屠杀安东尼的老弱残兵 简直是浪费时间{\r}\NIt seems a waste to slaughter what's left of Antony's army and Antony.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:19.50,3:36:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不会有屠杀，甚至不用流血{\r}\NThere will be no slaughter. I doubt there will be even bloodshed.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:23.55,3:36:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不费一兵一卒算打胜仗吗？我很怀疑{\r}\NHas a battle ever been won without a blow being struck? I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:28.64,3:36:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我再重申一次{\r}\NAt any rate, let me make it clear once more.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:31.97,3:36:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}要活捉安东尼 她也一样{\r}\NI want Antony alive, and I want her alive.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:36.19,3:36:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我要留活口{\r}\NShe must be taken alive.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:41.61,3:36:44.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉第二次到罗马{\r}\NQueen Cleopatra's second procession into Rome...
Dialogue: 0,3:36:44.82,3:36:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}盛况将胜过第一次{\r}\N...will surpass her first.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:59.88,3:37:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你父亲给你的戒指…{\r}\NThe ring your father gave you.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:03.80,3:37:05.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在{\r}\NIt is yours now...
Dialogue: 0,3:37:05.92,3:37:07.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}交给你了{\r}\N...to keep.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:07.89,3:37:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}光荣骄傲的戴上它{\r}\NWear it with pride and with honor.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:12.18,3:37:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我很害怕…{\r}\NI'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:14.02,3:37:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}虽然我知道我不应害怕{\r}\NI know I shouldn't be.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:16.73,3:37:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}谁说的？{\r}\NWho told you that?
Dialogue: 0,3:37:18.69,3:37:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}天下的国王{\r}\NAll kings...
Dialogue: 0,3:37:20.86,3:37:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}特别是女王，都会害怕{\r}\N...and especially queens, are afraid.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:24.07,3:37:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}与其他人不同的是{\r}\NThey just manage not to show it.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:27.32,3:37:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们会尽量掩饰{\r}\NSomething ordinary people cannot do.
Dialogue: 0,3:38:28.88,3:38:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}敬你，安东尼！{\r}\NHail Antony!
Dialogue: 0,3:38:54.12,3:38:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 离屋大维多远？ - 很近了，在山那边{\r}\N-How near is Octavian? -Very near. Over that low ridge.
Dialogue: 0,3:38:57.66,3:39:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}天黑后，他的营火会照亮天空{\r}\NAs it grows darker, the glow from his campfires will light up the sky.
Dialogue: 0,3:39:07.05,3:39:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们的部队一定想看看{\r}\NOur troops must find it attractive to watch.
Dialogue: 0,3:39:11.43,3:39:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}对我们招手呢{\r}\NInviting, even.
Dialogue: 0,3:39:13.14,3:39:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼的部队自己生火取暖{\r}\NAntony's legions warm themselves at their own fires.
Dialogue: 0,3:39:16.35,3:39:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是啊{\r}\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,3:39:18.31,3:39:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}骑马经过都觉得暖{\r}\NI could feel the warmth as I rode by.
Dialogue: 0,3:39:22.77,3:39:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 他有多少个军团？ - 二十个{\r}\N-How many legions has he? -Twenty.
Dialogue: 0,3:39:25.02,3:39:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 我们呢？ - 两个，是第十二军团，另一个是…{\r}\N-And we? -Two. The 12th and one made up--
Dialogue: 0,3:39:27.98,3:39:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}由各军团的残兵组成{\r}\NMade up from what was left of the others.
Dialogue: 0,3:39:30.65,3:39:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我记得凯撒以两个军团打赢亚历山卓{\r}\NAs I remember it, Caesar held Alexandria with two.
Dialogue: 0,3:39:39.12,3:39:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}鲁非欧，他们怎样部署？{\r}\NHow are they deployed? Rufio.
Dialogue: 0,3:39:45.00,3:39:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}骑兵分置左右，中央是步兵{\r}\NCavalry to the left, cavalry to the right, infantry to the center.
Dialogue: 0,3:39:49.51,3:39:54.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}另有三头大象虚张声势{\r}\NThree elephants deployed to stamp out a fly.
Dialogue: 0,3:39:54.97,3:39:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋大维和亚格里巴{\r}\NMy lords Octavian and Agrippa have all the strategic brilliance...
Dialogue: 0,3:39:59.26,3:40:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}比小女孩更不懂战术{\r}\N...of two vestal virgins.
Dialogue: 0,3:40:01.81,3:40:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们退至这边地质较软的地方{\r}\NWe can draw back here to softer ground...
Dialogue: 0,3:40:04.14,3:40:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}以瘫痪他的骑兵 然后与步兵决一死战{\r}\N...too soft for cavalry and make our stand against their infantry.
Dialogue: 0,3:40:06.98,3:40:11.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}决战？给他们踩扁？不！ 扣住大象{\r}\NStand? And let them stamp on us? No. Let the elephants stand.
Dialogue: 0,3:40:11.28,3:40:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们打游击战{\r}\NWe flies will bite and buzz and tickle.
Dialogue: 0,3:40:15.07,3:40:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}黎明第一道阳光升起时{\r}\NAt the first light of day...
Dialogue: 0,3:40:17.32,3:40:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}趁屋大维的营火仍照亮天空{\r}\N...while Octavian's glow still lights up the sky...
Dialogue: 0,3:40:21.54,3:40:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们就发动攻击{\r}\N...we will attack.
Dialogue: 0,3:40:26.04,3:40:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}日落时，我军阵容将会加强{\r}\NBy sunset, both our loyal legions will have grown larger...
Dialogue: 0,3:40:29.55,3:40:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}并更加忠心，我保证{\r}\N...and even more loyal, I promise you.
Dialogue: 0,3:40:33.38,3:40:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}晚安{\r}\NGood night.
Dialogue: 0,3:40:44.18,3:40:47.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}鲁非欧，吩咐卫兵{\r}\NRufio, tell the guards, please...
Dialogue: 0,3:40:47.35,3:40:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}天亮前叫醒我{\r}\N...I am to be awakened just before dawn.
Dialogue: 0,3:40:49.90,3:40:51.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当然{\r}\NOf course.
Dialogue: 0,3:40:51.32,3:40:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}鲁非欧{\r}\NAnd, Rufio...
Dialogue: 0,3:40:54.07,3:40:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}万一卫兵忘了或计错时间{\r}\N...if, for whatever reason, the guards should forget or misjudge the time...
Dialogue: 0,3:40:59.45,3:41:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}请你亲自来叫我{\r}\N...will you, yourself, wake me?
Dialogue: 0,3:41:01.58,3:41:03.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}卫兵会负责叫你{\r}\NThe guards will wake you.
Dialogue: 0,3:41:06.12,3:41:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 万一呢？ - 那么我会来，不要怕{\r}\N-But if they don't? -Then I will. Never fear.
Dialogue: 0,3:41:09.75,3:41:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我从来都不怕{\r}\NI never fear.
Dialogue: 0,3:41:17.05,3:41:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}再也不会怕了{\r}\NNot anymore.
Dialogue: 0,3:42:18.65,3:42:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}鲁非欧！{\r}\NRufio!
Dialogue: 0,3:43:34.19,3:43:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}鲁非欧…{\r}\NRufio.
Dialogue: 0,3:45:59.12,3:46:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}出手啊！{\r}\NFight!
Dialogue: 0,3:46:02.71,3:46:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}出手啊！{\r}\NFight!
Dialogue: 0,3:46:10.72,3:46:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}出手啊…{\r}\NFight!
Dialogue: 0,3:46:16.85,3:46:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为什么不出手？{\r}\NWhy don't you fight?
Dialogue: 0,3:46:43.71,3:46:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}难道没一个人愿意成全安东尼{\r}\NIs there no one who would grant Antony...
Dialogue: 0,3:46:46.80,3:46:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}光荣战死的心愿？{\r}\N...an honorable way to die?
Dialogue: 0,3:47:11.91,3:47:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在我之前…{\r}\NBefore me...
Dialogue: 0,3:47:14.37,3:47:19.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}它的主人是位被罗马杀死的罗马人{\r}\N...this was carried by another Roman killed by Rome.
Dialogue: 0,3:47:19.25,3:47:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}另一位{\r}\NAnother...
Dialogue: 0,3:47:21.54,3:47:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒{\r}\N...Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,3:47:32.76,3:47:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不{\r}\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,3:47:35.05,3:47:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他跑不了的{\r}\NWe will have him.
Dialogue: 0,3:47:38.10,3:47:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}等着一箭双雕吧！{\r}\NWe will have them both together.
Dialogue: 0,3:49:21.95,3:49:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她在哪儿？{\r}\NWhere is she?
Dialogue: 0,3:49:25.33,3:49:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她在哪儿？{\r}\NWhere is she?
Dialogue: 0,3:49:28.29,3:49:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}陛下要我转告你{\r}\NHer Majesty said to tell you...
Dialogue: 0,3:49:30.67,3:49:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她躲在最难找的地方{\r}\N...she can be found in the last possible place anyone would look.
Dialogue: 0,3:49:37.38,3:49:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}躲在最无可能的地方{\r}\NLiterally, the last possible place.
Dialogue: 0,3:49:46.60,3:49:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她可能在等我{\r}\NShe might have waited.
Dialogue: 0,3:49:48.73,3:49:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉{\r}\NOnce more, it seems...
Dialogue: 0,3:49:51.56,3:49:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}再次消失了踪影{\r}\N...Cleopatra is out of reach...
Dialogue: 0,3:49:55.69,3:49:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我还是要紧随在后{\r}\N...and I must hurry after.
Dialogue: 0,3:49:58.53,3:50:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}终其一生{\r}\NThroughout life...
Dialogue: 0,3:50:00.78,3:50:02.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}甚至生命以外{\r}\N...and now beyond.
Dialogue: 0,3:50:02.83,3:50:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一个女人，我唯一的爱{\r}\NOne woman, one love!
Dialogue: 0,3:50:10.21,3:50:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}从未曾改变{\r}\NNothing changes...
Dialogue: 0,3:50:13.00,3:50:15.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}至死不渝{\r}\N...except life into death.
Dialogue: 0,3:50:24.56,3:50:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}助我一臂之力{\r}\NWill you help me?
Dialogue: 0,3:50:31.90,3:50:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}请杀了我，阿波罗德斯！{\r}\NHelp me to die, Apollodorus!
Dialogue: 0,3:50:33.90,3:50:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我很想那样做{\r}\NI want to!
Dialogue: 0,3:50:36.61,3:50:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但我不能！{\r}\NBut I can't.
Dialogue: 0,3:50:53.29,3:50:56.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我时常羡慕鲁非欧{\r}\NI've always envied Rufio...
Dialogue: 0,3:50:56.80,3:50:59.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}鲁非欧有对长手臂{\r}\N...his long arms.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:17.65,3:51:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只有永远的…{\r}\NThe ultimate desertion:
Dialogue: 0,3:51:20.45,3:51:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}背弃自己{\r}\NI from myself.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:22.99,3:51:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}否则我怎会错失 尽一生去追求的目标？{\r}\NElse, how could I have missed what I must have aimed for all my life?
Dialogue: 0,3:51:29.12,3:51:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}可以给我痛快一次吗？{\r}\NWill you finish me now?
Dialogue: 0,3:51:32.54,3:51:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我的剑呢？请你了结我吧{\r}\NWhere is my sword? I beg you to finish me.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:36.54,3:51:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我骗你的，女王还在生{\r}\NI lied to you. I let you think the queen is dead.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:39.67,3:51:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在陵寝里等你{\r}\NBut she's alive in her tomb, waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:44.59,3:51:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}克莉奥佩特拉在等我？{\r}\NCleopatra waiting?
Dialogue: 0,3:51:48.26,3:51:52.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你帮我{\r}\NThere will be just enough time...
Dialogue: 0,3:51:52.44,3:51:54.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}还来得及{\r}\N...if you'll help me.
Dialogue: 0,3:52:53.83,3:52:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}把伤口紧紧绑住{\r}\NPerhaps, my lady, if we were to bind his wounds tightly....
Dialogue: 0,3:52:57.46,3:53:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}可能只会增加痛苦，让他睡吧{\r}\NIt would only give him pain. Let him sleep.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:14.06,3:53:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}睡神{\r}\NSleep.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:16.85,3:53:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}今晚请降临{\r}\NWill you come tonight...
Dialogue: 0,3:53:20.15,3:53:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}赐我一夜安眠{\r}\N...so that I can sleep?
Dialogue: 0,3:53:23.40,3:53:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}无尽黑夜的沉睡{\r}\NThe dark sleep.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:28.57,3:53:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们终于见面了{\r}\NThey did meet after all...
Dialogue: 0,3:53:31.62,3:53:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}相爱的人们{\r}\N...the lovers.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:34.20,3:53:36.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他们会长伴左右{\r}\NThey will always meet.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:37.79,3:53:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为我活下去{\r}\NBe lonely for me.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:40.63,3:53:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}好的，但不能太久{\r}\NBut not for very long.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:43.21,3:53:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我保证{\r}\NI promise.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:47.63,3:53:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一直以为我会…{\r}\NI thought always I would die...
Dialogue: 0,3:53:50.35,3:53:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}死得其所{\r}\N...so well...
Dialogue: 0,3:53:53.85,3:53:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}身为战士{\r}\N...as becomes a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:58.19,3:54:00.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}死得像个勇士{\r}\NA soldier's death.
Dialogue: 0,3:54:02.27,3:54:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我以为我活得名符其实{\r}\NI lived always as I saw fit.
Dialogue: 0,3:54:08.15,3:54:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}其实名过其实{\r}\NUnfittingly.
Dialogue: 0,3:54:10.37,3:54:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我想死后再来补偿{\r}\NI would make it up, I thought, in death.
Dialogue: 0,3:54:14.58,3:54:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}无论死后或生前{\r}\NI expected--
Dialogue: 0,3:54:17.37,3:54:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我都…{\r}\NI expected too much of me in death...
Dialogue: 0,3:54:20.92,3:54:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}期望过高{\r}\N...as in life.
Dialogue: 0,3:54:23.42,3:54:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你抱着我吗？{\r}\NAre you holding me?
Dialogue: 0,3:54:25.80,3:54:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}从来没有抱得那么紧{\r}\NNever so closely.
Dialogue: 0,3:54:28.38,3:54:30.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}再抱紧一点{\r}\NEven closer.
Dialogue: 0,3:54:32.97,3:54:35.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我们一起证明{\r}\NYou and I will prove death...
Dialogue: 0,3:54:35.93,3:54:38.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}死比相爱容易得多{\r}\N...so much less than love.
Dialogue: 0,3:54:40.94,3:54:42.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你和我，我们会…{\r}\NYou and I, we will--
Dialogue: 0,3:54:43.65,3:54:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}证明死…{\r}\NWe'll make of dying...
Dialogue: 0,3:54:46.28,3:54:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只不过是…{\r}\N...nothing more than one...
Dialogue: 0,3:54:49.74,3:54:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}最后的…{\r}\N...last...
Dialogue: 0,3:54:52.41,3:54:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}拥抱{\r}\N...embrace.
Dialogue: 0,3:54:59.62,3:55:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}吻我{\r}\NA kiss...
Dialogue: 0,3:55:03.38,3:55:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}封住我最后一口气{\r}\N...to take my breath away.
Dialogue: 0,3:55:25.86,3:55:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}世界从未…{\r}\NThere has never been...
Dialogue: 0,3:55:29.15,3:55:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如此寂静{\r}\N...such a silence.
Dialogue: 0,3:56:16.12,3:56:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将他转过来{\r}\NTurn him over.
Dialogue: 0,3:56:24.29,3:56:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}古怪的民族毒药闻起来像香水{\r}\NStrange people. Poisons that smell like perfume.
Dialogue: 0,3:56:28.54,3:56:32.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}多找一点用重伤的人做试验{\r}\NFind more. Have it analyzed. Test it on one of the badly wounded.
Dialogue: 0,3:56:38.68,3:56:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}阁下，找到克莉奥佩特拉了{\r}\NMy lord, they have found Queen Cleopatra.
Dialogue: 0,3:56:41.93,3:56:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她将自己锁在陵墓里{\r}\NShe is locked in a building, that is to say, a tomb.
Dialogue: 0,3:56:44.73,3:56:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}快{\r}\NHurry.
Dialogue: 0,3:56:52.07,3:56:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼与她在一起，已经死了{\r}\NOh, Marc Antony is with her, they say. He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,3:56:58.70,3:57:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}- 什么？ - 安东尼阁下死了{\r}\N-What? -Lord Antony is dead.
Dialogue: 0,3:57:03.96,3:57:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就这样轻松地说出口吗？{\r}\NIs that how one says it?
Dialogue: 0,3:57:07.58,3:57:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就这样轻松{\r}\NAs simply as that.
Dialogue: 0,3:57:11.17,3:57:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}马克安东尼死了{\r}\NMarc Antony is dead.
Dialogue: 0,3:57:14.84,3:57:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼阁下死了{\r}\NLord Antony is dead.
Dialogue: 0,3:57:19.30,3:57:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就像说汤很热或汤凉了{\r}\NThe soup is hot. The soup is cold.
Dialogue: 0,3:57:23.10,3:57:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼活着…安东尼死了{\r}\NAntony is living. Antony is dead.
Dialogue: 0,3:57:28.98,3:57:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}说这话时，你应吓得发抖！{\r}\NShake with terror when such words pass your lips...
Dialogue: 0,3:57:32.73,3:57:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如果有错，安东尼会割你的舌头{\r}\N...for fear they be untrue and Antony cut out your tongue for the lie!
Dialogue: 0,3:57:37.11,3:57:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若真的如此{\r}\NAnd if true...
Dialogue: 0,3:57:39.20,3:57:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}则够你吹捧一辈子{\r}\N...for your lifetime boast...
Dialogue: 0,3:57:41.70,3:57:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你三生有幸，宣布他的死亡{\r}\N...that you were honored to speak his name even in death.
Dialogue: 0,3:57:46.29,3:57:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}宣布这人的死{\r}\NThe dying of such a man...
Dialogue: 0,3:57:49.25,3:57:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}应该哭喊{\r}\N...must be shouted.
Dialogue: 0,3:57:51.96,3:57:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}大叫{\r}\NScreamed.
Dialogue: 0,3:57:54.01,3:57:58.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}直到宇宙彼方传来回响{\r}\NIt must echo back from the corners of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,3:57:59.43,3:58:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼已死！{\r}\NAntony is dead!
Dialogue: 0,3:58:02.81,3:58:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马巨头马克安东尼气绝身亡！{\r}\NMarc Antony of Rome lives no more!
Dialogue: 0,3:58:29.04,3:58:31.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}凯撒面前，你无须低头{\r}\NYou needn't lower your head before Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:32.46,3:58:34.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我并未低头{\r}\NI never did.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:34.71,3:58:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}若他真的在此我会乐意低头{\r}\NBut if he were here, I'd be happy to.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:37.42,3:58:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我就是凯撒{\r}\NI am Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:40.09,3:58:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}随你高兴，屋大维{\r}\NIf it pleases you, Octavian.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:43.89,3:58:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}看着我！{\r}\NLook at me.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:45.89,3:58:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}随你高兴{\r}\NIf it pleases you.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:50.60,3:58:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}历尽沧桑、战乱…{\r}\NAfter all this time and all that has happened...
Dialogue: 0,3:58:54.36,3:58:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你依旧明艳动人{\r}\N...I suppose you are still beautiful, in a way.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:58.69,3:59:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}多谢赞赏{\r}\NYou flatter me.
Dialogue: 0,3:59:00.36,3:59:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我是客观不带感情的说 别想歪了{\r}\NMy interest is impersonal. Should you have any intention--
Dialogue: 0,3:59:04.08,3:59:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在你是在奉承自己{\r}\NNow you flatter yourself.
Dialogue: 0,3:59:06.20,3:59:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}战争结束了{\r}\NThe fighting is over.
Dialogue: 0,3:59:09.00,3:59:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你的国家、财产、以及你本人 都是我的战利品{\r}\NYour country, your possessions and you are mine by right of conquest.
Dialogue: 0,3:59:13.25,3:59:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我准许你继续统治埃及 作为罗马的一省{\r}\NI will permit you to rule Egypt as a Roman province and return your possessions.
Dialogue: 0,3:59:18.05,3:59:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}只有一个条件 首先，你陪我回罗马{\r}\NThere is one condition. You will first accompany me to Rome.
Dialogue: 0,3:59:23.09,3:59:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}跟在你的战车后面？{\r}\NBehind your chariot?
Dialogue: 0,3:59:25.14,3:59:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}看着我！{\r}\NLook at me!
Dialogue: 0,3:59:33.31,3:59:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}高傲的罗马人会否有耐心 在烈日下等几个小时{\r}\NWould the proud citizens of Rome wait for hours in the hot sun...
Dialogue: 0,3:59:37.40,3:59:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}看我的尸体被拖过广场？{\r}\N...to see my dead body dragged through the Forum?
Dialogue: 0,3:59:40.95,3:59:42.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我会严密监视你{\r}\NI'll have you closely watched.
Dialogue: 0,3:59:44.82,3:59:46.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}屋太维雅…{\r}\NOctavian...
Dialogue: 0,3:59:46.87,3:59:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}当我决心一死{\r}\N...when I am ready to die...
Dialogue: 0,3:59:50.66,3:59:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就一定会死{\r}\N...I will die.
Dialogue: 0,4:00:06.10,4:00:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如果我答应你{\r}\NWhat if I promise no harm will come to you...
Dialogue: 0,4:00:08.81,4:00:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}丝毫无损的回亚历山卓呢？{\r}\N...that you will be returned safely to Alexandria?
Dialogue: 0,4:00:11.56,4:00:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}看着我！{\r}\NLook at me!
Dialogue: 0,4:00:15.98,4:00:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你还可以要求什么？{\r}\NWhat more could you ask?
Dialogue: 0,4:00:22.24,4:00:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你还没提到{\r}\NYou have not spoken...
Dialogue: 0,4:00:24.20,4:00:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我儿子{\r}\N...of my son.
Dialogue: 0,4:00:26.41,4:00:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你儿子？我忘了{\r}\NYour son. I'd forgotten him.
Dialogue: 0,4:00:29.91,4:00:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他在哪？{\r}\NWhere is he?
Dialogue: 0,4:00:31.50,4:00:33.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}在安全的地方{\r}\NSafe.
Dialogue: 0,4:00:35.83,4:00:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}如果我答应你去罗马{\r}\NIf I go with you to Rome...
Dialogue: 0,4:00:40.00,4:00:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你肯让我儿子统治埃及？{\r}\N...would you permit my son to rule Egypt?
Dialogue: 0,4:00:43.38,4:00:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我儿子的儿子…{\r}\NAnd his sons?
Dialogue: 0,4:00:45.34,4:00:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}世世代代统治下去{\r}\NAnd theirs?
Dialogue: 0,4:00:47.22,4:00:49.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我尽力而为{\r}\NI'll do everything I can.
Dialogue: 0,4:00:49.76,4:00:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这是罗马皇帝{\r}\NDo I have your word...
Dialogue: 0,4:00:52.27,4:00:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}和神的承诺？{\r}\N...as a Roman emperor and god?
Dialogue: 0,4:00:57.52,4:00:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是的{\r}\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,4:01:01.23,4:01:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}何时出发？{\r}\NWhen will you require me to go?
Dialogue: 0,4:01:03.49,4:01:05.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}尽快{\r}\NAs soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,4:01:07.36,4:01:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我很疲倦 需要休息{\r}\NAt the moment, I am very tired and would like to rest.
Dialogue: 0,4:01:11.24,4:01:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}请离开{\r}\NIf you'll leave me now.
Dialogue: 0,4:01:13.04,4:01:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你答应{\r}\NDo I have your word...
Dialogue: 0,4:01:15.92,4:01:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不会自残？{\r}\N...that you will not harm yourself in any way?
Dialogue: 0,4:01:19.71,4:01:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我以…{\r}\NI swear it.
Dialogue: 0,4:01:23.59,4:01:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}儿子的性命担保{\r}\NOn the life of my son.
Dialogue: 0,4:01:35.89,4:01:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}卫兵一定要守在里面吗？{\r}\NMust the guards remain inside?
Dialogue: 0,4:01:38.60,4:01:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我发过誓了{\r}\NI have sworn...
Dialogue: 0,4:01:40.77,4:01:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}用我儿子…{\r}\N...after all...
Dialogue: 0,4:01:43.53,4:01:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}担保{\r}\N...on the life of my son.
Dialogue: 0,4:01:57.29,4:02:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在，应该准备出发了{\r}\NAnd now I must make ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:00.54,4:02:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}没什么要准备的{\r}\NThere's little to do.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:03.34,4:02:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}首先，我要吃饱{\r}\NFirst, I shall want something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:07.59,4:02:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}路上才有力气{\r}\NSomething to sustain me on my way.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:11.26,4:02:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}水果可以吗？{\r}\NSome fruit, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,4:02:13.18,4:02:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}拿来{\r}\NBring it to me.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:17.10,4:02:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}夏蜜安！{\r}\NCharmian.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:21.94,4:02:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}艾拉，你拿{\r}\NYou then, Eiras.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:25.03,4:02:27.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你一直让我们跟在身边{\r}\NYou have never been without us.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:28.61,4:02:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}不要留下我们{\r}\NYou cannot leave us behind.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:31.45,4:02:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}或许…{\r}\NPerhaps...
Dialogue: 0,4:02:34.03,4:02:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}够我们三个一起{\r}\N...there may be enough for us all.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:37.33,4:02:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}拿张便条给我{\r}\NBring me a tablet to write on.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:39.92,4:02:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}留言给屋大维{\r}\NI want a message brought to Octavian.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:42.25,4:02:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}留这给这种人是浪费{\r}\NWords are wasted on such a man.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:45.05,4:02:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}反正已经浪费了太多 在许多男人身上{\r}\NI have wasted so many on so many men.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:49.22,4:02:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这是我最后一个请求{\r}\NA few more. One last request.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:52.22,4:02:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}你认为他会答应吗？{\r}\NWill he grant it, do you think?
Dialogue: 0,4:02:55.10,4:02:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我不知道{\r}\NI may never know.
Dialogue: 0,4:02:59.98,4:03:02.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}既然如此{\r}\NIn this case...
Dialogue: 0,4:03:03.23,4:03:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我应该…{\r}\N...I think I shall.
Dialogue: 0,4:03:13.24,4:03:16.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我会继续服侍陛下{\r}\NI will serve Her Majesty as always.
Dialogue: 0,4:03:16.29,4:03:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一向是我服侍她{\r}\NI have always served her.
Dialogue: 0,4:03:18.33,4:03:20.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}两个都等着{\r}\NYou will both wait...
Dialogue: 0,4:03:20.83,4:03:23.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}为我更衣{\r}\N...to dress me for my travels.
Dialogue: 0,4:03:23.96,4:03:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我要穿第一次{\r}\NI will wear--
Dialogue: 0,4:03:27.59,4:03:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}跟安东尼见面时穿的服装{\r}\NI want to be as Antony first saw me.
Dialogue: 0,4:03:30.80,4:03:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}黄金制造的衣服{\r}\NThe dress of gold?
Dialogue: 0,4:03:33.47,4:03:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}他一眼…{\r}\NHe must know at once...
Dialogue: 0,4:03:35.72,4:03:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就可以认出我{\r}\N...even from a great distance...
Dialogue: 0,4:03:38.39,4:03:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}就算距离很远也认得出来{\r}\N...that it is I.
Dialogue: 0,4:03:41.69,4:03:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这是你的最后一项任务{\r}\NThis will be the last thing you do.
Dialogue: 0,4:03:44.36,4:03:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}将这给门外的守卫转交屋大维{\r}\NDrop this to one of the guards outside for Octavian.
Dialogue: 0,4:03:49.11,4:03:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}但是要等过些时候{\r}\NBut be sure to wait.
Dialogue: 0,4:04:10.67,4:04:14.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在来试试无花果该有的味道{\r}\NAnd now let me see if the figs are as they should be.
Dialogue: 0,4:04:42.25,4:04:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}听说这东西效果强烈{\r}\NThe taste of these, they say, is sharp...
Dialogue: 0,4:04:45.29,4:04:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}而快速{\r}\N...and swiftly over.
Dialogue: 0,4:04:53.09,4:04:56.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我多么清醒啊{\r}\NHow strangely awake I feel.
Dialogue: 0,4:04:56.93,4:05:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}生命好像一场漫长的梦{\r}\NAs if living had been just a long dream.
Dialogue: 0,4:05:02.18,4:05:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}别人的梦{\r}\NSomeone else's dream.
Dialogue: 0,4:05:05.31,4:05:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}此时终于要结束了{\r}\NNow finished at last.
Dialogue: 0,4:05:13.69,4:05:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}现在{\r}\NBut then now...
Dialogue: 0,4:05:16.16,4:05:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}应该开始…{\r}\N...will begin...
Dialogue: 0,4:05:19.24,4:05:21.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我自己的梦了{\r}\N...a dream of my own...
Dialogue: 0,4:05:23.70,4:05:25.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}一场永不醒来的梦{\r}\N...which will never end.
Dialogue: 0,4:05:28.92,4:05:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼{\r}\NAntony?
Dialogue: 0,4:05:34.01,4:05:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}安东尼，等我{\r}\NAntony, wait.
Dialogue: 0,4:05:49.73,4:05:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}女王交给凯撒的讯息{\r}\NFrom the Egyptian queen, a message for Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,4:05:52.73,4:05:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}读出来，亚格里巴 抵达罗马的时候她的愿望将一一实现{\r}\NRead it. Whatever she wants will be granted upon her arrival in Rome.
Dialogue: 0,4:05:57.24,4:06:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}走在我座驾旁时再来讨论{\r}\NWe will discuss it as she walks beside my chariot.
Dialogue: 0,4:06:01.91,4:06:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}写着什么？{\r}\NWhat is it?
Dialogue: 0,4:06:03.49,4:06:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}我唯一的愿望{\r}\N"My one wish, which I implore you to grant...
Dialogue: 0,4:06:06.79,4:06:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}是葬在安东尼身旁{\r}\N...is to be buried at the site of Antony and to remain there...
Dialogue: 0,4:06:10.46,4:06:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}直到天荒地老，永不分离{\r}\N...until all things end."
Dialogue: 0,4:07:06.22,4:07:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}她这样合乎高贵礼仪吗？{\r}\NWas this well done of your lady?
Dialogue: 0,4:07:11.27,4:07:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}极为高贵{\r}\NExtremely well.
Dialogue: 0,4:07:13.94,4:07:15.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}许多…{\r}\NAs befitting...
Dialogue: 0,4:07:15.86,4:07:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}高贵的君主{\r}\N...the last of so many noble...
Dialogue: 0,4:07:19.70,4:07:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}最后都是如此{\r}\N...rulers.
Dialogue: 0,4:07:27.83,4:07:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}罗马人问道：{\r}\NAnd the Roman asked:
Dialogue: 0,4:07:30.25,4:07:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}这样做合乎高贵礼仪吗？{\r}\N"Was this well done of your lady?"
Dialogue: 0,4:07:34.00,4:07:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}婢女回答：{\r}\NAnd the servant answered:
Dialogue: 0,4:07:36.75,4:07:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}极为高贵{\r}\N"Extremely well.
Dialogue: 0,4:07:39.63,4:07:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}多高贵的君主{\r}\NAs befitting the last...
Dialogue: 0,4:07:42.05,4:07:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑体\fs24}最后都是如此{\r}\N...of so many noble rulers."
